(5, 6, 'Extreme Quad Biking In Coorg', 'Outdoor Fun', 'Cauvery River Road, Attur Forest, ', 'Karnataka', '571234', 900.00, 'Quad biking is done on an all-terrain vehicle, which is test-proven to have a good grip on any type of terrain. Before you start on the trail in this 90-minute experience, you will be given an orientation about quad bikes and the trail.\r\n\r\nThe biking center is near Dubare elephant camp, which is 8 km from Madikeri. Expert guides will accompany those who are below 15 years of age and others who opt for it.All through your 4 km biking trail, you will be passing through dense forests, while taking in the luxuriant outdoors. As you speed along, you will feel the wind on your face, with the same rigour – as your ride and adventure. You will come across curves that will test the endurance and grip of the rider, as you swerve a bit and then negotiate to get back on track. It will drive you to the edge, at times, but you can be rest-assured that you will not be thrown off-gear.\r\n\r\nThe ride through the slush in the midst of paddies will teach you to grapple with “soft-earth” grounds, where you need to be steady and be in motion, with your wheels whipping out the slush. Post your adventure, a look at the mud coat on your vehicle will gently remind you of the born-tough tires, of your bike.', 'PRICE INCLUDES:\r\n10 minutes of briefing on the handling of the ATV and the terrain\r\nExpert guides to accompany on the trail\r\nHelmets for the ride\r\n\r\nPRICE EXCLUDES:\r\nMeals/ Snacks\r\n\r\nLANGUAGES:\r\nEnglish\r\nKannada\r\n\r\nADDITIONAL DETAILS:\r\nSelf driving only for above 15 year old people', '', 'The ride through the slush in the midst of paddies will teach you to grapple with “soft-earth” grounds, where you need to be steady and be in motion, with your wheels whipping out the slush. Post your adventure, a look at the mud coat on your vehicle will gently remind you of the born-tough tires, of your bike.', '0145', 'Cauvery River Road, Attur Forest, Karnataka 571234, India', '0800', '5.jpg', 6, 'Active', '2018-02-28 08:48:29'),
(6, 5, 'Open Jeep Night Tour of Jaipur City Lights', 'Outdoor Fun', NULL, 'Jaipur', NULL, 3000.00, 'The tour starts after meeting your driver in your hotel lobby. \r\n\r\nFirst you will drive to the Amber fort to see the breathtaking play of lights on this majestic building. Located high on a hill Amer Fort\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\'s views are the principal tourist attraction in the Jaipur area.\r\n\r\nNext drive to Jal mahal palace to see the beautiful reflection of lights in the crystal clear lake that surrounds it. Continue the drive uphill to Nahargarh fort to see the breathtaking bird\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\'s eye view of illuminated Jaipur City. The view of the city from the fort is incomparable at night.\r\n\r\nFurther drive to the Wind Palace to see the celebration of lights on the palace. Hawa Mahal or Wind Palace, is so named because it was essentially a high screen wall built so the women of the royal household could observe street festivals while remaining unseen from the outside world.\r\n\r\nFinally drive further into the city to see Albert Hall all lit up at night. This tour will leave a long lasting memory of how truly beautiful Jaipur city is at night.\r\n\r\nDriver will drive you back to the hotel safely before wishing you a good night and sweet dreams.', 'Confirmation will be received at time of booking\r\nA warm jacket is recommended to bring during the winter since it can get cold at night\r\n\r\n\r\nPrice includes:\r\nHotel pickup and drop-off within Jaipur city\r\nTour in an open air Jeep\r\nPrivate driver\r\nFuel, parking fees, taxes and surcharges\r\n\r\n\r\nPrice Exclusions:\r\nLight and sound show tickets at Amber fort\r\nGratuities (optional)\r\nFood and drinks', 'Prices valid from 01st April 2018 to 31stMarch 2019\r\n Check-In / Check-out time at all the properties would at 1200 hrs (Noon)\r\n Mountain Trails Adventures & Expeditions Pvt. Ltd. will not bear any cost for flight cancelled or delayed due to Bad weather or any