(3, 'Hampta Pass Trek', 'Manali', NULL, '2017-06-26', '2019-12-31', 7000.00, 5000.00, 0, 0, 4, '3.jpg', 'north', 5, 4, 5, 'adventure,,family,honeymoon,romantic,sightseen,summer', 4, 0, 'Overview', 'Inclusions', '', 'Exclusions', 'Payment Policy', 'Cancellation Policy', 'Terms & Conditions', 4, 1),
(4, 'Chanderkhani Pass Trek', 'Himachal Pradesh', NULL, '2017-06-26', '2019-12-31', 6000.00, 5000.00, 0, 0, 4, '4.jpg', 'north', 5, 4, 4, 'adventure,,family,honeymoon,romantic,sightseen,summer', 4, 0, 'This breathtaking Chanderkhani Pass trek encompasses a plethora of jaw-dropping sights alongside the gorgeous environs of Himachal Pradesh.  This trekking package in India begins at Naggar and after crossing the Chanderkhani Pass at 3600m, the trail heads to the Malana village, famous for its distinct and very reserved social culture.\r\n\r\nThis trek is laden with a bunch of beautiful alpine pastures offering gorgeous views of some of the highest snow covered mountain peaks and open valleys. The trail requires walking through the blue Pine and Deodar, walnut, golden Oak and wild Cherry. The remarkable sight from the pass is magnified by the Bara bangal range towering high in the west while the Pir Panjal ranges fall in the north and Parvati in the east. A typical trek up in the hills of Himachal Pradesh, Chanderkhani Pass is one those Himachal trekking packages that is ideal for all trekking enthusiasts and nature lovers.', 'Inclusions', '', 'Exclusions', 'Payment Policy', 'Cancellation Policy', 'Terms & Conditions', 4, 1),
(5, 'Camping in Coorg', 'Karnataka', NULL, '2017-06-26', '2019-12-31', 3000.00, 2000.00, 0, 0, 4, '5.jpg', 'south', 2, 1, 2, 'adventure,,romantic,sightseen,summer', 4, 0, 'Witness whirling trails, picturesque tea and coffee plantations, numerous trekking routes and the hilly environs of the Scotland of India; Coorg and enjoy a fun and exciting two day tented camping experience here. Embark on a guided waterfall tour and discover the fascinating cascades situated in one of the private estates in Bettigeri. Enjoy camping at night and relax by the bonfire and enjoy delicious barbequed snacks. Explore the wilderness of Coorg and take a nature walk around the landscape of the beautiful southern hill station before you leave camp towards home. You can explore the attractions nearby namely, the Rajas Seat, Omkareshwara Temple, Abbi Falls, Talacauvery and Bhagamandala.', 'Jackets/Sweater - Night and mornings are cold. The weather is highly unpredictable. Therefore, carrying a light jacket or a sweater is recommended.', '', 'Consumption of alcohol or any other intoxicating products is strictly prohibited during this trip.\r\nFor safety purposes, do pay heed to the guidelines given by the instructors.', 'Payment Policy', 'If cancellations are made 15 days before the start date of the trip, no cancellation fees will be applicable.\r\nIf cancellations are made within 7-15 days before the start date of the trip, 10% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.', 'Terms & Conditions', 4, 1),
(6, 'Bandipur Wildlife Safari In Chamarajanagar', 'Karnataka', NULL, '2017-06-26', '2019-12-31', 5200.00, 4700.00, 0, 0, 4, '6.jpg', 'east', 2, 2, 1, 'adventure,,romantic,sightseen,summer', 4, 0, 'Spend a 2N/2D safari camping experience in Bandipur, a forested region nestled in the Chamarajanagar district of the Karnataka, bordering Mudumalai National Park and Wayanad Wildlife Sanctuary. \r\n    A perfect place for nature enthusiasts and animal lovers, the safari will surely take you on a ride of a lifetime. Enjoy the sight of the lovely animals in a pleasant environment with dark green hues all around you. \r\n    Head for an alluring jungle safari post your check-in to your hotel, dine in amazing food and indulge in a warm campfire under the stars at night.\r\n    Experience an adventure trek on Day 2 and head for a serene nature walk in the midst of calm environs.\r\n    Visit the Mysore zoo and explore the unique variety of wildlife in one of the best zoos of India before you leave for Bangalore around 04:30 PM.', 'Meals, Transport, Activities, Accomodation', '', 'Exclusions', 'Payment Policy', 'If cancellations are made 15 days before the start date of the trip, no cancellation fees will be applicable.\r\nIf cancellations are made within 7-15 days before the start date of the trip, 10% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\n\r\nThe applicable refund amount will be processed within 10 business days', 'Terms & Conditions', 4, 1),
(7, 'River Rafting in Betwa River, Orchha', 'Madhya Pradesh', NULL, '2017-06-26', '2019-12-31', 3000.00, 2000.00, 0, 0, 4, '7.jpg', 'east', 3, 2, 3, 'adventure,,art-culture,family,fort-palaces,shopping', 4, 0, 'Rafting in the river Betwa is also possible and the rafting starts from the boat club. Tickets are arranged through MP tourism and are available at the Betwa retreat or at the Hotel Sheesh Mahal. It could cost you around Rs. 1000 per hour or more per raft and a single raft would take 1-6 persons.', 'Inclusions', '', 'Exclusions', 'Payment Policy', 'Cancellation Policy', 'Terms & Conditions', 4, 1),
(8, 'Scuba Diving in Malvan', 'Maharashtra', NULL, '2017-06-26', '2019-12-31', 8500.00, 8250.00, 0, 0, 3, '8.jpg', 'east', 2, 1, 1, 'adventure,,family,honeymoon,romantic,sightseen,summer', 3, 0, 'Within these two delightful days, you will be discovering the stunning and magical beauty of Malvan’s underwater world. \r\n    Starting late night; around 08:00 PM, from Bangalore, an overnight bus journey will take you to Malvan and at around 07:00AM, you will be arriving Belgaum, where you can get freshened up and have your breakfast. After relaxing for a while, continue with your bus journey and reach Malvan by mid-noon; around 12:30PM. \r\n    Arriving in the town, check-in into a hotel and make yourself comfortable with a delicious buffet lunch and some rest. Post this, visit the Tsunami Island in Malvan and indulge is exciting water activities like banana boat ride, bumper boat ride and island tour. If you wish to, you can also go for parasailing on this day; however, parasailing can only be availed at an additional cost and you can pay for it while in the bus. \r\n    Returning from the island by evening, enjoy a buffet dinner beside the bonfire and retire for the night in the hotel. \r\n    Begin the day with an energising drink of tea and biscuits in the hotel followed by your transfer towards the boat jetty. Post this, you will be taken towards the jetty, from where a boat will take you to the decided spot. \r\n    Arriving at the decided spot, the trip guides and instructors will brief you about the dos and don’ts of diving. Once done with the briefing, gear up with the necessary equipment and take a dive into the kaleidoscopic waters of Malvan. \r\n    Post this, you can also go for snorkelling and take a look at the enchanting marine life beneath the clear waters of Malvan. By the time, snorkelling gets over, it will be time for lunch.\r\n    By late afternoon; at around 04:00PM, wish adieu to this exotic holiday destination and embark on the return trip to Bangalore via Belgaum; you will be reaching Bangalore by next day morning.\r\n    Depth of Water: Less than 35ft', 'Comfortable and casual clothing\r\nEven if you are not an expert swimmer, you can participate in this scuba diving tour.\r\nAs you will be touring around eco-friendly destinations, do not participate in or encourage littering in any form.\r\nWear clothes that do not restrict your body movements', '', '', '', 'If any cancellations are made before the start date of the trip, 100% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIn case of unforeseen weather conditions or government restrictions, certain activities may be cancelled and in such cases the operator will try his best to provide an alternate feasible activity. However no refund will be provided for the same.\r\nThe applicable refund amount will be processed within 10 business days', '', 4, 1),
(9, 'Goecha La Trek', 'Sikkim', NULL, '2017-06-26', '2019-12-31', 15000.00, 13680.00, 0, 0, 3, '9.jpg', 'north', 9, 8, 4, 'adventure,,honeymoon,romantic,sightseen,summer', 3, 0, 'Pack your bags to take part in a 9 day long trekking to Goechala in Sikkim and enjoy the tough paths to the top of several snowy hills.\r\n    Your trek starts from Yuksom, enjoy an overnight stay there and from the next day onward you will be trekking all around.\r\n    Start the trek to Sachen from Yuksom which will take almost five hours, rivet in the beauty of Rathong river valley and also enjoy the serenity of  Tshushay Khola falls.\r\n    Trek for four hours from Sachen to reach Tshoka where you will spot monasteries and cafes and also have a glimpse of the majestic Pandim mountain in Kanchenjunga.\r\n    The next day will be really awesome since you will get a chance to see various peaks in the Himalayas from Phedang and Dzongri.\r\n    Dzongri top is the main destination for the fifth day of the tour from where you can experience an enthralling view of many peaks spreading in the Kanchenjuga range.\r\n    Reach Thansing for an overnight stay and from Thansing you will trek to Lamuney the next day which will take 2 to 3 hours and also have the sight of Samiti lake for a while.\r\n    Get back to Lamuney for an overnight stay and then wake up for the most challenging trek the next morning to Goecha La and then walk to Thansing that consumes almost 11 hours of your day.\r\n    Enjoy the trail to Tshoka through the thick forest and you will reach the destination after 7 hours of walk and take rest in the camps.\r\n    Trek back to Tshoka from Thansing which will take 7 hours at the maximum and then on the last day you will reach Yuksom by evening where your tour ends.', 'Comfortable footwear, Camera, Guide,Breakfast Included, Lunch Included, Dinner Included', '', 'Exclusions', 'Payment Policy', 'If any cancellations are made before the start date of the trip, 100% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\n\r\nIn case of unforeseen weather conditions or government restrictions, certain activities may be cancelled and in such cases the operator will try his best to provide an alternate feasible activity. However no refund will be provided for the same.\r\n\r\nNo refund', 'Terms & Conditions', 4, 1),
(10, 'Rishikesh Rafting with Jungle Camp Stay', 'Uttarakhand', NULL, '2017-06-26', '2019-12-31', 2700.00, 2500.00, 0, 0, 4, '10.jpg', 'north', 2, 1, 2, 'adventure,,art-culture,family,shopping,sightseen,summer', 4, 0, 'For adventure junkies – Rishikesh has always been a favourite destination to satiate their thirst for adventure. Shed off all your office worries and get ready to lunge deep into the adventure world with friends and family. Get ready for an unforgettable experience while chilling out with your gang in this lovely abode.\r\n\r\nCrowned amidst stunning landscapes and picturesque natural beauty, adventure activities at Elephant Brook Resort, Rishikesh provides you with an array of activities; give a head start to your excursion with a rafting experience like never before. Enthral in this thrilling rafting exercise, fight the roaring tides as you balance your raft over the gushing water. You can also quench your adventure thirst by indulging in a thrilling body surfing while relaxing in Elephant Brook Resort, Rishikesh.\r\n\r\nBoost up your adrenaline as you head for a thrilling activity of cliff jumping. Feel your heart racing as you dive into icy-cold water in the stream below. Prepare to make some thrilling memories that you would cherish forever while indulging in adventure activities at Elephant Brook Resort, Rishikesh.', 'Meal, Activity, Vegetarian and Non- Vegetarian -Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner', '', 'Exclusions', 'Payment Policy', 'Cancellation Policy', 'Terms & Conditions', 4, 1),
(11, 'Jeep Safari at Kaziranga National Park', 'Assam', NULL, '2017-06-26', '2019-12-31', 17000.00, 15999.00, 0, 0, 4, '11.jpg', 'north', 4, 3, 2, 'adventure,,family,romantic,sightseen,summer', 4, 0, 'Indulge in this exciting wildlife tour in Kazairanga and get a chance to witness the diversifies flora and fauna at the Kaziranga National Park.\r\nStart your tour after getting picked up from the airport and leave for Kaziranga for a 6 hours journey.\r\nCheck into the hotel in Kaziranga and in the evening enjoy a refreshing walk by the river side.\r\nStart your morning ith a delightful elephnat safari and eplore the places.\r\nContinue your day with a jeep safari through the Kaziranga National Park in the central, eastern and western range.\r\nThis is a great opportunity for naturalist and wildlife lovers as you get a chance to witness the most rare and famous one horned rhino.\r\nGet a chance to spot some of the rare migratory birds in this region and Hoolock gibbons in the Burhapahar range in another jeep safari.\r\nEnd your tour by driving back to Guwahati.', '01 elephant ride,  3 rounds of Jeep safari, 1 Jungle Trail at Kaziranga, Entry fees', '', 'Exclusions', 'Payment Policy', 'If cancellations are made 30 days before the start date of the trip, 25% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made 15-30 days before the start date of the trip, 50% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made within 0-15 days before the start date of the trip, 100% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.', 'Terms & Conditions', 4, 1),
(13, 'Kareri Lake Trek', 'Himachal Pradesh', NULL, '2017-06-27', '2019-12-31', 20000.00, 17500.00, 0, 0, 5, '13.jpg', 'north', 8, 7, 4, 'adventure,,family,honeymoon,romantic,sightseen,summer', 5, 0, 'With the trek altitude of 3,300m above the sea level, the Kareri Lake Dharamshala or the Kumarwah Lake is one of the most stunning lakes in Himachal Pradesh. With the melting snow of the Dhauladhar Range as the source of water, this quaint lake and the terrains that leads to it, entices trekkers from different corners of the world.\r\n\r\nWhile the Dhauladhar Range adds to the mesmeric appeal of this lake, the fact that it remains frozen during early December to March/April, serves as the main attraction of this trek. The Kareri Lake trekking originates from the Kangra District of Himachal Pradesh and takes the participants through lush forests, narrow terrains, whirly passes, scenic meadows and much more. Adding more, while on this trek, the trekkers can also participate in local tours and adventure activities like Tyrolean Traversing.\r\n\r\nDuration of the Tour: 7N/8D\r\n\r\nAltitude: 3,300m\r\n\r\nActivities: Lake Visit, Tyrolean Traversing, Local Market Visit\r\n\r\nTotal Trekking Distance: 29km\r\n\r\nDifficulty Level: Easy to Moderate', 'Camping, kitchen and dining tents.\r\nSleeping bags and carry mats.\r\nAll meals during the trek as mentioned in the meal details.\r\nExperienced and qualified guides.\r\nCook and camp assistance', '', 'With the trek altitude of 3,300m above the sea level, the Kareri Lake Dharamshala or the Kumarwah Lake is one of the most stunning lakes in Himachal Pradesh. With the melting snow of the Dhauladhar Range as the source of water, this quaint lake and the terrains that leads to it, entices trekkers from different corners of the world.\r\n\r\nWhile the Dhauladhar Range adds to the mesmeric appeal of this lake, the fact that it remains frozen during early December to March/April, serves as the main attraction of this trek. The Kareri Lake trekking originates from the Kangra District of Himachal Pradesh and takes the participants through lush forests, narrow terrains, whirly passes, scenic meadows and much more. Adding more, while on this trek, the trekkers can also participate in local tours and adventure activities like Tyrolean Traversing.\r\n\r\nDuration of the Tour: 7N/8D\r\n\r\nAltitude: 3,300m\r\n\r\nActivities: Lake Visit, Tyrolean Traversing, Local Market Visit\r\n\r\nTotal Trekking Distance: 29km\r\n\r\nDifficulty Level: Easy to Moderate', 'Payment Policy', 'Cancellation Policy', 'Terms & Conditions', 4, 1),
(14, 'Chadar Frozen River Trek', 'Jammu and Kashmir', NULL, '2017-06-27', '2019-12-31', 30000.00, 27900.00, 0, 0, 4, '14.jpg', 'north', 9, 8, 4, 'adventure,,honeymoon,romantic,sightseen,summer', 4, 0, 'Make use of this opportunity to take part in Chadar Trek which is for nine days and experience the real sense of adventure and thrill amidst the thick snow of the Himalayas.\r\n    A trail on the Zanskar River will add on to the level of excitement you can ask for. January and February are the best months to indulge in Chadar trek and don\'t delay yourself and miss the fun.\r\n    You will feel the chilling climate as the temperature goes down till -35 degrees during winter and everywhere you will be able to see the white coloured serenity alone.\r\n    The trip starts from Delhi and goes through the major places like Leh, Tilad Do, Chilling, Gyalpo, Tibb Cave, Naerak etc and winds up after you get dropped off at Delhi on the last day of the trek.\r\n    The package includes food, accommodation in tents and round trip flight tickets.', 'All veg meals during the trek.\r\nOnly breakfast will be provided while stay in guest house.\r\nAll necessary permits and entry fees.\r\nFirst aid medical kit.\r\nQualified and experienced trek guide and support staff.\r\nInsurance up to Rs. 1 lakh.\r\nAll taxes.\r\nDelhi - Leh - Delhi economy class flight', '', 'Rucksack 55-65 lts & Knap sack.\r\nWaterproof, high ankle hiking boots or gumboots to wear over hiking/trekking shoes.\r\nTrekking pole.\r\nSeven pairs of thermal, thick wool and synthetic socks and seven pairs of liner socks', 'Payment Policy', 'If cancellations are made 30 days before the start date of the trip, 25% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made 15-30 days before the start date of the trip, 50% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made within 0-15 days before the start date of the trip, 100% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\n\r\nThe applicable refund amount will be processed within 10 business days', 'The customer receives a confirmation voucher via email within 12 hours of successful booking.\r\nIn case the preferred slots are unavailable, an alternate schedule of the customer’s preference will be arranged and a new confirmation voucher will be sent via email.\r\nAlternatively, the customer may choose to cancel their booking and a full refund will be processed.', 4, 1),
(15, 'Markha Valley Trek', 'Jammu and Kashmir', NULL, '2017-06-27', '2019-12-31', 21000.00, 20000.00, 0, 0, 4, '15.jpg', 'north', 8, 7, 5, 'adventure,,family,honeymoon,romantic,sightseen,summer', 4, 0, 'Visit the dream land of Ladakh – a virgin land untouched by urbanisation! Pack your bags and set upon a trek that will acquaint you with the most beautiful landscapes Mother Nature has in store for you. This trek will give the most exotic views and the largest variety of trails to follow.\r\n\r\nDuring the course of this trek, you will be witness to deep gorges, alpine grasslands and canyon walls. Make your way up to passes like the Kongmaru La and Ganda La at an altitude of 5,200m and 4,900m respectively. Get familiar with the lifestyle of the locals and have a thrilling time crossing the Markha River.\r\n\r\nA very popular trek among adventurers, this is your best opportunity to scale great heights and feel on top of the world, literally!\r\n\r\nAltitude: 5300m\r\n\r\nTemperature Range: July: 25-30 Degrees (Daytime),  4-15 Degrees (evening)', 'Camping, kitchen, dining, sleeping bags and carry mats.\r\nTrek guides and instructors.\r\nCooks, camp helpers and horseman with horses to carry loads', '', 'Backpack 35- 40L or small day pack of 20L.\r\nWater bottles.\r\nTrekking gears: shoes, warm gloves, socks, raincoat, jackets, hiking trousers and shirts.\r\nFlashlight with extra cells', 'Payment Policy', 'If any cancellations are made before the start date of the trip, 100% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIn case of unforeseen weather conditions or government restrictions, certain activities may be cancelled and in such cases the operator will try his best to provide an alternate feasible activity. However no refund will be provided for the same.', 'Terms & Conditions', 4, 1),
(16, 'Stok Kangri Expedition', 'Jammu and Kashmir', NULL, '2017-06-27', '2019-12-31', 20000.00, 18500.00, 0, 0, 4, '16.jpg', 'north', 9, 8, 4, 'adventure,,family,fort-palaces,honeymoon,romantic,sightseen,summer', 4, 0, 'The Stok Kangiri is the highest mountain range of the Himalayas in the Ladhak region, making this a very popular and challenging trek. \r\n    Your trek starts with your arrival from Delhi to Leh.\r\n    Spend some time and acclimatize yourself with the exquisiteness and the cold weather.\r\n    Start your trek to Stok, the whole path to the Stok Village is full of natural grandeur and flourishing green trees.\r\n    Reach Chang Ma, from where you head over to the Base Camp.\r\n    This destination of your base camp is blessed with lush greenery and numerous water bodies, your guide will train you and prepare you for your trek to Stok Kangri.\r\n    Trek for around 9-10 hours and reach the summit of Stok Kangri from where you can view the Karakoram Range to your north and Zanskar Range to your south.\r\n    Travel back to the base camp and then depart back to Leh.', 'Transport. \r\nBreakfast (Veg Only). \r\nTrekking. \r\nCamping. \r\nTrekking equipment. Necessary permits. \r\nFirst aid medical kits. \r\nQualified and experienced trek leader, guide, and support staff.', '', 'Shirts and trousers 3- 4 pairs.\r\nFleece jacket/ woollen sweater.\r\nWater and wind proof jacket.\r\nThermal top and bottom.\r\nWarm jacket.\r\nTwo 1 ltr water bottles (preferably thermos flasks)', 'Payment Policy', 'If any cancellations are made before the start date of the trip, 100% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIn case of unforeseen weather conditions or government restrictions, certain activities may be cancelled and in such cases the operator will try his best to provide an alternate feasible activity. However no refund will be provided for the same.\r\nNo refund applicable', 'This is a group tour.', 4, 1),
(17, 'The best of Leh-Ladakh', 'Jammu and Kashmir', NULL, '2017-06-27', '2019-12-31', 350000.00, 28500.00, 0, 0, 3, '17.jpg', 'north', 10, 9, 5, 'adventure,,art-culture,family,fort-palaces,honeymoon,romantic,shopping,sightseen,summer', 3, 0, 'A plethora of mind blowing places is Ladakh, a destination everyone keeps in their bucket list. \r\n    The rugged roads, the tough screes of the Himalayas, the monasteries flanked by the prayer flags, the high altitude adventurous spots, the colour changing lakes and moreover the hundreds of bikes, vehicles and passengers make Ladakh always vivacious.\r\n    Here comes a 10 day extensive tour of Ladakh starting from Srinagar just to satiate your thirst for enjoying the best of Ladakh in one trip.\r\n    Leh, Nubra Valley, Pangong Lake, Jispa and Manali are the locations you would encounter during the journey.\r\n    The package includes food, accommodation in hotels and transportation throughout the tour.', 'Breakfast and dinner on all days.\r\nExpert guide driver.\r\nNewly introduced environment fee of INR 450 per pax.\r\nSightseeing.\r\nDouble sharing rooms at all locations', '', 'Comfortable footwear.\r\nComfortable clothes.\r\nWater bottle.\r\nTrekking shoes.\r\nInsect repellent.\r\nPersonal medicine kit, if any.\r\nSunscreen.', 'Payment Policy', 'If cancellations are made 30 days before the start date of the trip, 25% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made 15-30 days before the start date of the trip, 50% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made within 0-15 days before the start date of the trip, 100% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\n\r\nThe applicable refund amount will be processed within 10 business days', 'This is a group tour.', 4, 1),
(18, 'Lamayuru Chilling Trek', 'Jammu and Kashmir', NULL, '2017-06-27', '2019-12-31', 17000.00, 15000.00, 0, 0, 3, '18.jpg', 'north', 5, 4, 4, 'adventure,,family,honeymoon,romantic,sightseen,summer', 3, 0, 'With Lamayuru to Chilling trek, experience Ladakh treks like never before! Be a part of an exotic experience that takes you through beautiful and challenging trails, giving you splendid mountain peak views.  Of all the trekking trips in India, this is surely one which will reveal natural treasures tucked away near the remote villages of Leh and Ladakh. \r\n\r\nWith this Lamayuru Chilling trek experience, walk through snow covered trails, cross rivers and pass villages that are not just beautiful but also hospitable. During the course of this trek, you will get to see beautiful views of the Stok and Karakoram ranges and get up and close with three passes namely Dung Dung Chan La Pass, Prinkti La Pass and the Kongskil La Pass, where you will be fascinated with unusual flora and fauna. Be part of a monastery visit and get an insight of the life and lifestyle of its residents. If you love to trek, be sure not to miss out on this Lamayuru to Chilling trek!\r\n\r\nAltitude: 4950m', 'Nutritious, high calorie vegetarian food.\r\nCamping, kitchen, and dining tents.\r\nSleeping bags and carry mats.\r\nVegetarian meals during the tour.', '', 'Good hiking shoes.\r\nSmall Day pack 20 Litres (if you do not want to carry your large backpack on a daily basis).\r\nHiking trousers and shirts, warm jackets, pullovers and raincoat.\r\nHiking gloves and extra pair of socks.\r\nFlash light with extra batteries.\r\nSunglasses and camera (optional).', '', 'If cancellations are made 30 days before the start date of the trip, 25% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made 15-30 days before the start date of the trip, 50% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made within 0-15 days before the start date of the trip, 100% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIn case of unforeseen weather conditions or government restrictions, certain activities may be cancelled and in such cases the operator will try his best to provide an alternate feasible activity. However no refund will be provided for the same.\r\n\r\nThe applicable refund amount will be processed within 10 business days', 'The customer receives a confirmation voucher via email within 24 hours of successful booking.\r\nIn case the preferred slots are unavailable, an alternate schedule of the customer’s preference will be arranged and a new confirmation voucher will be sent via email.\r\nAlternatively, the customer may choose to cancel their booking and a full refund will be processed.', 4, 1),
(19, 'Ladakh Cultural and Adventure', 'Jammu and Kashmir', NULL, '2017-06-27', '2019-12-31', 6000.00, 5000.00, 0, 0, 3, '19.jpg', 'north', 7, 6, 5, 'adventure,,art-culture,family,fort-palaces,honeymoon,romantic,sightseen,summer', 3, 0, 'Ask any adventurer, travel enthusiast or even just the next guy you see on the street and they will undoubtedly tell you that Ladakh in unmatched in its beauty and natural charms. Here, Mother Nature will meet you in all her majestic avatars, each more magnificent than the last. Where in Nubra you will see her as a maid laden with flowers, in Pangong Tso she will take on the guise of a demure lady in blue. You will see her giggling like a child in the mountain streams or roaring like an angry mother in the whoosh of the strong winds.\r\n\r\nA religion like Tibetan Buddhism that holds the core values of inner peace and tranquillity has a stronghold in this land, and once you come here, you will see why.\r\n\r\nDuration of the Tour: 6N/7D\r\n\r\nActivities: Sightseeing, Cultural Tour\r\n\r\nHighest Altitude: 18,380ft\r\n\r\nTemperature Range: 3 to 35 Degrees (Summer)', 'Travel assistance on arrival and departure from Leh.\r\nAccommodation on double occupancy basis at the above mentioned hotels/ camps or similar properties.\r\nEnvironmental cess and taxes as applicable.\r\nMeals as mentioned in the itinerary', '', 'Do not consume alcohol or any other intoxicants during the trek.\r\nClimatic conditions in the high altitudes vary from the plains; take adequate time to get acclimatized to high altitudes.\r\nAvoid roaming during the nights.\r\nCarry basic medications and a first-aid kit', '', 'If cancellations are made 15 days before the start date of the trip, no cancellation fees will be applicable.\r\nIf cancellations are made within 7-15 days before the start date of the trip, 10% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made within 3-6 days before the start date of the trip, 25% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made within 0-2 days before the start date of the trip, 50% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\n\r\nThe applicable refund amount will be processed within 15 business days', 'The customer receives a confirmation voucher via email within 24 hours of successful booking.\r\nIn case the preferred slots are unavailable, an alternate schedule of the customer’s preference will be arranged and a new confirmation voucher will be sent via email.\r\nAlternatively, the customer may choose to cancel their booking and a full refund will be processed.', 4, 1),
(20, 'A Tryst with Ladakh', 'Jammu and Kashmir', NULL, '2017-06-27', '2019-12-31', 15000.00, 13500.00, 0, 0, 4, '20.jpg', 'north', 4, 3, 4, 'adventure,,art-culture,family,fort-palaces,sightseen,summer', 4, 0, 'Your tryst with Ladakh begins at Delhi Airport from where you will take a flight to Leh Airport. After resting and getting acclimatised to the  high altitudes, your excursion to witness the unmatched beauty of this region begins. Get off to a great start, by watching the natural and architectural wonders like numerous monasteries, Magnetic Hill and quaint and beautiful villages enroute. Camp under the stars on the shores of the immaculate blue Pangong Tso Lake, get a taste of local life in the peculiar villages, drive by the highest motorable road in the world and all in all enjoy a trip to paradise that is Ladakh !\r\n\r\nDuration of the Tour: 3N/4D\r\n\r\nActivities: Sightseeing, Camel safari, Leisure\r\n\r\nHighest Altitude: Khardung La  Pass (18,380ft)\r\n\r\nTemperature Range: 3 to 35 Degrees (Summers)  -3 to -35 Degrees (Winters)', 'All transportation as mentioned in itinerary.\r\nAll meals as mentioned.\r\nAccommodation on twin sharing basis (based on hotels/camps selected).\r\nInnerline Permit for restricted areas.\r\nReach Ladakh Guide Book.', '', 'Do not consume alcohol or any other intoxicants during the tour.\r\nPay heed to the tour leaders or instructors in order to enjoy a safe and sound experience.\r\nAvoid roaming during the nights.\r\nCarry basic medications and a first-aid kit during the tour.\r\nThe tour takes place through eco-friendly zone; do not encourage littering the local sites or campsites.\r\nCost of this package cannot be clubbed with any other package', '', 'If cancellations are made 30 days before the start date of the trip, 25% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made 15-30 days before the start date of the trip, 50% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\nIf cancellations are made within 0-15 days before the start date of the trip, 100% of booking value will be charged as cancellation fees.\r\n\r\nThe applicable refund amount will be processed within 10 business days', 'The customer receives a confirmation voucher via email within 24 hours of successful booking.\r\nIn case the preferred slots are unavailable, an alternate schedule of the customer’s preference will be arranged and a new confirmation voucher will be sent via email.\r\nAlternatively, the customer may choose to cancel their booking and a full refund will be processed.', 4, 1),
