(461, 'Sarthak Regency Manali Volvo Package', 'Sarthak Regency Manali Volvo Package', NULL, '2018-01-04', '1970-01-01', 10000.00, 11900.00, 1, 4, 3, '1Manali.jpg', 'north', 1, 1, 4, 'adventure,,art-culture,fort-palaces,honeymoon', 3, 0, 'Manali with its unspoilt scenic grandeur is extremely popular with the tourists, for a lavish display of\r\nnatural scenery. It is one of the principal show places of the Kullu region. To its North, South and West are\r\nostentations of pinnacles and ridges which, in fine weather, stand out in bold relief against skyline. At the\r\nlower elevation and in every direction there are vivid green patches of grassland and evergreen valleys\r\nascending in irregular formation present probably the best view in the country.', '- 03 Nights accommodation on Twin/Triple sharing basis\r\n 03 breakfasts and 03 dinners per person in Manali Hotel\r\n Return Tickets from/to Delhi/Manali in Semi Sleeper AC Volvo Bus\r\n All local transfers and sightseeing by Non-Ac Vehicles\r\n Excursion to Jana Falls (Naggar) by Non-Ac Vehicles\r\n Local sightseeing in Manali by Non-Ac Vehicles\r\n All toll taxes, parking charges, driver allowances.\r\n All currently applicable hotel taxes except Applicable GST', 'transfer,accomodation,meals', 'The above Price doesn\'t include:\r\n Any Air or Rail fare.\r\n Any other meal not mentioned in price includes.\r\n Any other destination not mentioned in itinerary.\r\n Any Pony ride, adventure activities\r\n Excursion to Rohtang Pass by local Vehicle.\r\n Any monument entrance fees, camera fees, guide charges.\r\n Any expenses of personal nature.\r\n Applicable GST.', 'Advance Booking Fee\r\n        30 days or more before date of departure: 25% of total cost\r\n        29 - 20 days before date of departure: 50% of total cost\r\n        19 days or less before date of departure: 100% of total cost\r\n\r\n    Important : The booking stands liable to be cancelled if 100% payment is not received less than 20 days before date of departure.', 'If you Cancel your Holiday\r\n    You or any member of your party may cancel their travel arrangements at any time. Written notification or an e-mail to that effect from the person who made the booking must be received at our office. The cancellation charges applicable are as per the published cancellation policy below:\r\n\r\n    Cancellation charges per person\r\n        30 days or more before departure: 25% of total cost\r\n        29 – 20 days before departure: 50% of total cost\r\n        Less than 19 days before departure: 100% of total cost\r\n\r\n    If we change or cancel your holiday\r\n        We do plan the arrangements in advance. It is unlikely that we will have to make any changes to your travel arrangements.\r\n        Occasionally, we may have to make changes and we reserve the right to do so at any time. If there are any changes, we will advise you of them at the earliest possible date.\r\n        We also reserve the right under any circumstances to cancel your travel arrangements by assigning reasons to you.\r\n        If we are unable to provide the booked travel arrangements due to reasons beyond our control (e.g. bad weather):We shall first try to offer alternative dates for the tour if the tour hasn’t already commenced.\r\n        If the tour has already commenced, then we shall refund the booking price/fee charged to you on a pro-rata basis depending on the portion of the tour utilized by you.\r\n        In all circumstances, however, our liability shall be limited to refunding to you the price we charged as tour fees.\r\n\r\n    If you want to change your holiday plan\r\n    After confirmation of services, if you wish to change your travel arrangements in any way (e.g. your chosen departure date or accommodation), we will do our utmost to make these changes but it may not always be possible. Any request for changes must be in writing from the person who made the booking. All cost incurred due to amendment will be borne by you.\r\n\r\n    If you have a complaint\r\n    If you face any problem during your holiday, please inform the relevant supplier (e.g. your hotelier, transporter etc.) and/or our representative immediately who will endeavour to set things right. If your complaint is not resolved locally, please follow this up within 28 days of your return home by writing to us, with your booking reference and all other relevant information. However, please be advised that while we are happy to assist you in the redressal of your complaint, if any, we will be able to extend only our best efforts in managing/coordinating your complaint with the respective service provider. All third party service providers are independent contractors who are at no time under our control or supervision', 'Please note rooms are subject to availability. We are not holding any rooms.\r\n Few hotels / resorts used in the packages are located on the outskirts of the towns; specifically selected\r\nto avoid crowed areas and traffic congestions in the peak season.\r\n You can hire the snow-wears on the way to Snow Point, Manali on direct payment basis.\r\n It is mandatory to carry photo ID card (except Pan Card) while you are on tour.\r\n We will not be responsible for any change in the itinerary due to strikes, landslides, flight cancellations,\r\nweather conditions , government enforcements or any unforeseen circumstances which are beyond our\r\ncontrol. The additional cost incurred will be in addition to the cost and directly payable.\r\n Allocation of Seats in Volvo buses are on first-come- first basis and subject to availability. The\r\npassengers would have to reach the pickup point on their own.\r\n Most of the hotels offer complimentary heaters or are centrally heated. However, some hotels might\r\ncharge extra for the heaters provided. The cost for these heaters is not included in the package cost and\r\nhas to be directly paid at the hotel. The cost may vary from INR 100 to INR 300 per heater per night.\r\n Rohtang Excursion : the client can take the local State Transport Bus and visit Rohtang. The frequency of\r\nthese buses is good. The client has to get the tickets from the Bus Depot at Mall Road. The client can also\r\nconnect with the hotel staff for further guidance and timing schedule of the buses. The local cabs charge\r\nsomewhere between INR 2200 to INR 6000 depending on the demand - the hotel reception shall guide the\r\nguest on the same.\r\n Excursion to snow point will be organized by local vehicles as a rule by Himachal Local Taxi Union (on\r\ndirect payment basis)\r\n In case the client doesn’t want to visit Rohtang anyway, he can go for - Naggar sightseeing (half day),\r\nJana Waterfall trail (half day), Kullu (full day), Manikaran (full day) on direct payment basis. Note that all\r\nthe above mentioned sightseeing won’t be possible in one single day.\r\n\r\nGeneral Information:\r\nAll domestic Hotels/Transport rates are based on current tariff & subject to change without prior\r\nnotification; the revised rates will be charged extra.', 4, 1),
(475, 'TOP OF THE WORLD', 'Leh', NULL, '2018-02-17', '2018-09-30', 8800.00, 13999.00, 2, 4, 3, 'Manali_1519380285.jpg', 'north', 4, 3, 1, 'adventure,,family,sightseen,summer', 3, 0, 'Leh Kushok Bakula Airport (This must be one of the Most Sensational Flights in the World. On a clear day from one side of the aircraft can be seen in the distance the peaks of K2, Nanga Parbat, Gasherbrum and on the other side of the aircraft, so close that you feel you could reach out and touch it, is the Nun Kun massif.)', '', 'transfer,accomodation,meals,sightseen', '•	Any Airfare or GST (5%)\r\n•	Any Kind of Personal Expenses or Optional Tours / Extra Meals Ordered\r\n•	Anything not specifically mentioned under the head “Prices included”.\r\n•	The Services of Vehicle is not included on leisure days & after finishing the sightseeing as per the Itinerary\r\n•	Guide fee, Camera fee & any monument Entrances\r\n•	Medical & Travel insurance\r\n•	Any changes you may choose to make during your tour', '•	25% any time after confirmation ,\r\n•	50% Before 30 days of arrival date,\r\n•	100% before 15 days from date of departure', '•	25% any time after confirmation ,\r\n•	35% Before 30 days of arrival date,\r\n•	50% before 15 days from date of departure\r\n•	No Refund within 07 Days from the date of departure\r\n•	No Refund or Compensation on any changes on ongoing trip.', '	Prices valid from 01st April 2018 to 31stMarch 2019\r\n	Check-In / Check-out time at all the properties would at 0900 hrs \r\n	 Any price hike due to flight cancelled or delayed due to Bad weather or any other reason given by the airline. Cost for accommodation and transport in such cases will have to be borne by passenger.\r\n	There would be no refund for the road blocks at Nubra | Pangong & Tsomoriri due to natural calamity. \r\n	No Refund or Compensation for any unused services.\r\n	No changes in the date of travel once booked.\r\n	Room allotment will be as per availability at the time of check in, floor or view preferences are not guaranteed.\r\n	Food menu as per availability of vegetables based on Buffet | Fixed menus\r\n	Any dispute will be subject to Delhi jurisdiction\r\n	25% advance (Non Refundable) to be deposited at the time of booking confirmation & Balance 75% one month prior to arrival.\r\n	Cost of Child between 5 to 11 Yrs (Without Bed only) & for extra Bed kindly consider the cost of Extra Bed\r\n	Child below 5 Yrs of age will be complimentary.\r\n	Maximum 06 Pax can be accommodated in one vehicle (Scorpio or Similar)\r\n	Any addition in Tax or Fuel charge done by Airlines / Transport Company etc will be chargeable to group members.\r\n	The above rates are applicable strictly for resident Indian citizens only\r\n	Journey can be arranged from Chandigarh / Jammu Railway Station or Airport at Nominal Extra charges.\r\n	Hotel Accommodation in Chandigarh, Manali, Keylong, Jammu, Srinagar can be arranged on best deals.\r\n	Blocking of Rooms will be hold for period of 01 month only.', 5, 1),
