(822, 184, 'Arrival in Kuala Lumpur', '\"Welcome to Malaysia - a paradise for shoppers, Mecca for food lovers and every partygoers\r\ndream.\r\nUpon arrival, check in to the hotel and spend some time at leisure. We recommend that you opt for Kuala Seleangor Fireflies Tour or the Central Market Night Tour (on your own). Return to hotel for an overnight stay. \"'),
(823, 184, 'Kuala Lumpur Half-day City Tour', '\"After a scrumptious breakfast, get ready for the Kuala Lumpur Half-day City Tour.\r\nOn this tour you will visit Thean Hou Temple, Independence Square for Photo-stop, Passby National Mosque and Old Railway Station and then Depart to Royal Selangor Pewter for guided Factory tour.\r\nLater from Royal Selangor Pewter factory proceed to KLCC photo stop and then later proceed to MATIC for chocolate shopping. This half day city tour will end at Pavilion mall or guest can opt to take a drop back to hotel.\r\nSpend the rest of the day at leisure. Return to hotel for an overnight stay.\"'),
(824, 184, 'Day At Leisure / Sunway Lagoon for \"with Frills\" package', '\"After breakfast, enjoy the rest of the day at leisure.\r\nWith Frills Package:\r\nIf you opt for with frills package you will enjoy the Sunway Lagoon Tour . \r\nIn Sunway Lagoon, you will be experiencing the 5 theme parks with more than 80 rides and attractions which will be loved by the old and young alike. Fun, cheer, excitement and thrill - this is what best defines Asia\'s popular attraction, Sunway Lagoon.\r\nReturn to Kuala Lumpur in the evening for an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(825, 184, 'Transfer to Singapore and Board the Cruise', '\"After an early sumptuous breakfast, get ready to be transfered to Singapore by coach. Welcome to Singapore - a bustling metropolis, a shopper’s fantasy, an adventurer’s dream, and a foodie’s delight. Upon arrival, you will be taken to the Cruise Terminal.\r\nThereafter, board the Super Star Virgo cruise. Enjoy dinner and an overnight stay onboard the cruise.\"'),
(826, 184, 'Star Gemini Cruise', '\"Relish the sumptuous breakfast onboard the cruise. Indulge yourself in fun-filled activities and entertainment programmes. Enjoy your dinner and a comfortable overnight stay onboard the cruise.\r\n\"'),
(827, 184, 'Dis-embark Cruise / Day at Leisure', '\"Check in at the hotel and rest of the day is free to spend at leisure and explore the magnificent landmarks of Singapore.\r\nWelcome to Singapore - a bustling metropolis, a shopper’s fantasy, an adventurer’s dream, and a foodie’s delight. Upon arrival, you will be taken  to your hotel. Freshen up and relax, spend the rest of the day at Leisure. You can choose to experience the famous Night Safari Tour (on your own). Experience up close and personal encounters with over 2,500 nocturnal animals from 130 species. You will kick-start your adventure with a fiery Thumbuakar tribal performance and continue your journey with an exciting guided tram Safari Adventure through 7 geographical regions of the world, from the Himalayan Foothills to Equatorial Africa.       Complete your adventure with Creatures of the Night Show – an amazing show of nocturnal animals. Explore the walking trails, come close to the majestic leopard and feel the giant flying squirrel cruise above your head.\r\n\"'),
(828, 184, 'Half Day City Tour / Sentosa Experiential tour for \"with Frills\" package', '\"After enjoying a scrumptious breakfast at the hotel, gear up for an exciting half-day city tour of Singapore!\r\nYou will begin the tour with Gardens By The Bay - rated as \"\"Top 10 Indoor Gardens of the World\"\", featuring more than 500,000 plants from over 2,200 species. The Flower Dome replicates the cool and dry Mediterranean climate featuring 9 different gardens from 5 continents. Explore the highlands in the Cloud Forest,  amidst orchids, pitcher plants and ferns from a cool-moist Tropical Montane region, featuring one of the World\'s tallest indoor waterfalls at 35metres as well as 7 discovery zones. Be inspired by nature and let your wonder bloom and experiences flourish.\r\nNext, you will get to see the Merlion Statue – one of the hallmarks of Singapore. After that, you will stop at China Town where you can shop for reasonably priced trinkets and souvenirs. After that, we will take you to an amazing Chocolate Factory and Jewellery Shop. The tour will commence at Mt. Faber and Little India.\r\nWith Frills Package:\r\nif you opt for with frills package next on the cards for you is The Sentosa Experiential Tour.\r\nDiscover the underwater world at the world’s largest aquarium at Resorts World Sentosa Singapore.  Enjoy the rush of a Skyride and skid down the hills with the Luge, the first and only part go-cart, part-toboggan ride in Southeast Asia for an adrenalin rush. This tour ends with the spectacular show Wings Of Time – a dazzling display of laser lights and fireworks. Return to hotel for an overnight stay.\"'),
(829, 184, 'Day At Leisure / Universal Studios Tour for \"with Frills\" package', '\"After breakfast, spend the day at leisure.\r\nWith Frills Package:\r\nif you opt for with frills package you will visit the Universal Studios today, Asia\'s only Hollywood movie theme park featuring rides and attractions based on famous Hollywood animation movies such as Shrek, Battlestar Galactica and Madagascar. Experience death-defying stunts, explosions and an ocean of thrills at the Water World. Next, take a walk into pre-history at the Jurassic Park Rapids Adventure. Also, visit the Hollywood Boulevard for a stroll down the famous Walk of Fame.\"'),
(830, 184, 'Departure For India', 'After a hearty breakfast, you will have a few hours in Singapore before you leave for the airport and make your journey back to India. We sincerely hope you had a memorable time!'),
(831, 185, 'Arrive in Kuala Lumpur', 'Bid adieu to your home as you take a flight from the airport and arrive in Kuala Lumpur for your trip. Take the pre-arranged transfer to your hotel and check-in to your room. Spend some time relaxing and leave the room to visit the KLCC - Kuala Lumpur City Centre. Located at the north-east of the old city centre, it is the place that houses most of the city\'s shopping malls and the famous Petronas Twin Towers. Watch the metropolis cascaded in city lights, try mouth-watering dishes and return to your hotel late at night, for a relaxing over-night stay!'),
(832, 185, 'Kuala Lumpur', 'The city has it all - historic monuments, gardens, shopping malls, skyscrapers, bustling streets and amazing night spots. Best explored on foot, Kuala Lumpur has much to offer. Take the connecting bridge of the iconic Petronas Towers and click awe-inspiring pictures from the observation deck. Avoid the mishap of not getting a ticket and customise the package to include a visit to the Towers. Having enjoyed Kuala Lumpur\'s panoramic views, return to your hotel for a comfortable stay.'),
(833, 185, 'Kuala Lumpur', 'Kuala Lumpur is a city known for its food, so start your day with a visit to the Central Market, move on to Jalan P. Ramlee\'s Food Stalls and end your food journey at the famous Chinatown or choose from the various activities available in the customisation section. We\'ve already included a few exciting activities you can indulge in. Once you\'ve explored the city, return to your hotel for the night.'),
(834, 185, 'Kuala Lumpur to Singapore', 'This will be the day that you fly to Singapore so plan your day accordingly. Check-out from your hotel as per the hotel policies and get a transfer from there to the airport. Reach Singapore by afternoon, take the pre-arranged transfer to your hotel and check-in to your room. Spend the day relaxing in your room or take a walk at dusk by the Marina Bay. Return to your hotel for a relaxing overnight stay.'),
(835, 185, 'Singapore', 'Singapore is famous for its variety of foods and its shopping centres that sell things at throw-away prices. Therefore, spend your day trying dishes at the famous Chinatown, Gluttons Bay, Little India or shopping at Pedder-On-Scotts and 112 Katong. Explore the famous Vivo City Mall or shop for handicrafts at the Holland Road Shopping Centre. You can also indulge in the activity included in the package or use the customisation option to add activities of your choice! After having explored Singapore, return to your hotel for a relaxing night.'),
(836, 185, 'Singapore', 'Singapore is famous for its variety of foods and its shopping centres that sell things at throw-away prices. Therefore, spend your day trying dishes at the famous Chinatown, Gluttons Bay, Little India or shopping at Pedder-On-Scotts and 112 Katong. Explore the famous Vivo City Mall or shop for handicrafts at the Holland Road Shopping Centre. You can also indulge in the activity included in the package or use the customisation option to add activities of your choice! After having explored Singapore, return to your hotel for a relaxing night.'),
(837, 185, 'Depart from Singapore', 'As this will be your last day in Singapore, we suggest that you plan your day according to the time of your flight. Check-out from your hotel as per the hotel policies and get a transfer to the airport. As you board your flight, bid goodbye to the lion city and return safely to your home.'),
(838, 186, 'Delhi', '\"Our representative will receive you on arrival at the airport in Delhi and will take you to your hotel.\r\n\r\nNew Delhi the capital of India is one of the most charming & happening place in the world. With thousands of sightseeing places like India Gate, Red fort, Jama Masjid and of course The Connaught Place. This city has been beautifully planned with extra greenery to suite your eyes! Delhi is surely the travelers delight.\r\n\r\nActivities: Our full day tour of Delhi will highlight the remarkable contrast between Old and New Delhi. We will visit iconic historical monuments like Red Fort, Qutub Minar, Humayun’s Tomb, and the Jama Masjid which is also the largest mosque in Asia. Form the mosque we will take a ride in Rickshaw to absorb the sights and sounds of the famous Chandani Chowk market in the heart of Old Delhi.\r\n\r\nWe will also visit the Gandhi memorial at Raj Ghat, India Gate, Lotus Temple, Presidents residence, National Museum and modern wonders such as the Akshardham Temple.\"'),
(839, 186, 'Delhi', '\"Our representative will receive you on arrival at the airport in Delhi and will take you to your hotel.\r\n\r\nNew Delhi the capital of India is one of the most charming & happening place in the world. With thousands of sightseeing places like India Gate, Red fort, Jama Masjid and of course The Connaught Place. This city has been beautifully planned with extra greenery to suite your eyes! Delhi is surely the travelers delight.\r\n\r\nActivities: Our full day tour of Delhi will highlight the remarkable contrast between Old and New Delhi. We will visit iconic historical monuments like Red Fort, Qutub Minar, Humayun’s Tomb, and the Jama Masjid which is also the largest mosque in Asia. Form the mosque we will take a ride in Rickshaw to absorb the sights and sounds of the famous Chandani Chowk market in the heart of Old Delhi.\r\n\r\nWe will also visit the Gandhi memorial at Raj Ghat, India Gate, Lotus Temple, Presidents residence, National Museum and modern wonders such as the Akshardham Temple.\"'),
(840, 186, '\"Delhi – Haridwar By train  Haridwar – Rishikesh By road in .30 hr. (25 km)\"', '\"Also acknowledged as the ‘gateway to the Himalayas’, Rishikesh is pleasingly located where the holy river Ganges flows down the lap of Himalayas.\r\n\r\nThe famous Four-Shrine-Sacred-Journey of India ideally begins from Rishikesh. It is basically a Hindu pilgrimage center with magnificent temple of deities. There is Trivani Ghat – where devotees take holy dip in Ganges water.\r\n\r\nRishikesh is an ideal destination not only for pilgrims but also for those who want to delve deeper into meditation, yoga and other aspects of Hinduism. Rishikesh is also called the \"\"Yoga capital of the world\"\".\r\n\r\nFor the adventure hungers, there is a lot to soothe their nerve- From White Water Rafting to Rappelling and Kayaking!\r\n\r\nActivities: We will start our day with visits to Bharat Mandir, Kailash Niketan Temple and Satya Narayan Temple. Later we will visit a hallowed spot called ‘Vasishta Gufa’ – 2 caves where the Hindu sage and yogi Vasishta practiced spirituality.\r\n\r\nIn the evening we will proceed towards Parmarth Niketan Ashram for sunset Aarti, where you can enjoy and participate in religious singing with Ashram students.\r\n\r\nDuring our Haridwar excursion, we will visit Chandi Devi Temple, accessible only by a ropeway ride; Mansa Devi Temple and will explore the famous Har Ki Pauri ghat on the banks of Ganges. On the ghat experience the evening Aarti performed by priests accompanied by spiritual chants.\r\nRishikesh Parmarth Niketan Ashram\r\nRishikesh Parmarth Niketan Ashram\"'),
