(1004, 207, 'Ooty', '\"After breakfast proceed for sightseeing tour of Ooty. Visit the Botanical Garden, one of the best tourist attractions that allures visitors from all over the world. This garden was laid out in 1847 by the Marquis of Tweedale and is spread over 22 hectares ascending the slopes on the hill at an elevation of 2,400 meters above sea level. Later visit Doddabetta (highest point of the place), Ooty Lake and Rose Garden.\r\nLocated in the heart of Ooty, Rose Park is not even a km from Charing Cross at Vijayanagaram. It has been laid on 10 acres of land in terraces with rose tunnels, pergolas and bowers with rose creepers.\r\nOvernight stay at the hotel.\"'),
(1005, 207, 'Ooty – Coonoor – Coorg (238 Kms)', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will take you for a local tour of Coonoor, which includes a visit to Ketti valley view, Wenlock Downs, Lamb\'s Rock, Dolphin’s Nose Point, Sim\'s Park and Wellington Island. Later drive to Coorg andon arrival check-in at a hotel for overnight stay.'),
(1006, 207, 'Coorg', 'After breakfast full day city tour of Coorg, visit Dubare Elephant Camp, a forest camp on the banks of the River Kaveri where bathing and feeding of the elephants are done. Dubare elephant camp in Coorg is the perfect destination to enjoy Elephant rides and bird watching. In afternoon visit to Talacauveri, which is situated in the picturesque location of Brahmagiri hills. It is the origin of River Kaveri and a beautiful Talacauvery Temple built around it. Later, climb Brahmagiri peak and then pay a visit to Bhagamandala. Bhagamandala is famous for the confluence of the three sacred rivers, Kaveri, Sujyothi and Kanike. You can also visit to the temple dedicated to Bhagandeshwara (Lord Shiva) and get the blessings. Return to the hotel by evening for overnight stay.'),
(1007, 207, 'Coorg- Bangalore (260 kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Bangalore. On arrival at Bangalore, we will proceed to airport/railway station for your onward destination.'),
(1008, 208, 'Arrive Bangalore', 'On arrival at Bangalore our representative will meet you at the airport / railway station and assist you till your check in process at the hotel. Stay overnight at the hotel.'),
(1009, 208, 'Bangalore - Coorg (260 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Coorg. En-route visit Bylakuppe Tibetan Settlement (Golden Temple), the largest Tibetan settlement in India located near Kushalanagar in Kodagu District. The settlement set up in 1960 and holds several monasteries and temples of all major Vajrayana (Indo-Tibetan Buddhist) lineages. On arrival at Coorg, check-in at a hotel. Rest of the day is free for your own activity. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1010, 208, 'Coorg', 'After breakfast full day city tour of Coorg, visit Dubare Elephant Camp, a forest camp on the banks of the River Kaveri where bathing and feeding of the elephants are done. Dubare elephant camp in Coorg is the perfect destination to enjoy Elephant rides and bird watching. In afternoon visit to Talacauvery, which is situated in the picturesque location of Brahmagiri hills. It is the origin of River Kaveri and a beautiful Talacauvery Temple built around it. Later, climb Brahmagiri peak and then pay a visit to Bhagamandala. Bhagamandala is famous for the confluence of the three sacred rivers, Kaveri, Sujyothi and Kanike. You can also visit to the temple dedicated to Bhagandeshwara (Lord Shiva) and get the blessings. Return to the hotel by evening for overnight stay.'),
(1011, 208, 'Coorg - Wayanad (107 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Wayanad. On arrival, check into the hotel. Evening free for your own activity. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1012, 208, 'Wayanad', 'After breakfast proceed to Wayanad Wildlife Sanctuary. Later visit the Pookode Natural Lake, Soochipara Waterfalls, Muthanga Wildlife Sanctuary and Edakkal Caves (a prehistoric shelter made of natural rock formation). Throughout this journey you can enjoy different types of spice plantations like cardamom, vanilla, pepper, cinnamon, clove etc. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1013, 208, 'Wayanad - Mysore (105 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Mysore. On arrival, check-in at a hotel. Later proceed for city tour of Mysore and visit the ancient princely city that is famous for its silks, sandalwood and various palaces. The city has the largest palace in India, built in Indo-Persian style in 1900. Visit an art gallery and the Chamundeshwari Temple dedicated to Goddess Kali on Chamundi Hill, from where you can have a panoramic view of the city. We will also visit Somnathpur, which is famous for the temple of Keshava. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1014, 208, 'Mysore - Bangalore (160 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Bangalore. On arrival, we transfer you to airport / railway station for onward destination.'),
(1015, 209, 'Arrive Bangalore', 'On arrival at Bangalore our representative will meet you at the airport/railway station and assist you till your check in process at the hotel. Stay overnight at the hotel.'),
(1016, 209, 'Bangalore – Kodaikanal (460 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Ooty. Ooty is in deep within the Nilgiri hills, which is also known as The Blue Mountains. On arrival at Ooty, check in at a hotel.For rest of the day you are free for leisure. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1017, 209, 'Kodaikanal', 'After breakfast proceed for sightseeing tour of Kodaikanal. The tour will include a visit to Kurinji Andavar, Bryant\'s Park, Pillar\'s Rock, Coaker\'s Park, Green Valley View Point, Telescope House, Silent Valley View, Star Shaped Kodai Lake and Chettiar Park. Later in the evening transfer to the hotel for overnight stay.'),
(1018, 209, 'Kodaikanal – Bangalore (460 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Bangalore. On arrival at Bangalore, transfer to airport/railway station for your onward destination.'),
(1019, 210, 'Arrive Bangalore', 'On arrival at Bangalore, our representative will meet you at the airport/railway station and assist you till your check in process at the hotel. Stay overnight at the hotel.'),
(1020, 210, 'Bangalore – Ooty (265 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Ooty. Ooty is in deep within the Nilgiri hills that are also known as The Blue Mountains. On arrival at Ooty, check into a hotel.For the rest of the day you are free for leisure. Overnight stay atthe hotel.'),
(1021, 210, 'Ooty', '\"After breakfast proceed for sightseeing tour of Ooty. Visit the Botanical Garden, one of the best tourist attractions that allures visitors from all over the world. This garden was laid out in 1847 by the Marquis of Tweedale and is spread over 22 hectares ascending the slopes on the hill at an elevation of 2,400 meters above sea level. Later, visit Doddabetta (highest point of the place), Ooty Lake and Rose Garden.\r\nLocated in the heart of Ooty, Rose Park is not even a km from Charring Cross at Vijayanagaram. It has been laid on 10 acres of land in terraces with rose tunnels, pergolas and bowers with rose creepers. \r\nOvernight stay at the hotel.\"'),
(1022, 210, 'Ooty – Coonoor – Kodaikanal (280 Kms)', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will take you for a local tour of Coonoor, which includes a visit to Ketti valley view, Wenlock Downs, Lamb\'s Rock, Dolphin’s Nose,Sim\'s Park and Wellington Island. Drive to Kodaikanal in the afternoon. On arrival check-in at a hotel for overnight stay.'),
(1023, 210, 'Kodaikanal', 'Famous as the king of hill stations, Kodaikanal is situated at an altitude of about 2,133m amidst the folds of the verdant Palani hills and covers an area of 21.45 sq km. After breakfast proceed for local tour of Kodaikanal and visit the Kodaikanal Lake, Pillar Rocks, Coaker\'s Walk, Telescope Houses, Kurinji Andavar Temple, Silver Cascade and Bear Shola Falls. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1024, 210, 'Kodaikanal – Wayanad (366 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Wayanad. On arrival, check into the hotel. Evening free for your own activity. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1025, 210, 'Wayanad', 'After breakfast, proceed for game drive to Wayanad Wildlife Sanctuary. Later, pay a visit to Pookode Natural Lake, Soochipara Waterfalls, Muthanga Wildlife Sanctuary and Edakkal Caves (a prehistoric shelter made of natural rock formation). Throughout this journey you can enjoy different type of spice plantations like cardamom, vanilla, pepper, cinnamon, clove etc. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1026, 210, 'Wayanad – Coorg (120 kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Coorg. On arrival, check into the hotel. Rest of the day is free for leisure or your own activity. Overnight stay is at the hotel.'),
(1027, 210, 'Coorg', 'After breakfast full day city tour of Coorg, visit Dubare Elephant Camp, a forest camp on the banks of the River Kaveri where bathing and feeding of the elephants are done. Dubare elephant camp in Coorg is the perfect destination to enjoy Elephant rides and bird watching. In afternoon visit to Talacauveri, which is situated in the picturesque location of Brahmagiri hills. It is the origin of River Kaveri and a beautiful Talacauvery Temple built around it. Later, climb Brahmagiri peak and then pay a visit to Bhagamandala. Bhagamandala is famous for the confluence of the three sacred rivers, Kaveri, Sujyothi and Kanike. You can also visit to the temple dedicated to Bhagandeshwara (Lord Shiva) and get the blessings. Return to the hotel by evening for overnight stay.'),
(1028, 210, 'Coorg- Bangalore (260 kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Bangalore. On arrival at Bangalore, transfer to airport/railway station for your onward destination.'),
(1029, 211, 'Arrive Coimbatore – Coorg (368 Kms)', 'Upon arrival at Coimbatore railway station, meet our representative and drive straight to Coorg. On reaching, check into a hotel. For the rest of the day you are free for leisure. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1030, 211, 'Coorg', 'After breakfast full day city tour of Coorg, visit Dubare Elephant Camp, a forest camp on the banks of the River Kaveri where bathing and feeding of the elephants are done. Dubare elephant camp in Coorg is the perfect destination to enjoy Elephant rides and bird watching. In afternoon visit to Talacauveri, which is situated in the picturesque location of Brahmagiri hills. It is the origin of River Kaveri and a beautiful Talacauvery Temple built around it. Later, climb Brahmagiri peak and then pay a visit to Bhagamandala. Bhagamandala is famous for the confluence of the three sacred rivers, Kaveri, Sujyothi and Kanike. You can also visit to the temple dedicated to Bhagandeshwara (Lord Shiva) and get the blessings. Return to the hotel by evening for overnight stay.'),
(1031, 211, 'Coorg- Coimbatore (368 kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Coimbatore. On arrival at Coimbatore, transfer to railway station for your onward destination.'),
(1032, 212, 'Bangalore – Ooty', 'Morning meet with our representative and leave for Ooty. On arrival check into the hotel. Evening free to explore the beautiful & ravishing beauty of Ooty. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1033, 212, 'Ooty', 'Morning after breakfast full day excursion to Connor. Later return to Ooty. Afternoon free at leisure. Overnight stay at hotel'),
(1034, 212, 'Ooty – Coimbatore', 'Morning after breakfast, sightseeing of Ooty, visit the beautiful botanical garden designed in 1847. Visit the shores of Lake Ooty, where boating is a favourite pastime and Doddabetta Peak, the highest point in the Nilgiri mountains (2,623 m.). Later about 13:00 hrs transfer to Udamandalam railway station to board the TOY TRAIN for Metupalaiyam. On arrival meet with our representative and drive to Coaimbatore for overnight stay. Overnight at hotel.'),
(1035, 212, 'Coimbatore – Maduraimeenakshi-temple', 'Morning after breakfast drive to Madurai. On arrival check in at the hotel. After fresh-n-up visit the ancient city of Madurai, some 2600 years old is laid out in the banks of river Vaigai as a lotus flower with the Meenakshi temple in the centre. Visit including Meenakshi Temple, King Tirumala\'s Palace, Great tank and Gandhi museum. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1036, 212, 'Madurai – Rameshwaram', '\"Morning after breakfast an excursion to Rameshwaram- the most sacred temple town of India is an island hallowed by the epic Ramayana, where Lord Rama is said to have visited before going into battle of Srilanka. The presiding deity is the Linga Of Sri Ramanatha Swamy, which happens to be one of the twelve Jyotirlingas of India. Rameswaram is also popularly referred to as the \'Benaras of the south\'. In order to attain Moksha it is believed that the visit to Rameswaram is mandatory.\r\nLater after Pooja Darshan drive back to Madurai for overnight stay.\"'),
(1037, 212, 'Rameshwaram – Thanjavur', '\"Morning after breakfast drive to Tanjore. On arrival check in at the hotel. Later temple tour of Tanjore visiting Bridhadeswara temple, Tanjore palace & museum.. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\nTanjore - The home of Carnatic music, musical instruments, dance and traditional handicrafts, Tanjore (Thanjavur) is famous for the Brahadeeswarar Temple. The temple constructed more than a thousand years ago by the Chola King Raja Rajan is an architect\'s marvel. The Art Gallery and the Saraswathi Mahal Library are also well known places of interest.\"'),
(1038, 212, 'Thanjavur – Pondicherry', '\"Morning after breakfast drive to Pondichery. On arrival check in at the hotel. In the afternoon sightseeing of Pondichery. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\nPondicherry - Although the French influence is gradually fading, Pondicherry retains a few Gallic accents. Pondicherry\'s main sights are the Raj Nivas, the Sacred Heart Church and the Sri Aurobindo Ashram. The ashram retreat was founded in 1926 by Sri Aurobindo after whose death the spiritual authority passed to one of his disciples, a French woman known as the Mother. The Mother was also instrumental in founding the city of Dawn Auroville, 10 km from Pondicherry. Its original charter aimed at creating a city of the future where people from India and abroad could live and work together in a spiritual environment.\"'),
(1039, 212, 'Pondicherry – Bangalore', 'Morning free at leiusure. In the afternoon leave for Bangalore.'),
(1040, 213, 'Arrive Coimbatore - Kodaikanal (145 Kms)', '\"Our representative will meet you on arrival at Coimbatore Railway station, thereafter drive to Kodaikanal. On arrival, check into a hotel. Rest of the day you are free for leisure. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1041, 213, 'Kodaikanal', '\"After breakfast proceed for sightseeing tour of Kodaikanal, which includes a visit to Kurinji Andavar, Bryant\'s Park, Pillar\'s Rock, Coaker\'s Park, Green Valley View Point, Telescope House, Silent Valley View, Star Shaped Kodai Lake and Chettiar Park. Later in the evening transfer to the hotel for overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1042, 213, 'Kodaikanal - Munnar (160 Kms)', '\"After breakfast drive to Munnar. On arrival at Munnar, check into a hotel. For the rest of the day you are free for enjoying your own activities. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1043, 213, 'Munnar', '\"After breakfast, we will proceed for a full day sightseeing tour of Munnar. The tour will include a visit to Photo Point, Elephant Arrival Spot, Shooting Spot and Echo Point. Later, after lunch we will take you to the Tea Museum, Nyayamakad Waterfalls, Anamudi view, (RAJAMALA), \"\"SOUTH INDIA HIGHEST PEAK 8841 feet, 2695 meters\"\", Eravikulam National Park, Blossom Park, Pothamedu View, Plantations of Cardamom, Coffee & Pepper and Atukkad Waterfalls. In the evening transfer to the hotel for overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1044, 213, 'Munnar - Ooty (245 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Ooty. Ooty is in deep within the Nilgiri hills that are also known as The Blue Mountains. On arrival at Ooty, check into a hotel and for therest of the day you are free for leisure. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1045, 213, 'Ooty', '\"After breakfast proceed for sightseeing tour of Ooty. Visit the Botanical Garden, one of the best tourist attractions that allures visitors from all over the world. This garden was laid out in 1847 by the Marquis of Tweeddale and is spread over 22 hectares ascending the slopes on the hill at an elevation of 2,400 meters above sea level. Later visit Doddabetta (highest point of the place), Ooty Lake and Rose Garden.\r\nLocated in the heart of Ooty, Rose Park is not even a km from Charing Cross at Vijayanagaram. It has been laid on 10 acres of land in terraces with rose tunnels, pergolas and bowers with rose creepers. \r\nOvernight stay at the hotel.\"'),
(1046, 213, 'Ooty - Coimbatore (130 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Coimbatore. On arrival at Coimbatore we will transfer you to railway station for your onward destination.'),
(1047, 214, 'Delhi - Khajuraho', 'On your arrival in Delhi airport you will be welcomed by our representative & transfer to the domestic airport to board the flight for Khajuraho. On arrival at Khajuraho meet with the representative at the airport and transfer to the hotel. In the afternoon temple tour of Khajuraho Temples which includes Kandariya Mahadeo Chausath Yogini, Chitragupta temple, Vishwanath Temple and Matangeshwar Temple.'),
(1048, 214, 'Khajuraho - Bandhavgarh (250 km / 05 Hrs)', 'Morning after breakfast half day visit to Khajuraho & then drive to Bandhavgarh National Park. On arrival check in at the wildlife resorts. Overnight stay at resorts.'),
(1049, 214, 'Bandhavgarh National Park', 'Morning & afternoon Jeep Safari for the national park.. Bird watching and a walk to the fort. Overnight at the wildlife resort.'),
(1050, 214, 'Bandhavgarh National Park', 'Morning and evening Jungle exploration on Jeep. Overnight at the wildlife resort.'),
(1051, 214, 'Bandhavgarh - Kanha National Park (250 km / 04 Hrs)', 'Morning after breakfast at the resort drive to Kanha National Park. On arrival check in at the resort. Overnight stay at the Wildlife resort.'),
(1052, 214, 'Kanha National Park', 'Morning and evening Jungle exploration on Jeep. Overnight at the wildlife resort.'),
(1053, 214, 'Kanha National Park', 'Morning and evening jeep safari to the national park. Overnight at wildlife resort.'),
(1054, 214, 'Kanha National Park - Pench National Park (200 km / 03 Hrs)', 'Morning at leisure after breakfast at the resort, drive to Pench National Park. On arrival check-in at the resort. After lunch evening Jeep Safari for the national park. Overnight stay at the Wildlife Resort.'),
(1055, 214, 'Pench National Park', 'Morning and evening Jungle exploration on Jeep. Overnight at the wildlife resort.'),
(1056, 214, 'Pench National Park - Nagpur - Delhi (100 Kms / 02 Hrs)', 'Morning at leisure after breakfast transfer to Nagpur airport to board the flight for Delhi. On arrival in Delhi meet with the representative & transfer to hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1057, 214, 'Delhi Depart', 'Breakfast at the hotel and transfer to international airport to connect flight for onward destination.'),
(1086, 217, 'Arrival at Vadodara/Ahemdabad', '\"On arrival at Vadodara/Ahmedabad airport/ railway station, meet our representative who will be there for your welcome and transfer you to your already booked hotel. On arrival, check in at the hotel for an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1087, 217, 'Jambughoda Sightseeing', '\"Today post breakfast in the morning set out for a full day sightseeing tour of Jambughoda and witness its traditional culture and lifestyle. An overnight stay in the hotel in Jambugodha.\r\n\"'),
(1088, 217, 'Jambughoda - Uthelia', '\"We will leave post breakfast in the morning and leave by road for Uthelia via Champaner. It is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and home to more than hundred architectural edifices. Enjoy an overnight stay in Uthelia.\r\n\"'),
(1089, 217, 'Uthelia - Bhavnagar', 'In the morning post breakfast, we will leave for excursion to Harrappen Era, located at Lothal. Thereafter, we will proceed towards Bhavnagar, a historical town. In the evening, we will visit the Museum and the local markets. Stay overnight in the hotel in Bhavnagar.'),
(1090, 217, 'Bhavnagar', 'Today early in the morning, we will drive towards Palitana. En-route, we will visit Shetrunjaya Hill, nestled at 2000 feet. The town has around 863 temples with arches, carved pillars and ornamented idols, which dates back to the 11th century. Later return back to your hotel in Bhavnagar for an overnight stay.'),
(1091, 217, 'Bhavnagar - Gondal', 'Post breakfast in the morning, we will hit the road to Gondal. On arrival in Gondal by afternoon check in at the hotel. In the evening, we will visit the Naulakha Palace, which was built in the 17th century and known for its stone carvings and exquisite Jarokha balconies. Take pleasure of a relaxing overnight stay in the hotel in Gondal.'),
(1092, 217, 'Gondal - Wankaner', 'Today post breakfast, we will leave by road for Wanakner. On the way, we will explore the tourist attractions in Rajkot which include Watson Museum and Rashtriya Shala. On arrival in Wanakner by afternoon, we will check in at the pre-booked hotel and leave to explore the Palace Museum and the local village. Later, we will return back to the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1093, 217, 'Wankaner - Ahmedabad', '\"Post an early morning breakfast, we will drive to Ahmedabad today. On reaching Ahmedabad check in at the hotel. In the afternoon, we will set off for a half day sightseeing tour of Ahmedabad. Later, return back to the hotel in for an overnight stay in Ahmedabad.\r\n\"'),
(1094, 217, 'Departure - Ahmedabad', 'Today, you will transfer you to the airport to board the flight for onward destination.'),
(1095, 218, 'Ahmedabad - Dasada (90 kms)', 'After your arrival in Ahmedabad, we will drive to Dasada. Enjoy evening safari in the Little Rann of Kutch. This desert wildlife sanctuary is popular for being home to Asiatic wild ass, which is found nowhere else in India. Take pleasure of the mesmerizing sunset and bird watching at Bajana Lake. An overnight stay at Dasada.'),
(1096, 218, 'Dasada - Gir National Park', 'Today early in the morning explore the wildlife by enjoying a Jungle safari in the Little Rann. Thereafter, we will continue to Gir National Park. On arrival, check-in at a forest lodge and enjoy an overnight stay.'),
(1097, 218, 'Jungle Safari at Gir National Park', 'Enjoy wildlife safari in the Gir National Park in the morning as well as evening. Later return back to your lodge to enjoy dinner followed by an overnight stay.'),
(1098, 218, 'Wildlife Safari at Gir National Park & Nearby Sightseeing', 'The next two days are fixed for morning and evening safaris into the park. You can spot the big cats and other exotic animal species in the park while enjoying safaris. Also, you can visit Devaliya, a special area for the lions. Enjoy nature walk or bird watching in the Gir National Park. You can also opt for a visit to extremely popular the Somnath temple, Ahilya temple and Sun temple, etc. Enjoy dinner followed by an overnight stay at the lodge.'),
(1099, 218, 'Wildlife Safari at Gir National Park & Nearby Sightseeing', 'The next two days are fixed for morning and evening safaris into the park. You can spot the big cats and other exotic animal species in the park while enjoying safaris. Also, you can visit Devaliya, a special area for the lions. Enjoy nature walk or bird watching in the Gir National Park. You can also opt for a visit to extremely popular the Somnath temple, Ahilya temple and Sun temple, etc. Enjoy dinner followed by an overnight stay at the lodge.'),
(1100, 218, 'Sayla', 'After breakfast, we will proceed to Sayla. On arrival, check-in at the hotel and relax for some time. Later, we will drive to a place where you can spot huge flock of blackbuck antelope. An overnight stay in a heritage hotel in Sayla.'),
(1101, 218, 'Sayla - Ahmedabad', 'Today, we will enjoy an early morning visit to Nalsarovar Bird Sanctuary for bird watching. (NOTE: Boat ride is subjected to weather conditions). Later, we will drive back to the Ahmedabad airport to catch a flight for onward destination.'),
(1102, 220, 'Ahmedabad - Sayla', '\"On arriving in Ahmedabad, meet our representative who will transfer you to your already booked hotel. Check-in at the hotel. Thereafter, proceed to Sayla. In the afternoon, we will pay a visit to the Asiatic Wild association located in Latura. Enjoy an overnight stay at the hotel in Sayla.\r\n\"'),
(1103, 220, 'Sayla- Gir', '\"In the morning after breakfast, we will drive straight to Gir, the way to visit Junagadh to see the magnificent Uparkot Fort, 3rd century BC Ashoka rock edicts, the flamboyant royal mausoleum complexes, Buddhist cave-sites, the palace museum filled with Nawabi treasures, etc.\r\n \r\nReach hotel in the afternoon to enjoy lunch. Thereafter, we will proceed to experience safari in the Wildlife Sanctuary and the Gir National Park. Enjoy dinner and an overnight stay at the hotel in Gir.\r\n\"'),
(1104, 220, 'Gir National Park Jungle Safari & Nearby Sightseeing', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will drive to the deciduous Gir forests and get a chance to visit the two big cats and other wildlife in their natural habitat. En-route, we will visit the Somnath temple, which is considered as one of the 12 holy abodes of Shiva. Later in the afternoon, we will visit the Ahilya Temple, Sun Temple and other monuments. Enjoy an overnight stay and dinner at the lodge.'),
(1105, 220, 'Gir National Park Jungle Safari & Nearby Sightseeing', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will drive to the deciduous Gir forests and get a chance to visit the two big cats and other wildlife in their natural habitat. En-route, we will visit the Somnath temple, which is considered as one of the 12 holy abodes of Shiva. Later in the afternoon, we will visit the Ahilya Temple, Sun Temple and other monuments. Enjoy an overnight stay and dinner at the lodge.'),
(1106, 220, 'Ahmedabad', 'Today, we will drive back to Ahmedabad to board a return flight for your onward destination.'),
(1107, 221, 'Ahmedabad- Wankaner', 'On arrival at Ahmedabad Airport/ Railway Station, meet our tour executive who will take you to Wankaner, which is around four hour drive. On reaching Wankaner, check in at your already booked the hotel and relax for a while. Wankaner was an 11-Gun Salute State during the British era, and today it\'s renowned for its royal palaces. In the evening, you can visit some of this city\'s attractions such as Ranjit Vilas Palace (official residence of the maharaja of Wankaner), Ceramic Zone (an industrial zone that worked as a boon for the economy and employment in the state), Hazrat Shah Bava Dargah Sharif (a sacred shrine of high significance for Muslims as well as Hindus), etc. Enjoy an overnight stay in the hotel in Wankaner.'),
(1108, 221, 'Wakaner- Mandvi', 'After breakfast in the morning, get ready to visit Mandvi. It is about 4-hour long drive,. On reaching, check in at the hotel in Mandvi and relax for some time. Later, you can opt to behold the view of sunset in its magnificent beaches or visit some of the major attractions here such as Vijay Vilas Palace (a heritage site that reflects grandiose and brilliance of Rajput architecture), Navjivan Nature Cure Centre (a heaven meant for rejuvenation, relaxation and medical treatment) and Mazar-e-Noorani (a beautiful white mazar having a tranquil ambience). In the evening, return back to the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1109, 221, 'Mandvi- Bhuj', 'Today, we will visit one of the popular cities of Gujarat, Bhuj. On reaching, check in at a hotel and relax for a while. Therafter, we will proceed for the sightseeing tour of Bhuj. This city is famed for its culture, wildlife and architectural marvels. Swaminarayan temple is one of its prime attractions; the temple complex is dedicated to Narnarayan Deva and Harikrishna Maharaj. Other locations that can be visited are Kutch Museum, Prag Mahal, Aina Mahal, and Cenotaphs Complex. In the evening, return to the hotel and enjoy an overnight stay.'),
(1110, 221, 'Bhuj- Rann of Kutch- Bhuj', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will leave to explore the white desert. Rann of Kutch is a salt marsh located in the Thar Desert. Relax in your room and enjoy the view of the surroundings. In the evening, be ready for an enthralling desert safari that gives you a chance to behold the sight of animals like wild-ass, desert fox, blackbuck, wolf, jackal etc. Stay overnight in hotel.'),
(1111, 221, 'Bhuj- Ahmedabad', 'After breakfast in the morning, check out from the hotel and get timely transfer to Ahmedabad Airport/ Railway Station to board the flight or train to your onward destination.'),
(1112, 222, 'Ahmedabad', '\"On arrival at the Ahmedabad Airport, meet our representative who will transfer you to your already booked hotel. In the afternoon, leave from the hotel to explore the major attractions of Gujarat including Calico Museum, Akshardham Temple, Gandhi Ashram and Adalaj Stepwell in Gandhinagar. Later return back to the hotel for an overnight stay.\r\n\"');
INSERT INTO `tour_daywise` (`itinerydata_id`, `tour_id`, `itinerydata_title`, `itinerydata_description`) VALUES
(1113, 222, 'Ahmedabad – Rajkot (220 Kms/5 Hours Drive)', '\"In the morning post breakfast, we will take a road journey to Rajkot. On the way, we will stop at Virpur Temple for worship. On arrival in Rajkot by evening, check in the hotel for a relaxing overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1114, 222, 'Rajkot – Somnath (189 Kms/ 5 Hours Drive)', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will drive from Rajkot to Somnath. On arrival, check in at the hotel. In the evening, we will visit the Somnath temple. Enjoy an overnight stay in the hotel in Somnath.'),
(1115, 222, 'Somnath – Dwarka ( 230 kms / 5 Hours Drive)', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will hit the road to Dwarka. En-route, we will halt in Porbandar and explore the surrounding attractions. On arrival in Dwarka by evening, check into the hotel and take pleasure of an overnight stay.'),
(1116, 222, 'Dwarka', 'The day is booked for the sightseeing tour of Dwarka. We will leave in the morning after breakfast to explore Dwarka and its surrounding areas. Later return back to the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1117, 222, 'Dwarka – Jamnagar airport', 'Today, we will transfer you to the Jamnagar Airport to board the flight for onward destination.'),
(1118, 223, 'Arrival at Ahmedabad & Then Sightseeing Tour of Ahmedabad', 'On arrival in Ahmedabad, meet our representative, we will transfer you to your already booked hotel and assist you with the check in process. After check into the hotel, freshen up and get ready to leave for the sightseeing tour of Ahmedabad. We will visit the Gandhi Ashram next to the banks of the River Sabarmati. It is the place where Mahatma Gandhi set out on his Dandi March and has now been converted into a museum. You can witness the intricate carvings at the Hate Singh Jain Temple and marvel at the grand architecture of the Akshardham Temple here. Later return back to the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1119, 223, 'Ahmedabad- Jamnagar ( Approx 6 hours Drive)', 'Today post morning breakfast, check out from the hotel and leave for Jamnagar by road. En-route, visit the ancient and delightfully carved steep well. On reaching Jamnagar, check into the hotel. In the evening, you can visit the Bala Hanuman Temple. It is listed in the Guinness Book of World Records for the continuous chanting of \'Shri Ram, Jai Ram, Jai Jai Ram\' by its devotees since 1964. Enjoy an overnight stay in the hotel in Jamnagar.'),
(1120, 223, '\"Jamnagar to Dwarka (Approx 3 hours Drive)  \"', 'In the morning post breakfast, check out from the hotel and leave by road for Dwarka. On reaching Dwarka, check into the hotel. Post lunch, we will visit the Beyt Dwarka, believed to be the original abode of Lord Krishna and the famous \'Nageshwar Jyotirlinga Temple\', which is home to one of the 12 Swayambhu Jyotirlingas in the world. Later, we will visit the Gopi Talav, the lake where Gopis are said to have reunited with Lord Krishna. Thereafter, we will visit the Rukmini Devi Temple, dedicated to the wife of Lord Krishna. Later, return back to the hotel to take pleasure of an in Dwarka.'),
(1121, 223, 'Dwarka to Somnath ( Approx 5 hours Drive)', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will proceed to visit Somnath. En-route, we will visit the famous Kirti Mandir in Porbandar, the Haveli in which Mahatma Gandhi was born. Now it has been converted into a museum. Also, we will visit the Sudama Temple, which is built to honour the friendship between Krishna and Sudama. On reaching Somnath, go to the Somnath Temple and Bhalka Tirth Temple, where Lord Krishna is said to have been accidentally shot in the foot. Enjoy an overnight stay in Somnath.'),
(1122, 223, 'Somnath to Gir National Park ( Approx 1.5 hours Drive) and Enjoy Jungle safari in Gir Forest', 'Post breakfast in the morning, check out from the hotel and drive towards Gir. Sasan Gir is the famed place for Lion sightseeing and is well acknowledged as the only forest reserve in Asia for housing wild Lions,. Other animal species include the Sambhar, Spotted Deer, Nilgai and the Chausingha (the world\'s only four-horned antelope) can also be spotted in the forest. Even crocodiles can be seen in the reservoir and rivers flowing through the sanctuary. In the afternoon, we will go for a jungle safari in the National Park. Enjoy a night stay in Gir.'),
(1123, 223, 'Gir to Diu (Approx 2 hours Drive)', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will leave for Daman & Diu by road. On reaching Daman & Diu, check into the hotel. The rest of the day is free for leisure or to spend at the beaches of Daman & Diu. An overnight in the hotel.'),
(1124, 223, 'Diu to Ahmedabad (Approx 8 hours Drive) & Departure for Onward Journery', 'Today, we will leave for Ahmedabad by road post breakfast. Later, we will continue the journey towards the airport to catch the flight for onward destination.'),
(1125, 224, 'Diu', 'On arrival in Diu, meet our representative who will be there to receive you and transfer you to your already booked hotel in Die. Check in at your pre-booked resort. The rest of the day is free for admiring the surrounding natural beauty, interacting with locals, taste the local renditions, indulge in fun activities at the beach. Enjoy a leisure walk watching the sunset in the evening. Later, return back to the hotel for an overnight stay in Diu.'),
(1126, 224, 'Diu', 'On the second day of the tour, get involved in fun activities at the beach such as sun-bathing, book-reading, water sports activities, etc. In the afternoon post lunch, hit the road to Sasan Gir National Park, sole home of the Asiatic Lion. On arrival, board on a jeep safari during which you may spot animal species like Indian Leopards, Indian Palm Civets, Sloth bears, Jungle cats, Indian Cobras, Striped Hyenas, Golden Jackals, Ratels. Desert cats, and Indian Mongoose along with around 300 avifauna species. Later return back to Diu in the evening for an overnight stay in the hotel.'),
(1127, 224, 'Diu-Sasangir', 'Today, we will start our day a bit early in the morning to visit the beach. Enjoy the mesmerizing sunrise at the beach. Later after breakfast, we will leave to drive to Sasangir National Park, which is located at a distance of around 150 km. Founded in 1965, this national park is the only home of the Asiatic Lions. On arrival, check-in at the Jungle Camp/Hotel. In the evening, you can participate in Lion Sanctuary (Jeep safari Optional). Enjoy an overnight stay in Sasangir.'),
(1128, 224, 'Sasangir-Gondal', 'Today post-breakfast, we will leave to visit Gondal by road. En-route, we will halt at Junagarh, a former princely state. In Junagarh, we will visit the city\'s popular attractions including the very popular Ashoka\'s Rock Edicts-carrying Emperor Ashoka\'s edicts carving on a huge granite boulder, Junagarh Museum-housing manuscripts, pre-historic stones, silver ware, textiles, woodcarvings, stone carvings and more. In the evening, we will arrive at the historic city of Gondal and enjoy a relaxing stay in the hotel.'),
(1129, 224, 'Gondal-Wankaner', 'Post-breakfast in the morning, we will begin driving to Wankaner. En-route, we will visit the historic city of Rajkot, acknowledged for its important during the days of freedom fighting. In Rajkot, we will visit the Watson Museum-housing a vast collection of valuable of Rajkot as well as those of colonial times, Rashtriya Shala-another important historic monument and so on. Further, we will continue our drive to Wankaner. On arrival in Wankaner in the afternoon check in at the hotel. Later, enjoy a visit to the Palace Museum- erected in 1907 on a hill, this palace has now been turned into a museum that is home to collection of paintings, exotic furniture, portraits, royal silver ware etc. After exploring the Palace Museum, we will visit the local village. An overnight stay at the hotel in Wankaner.'),
(1130, 224, 'Wankaner-Dasada', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will begin driving to Dasada, which is home to the very popular Little Rann of Kutch. It is a small desert that is salt marsh. Little Rann of Kutch is recognized for being home to good number of Asiatic Wild Ass that are found here. In the afternoon, we will visit the sanctuary to explore the exotic wildlife and the amazing scenery. This is followed by a visis to the nearby local villages to see the daily activities and lifestyle of the region\'s local tribes. Stay overnight in Dasada.'),
(1131, 224, 'Dasada', 'The day is fixed for a jeep safari in the white desert, which is also a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Little Rann of Kutch is famed for being a rich biosphere. During the safari, along with the Indian Wild Ass, you may also spot other animal species such as blue bull, Indian antelope, Indian rat snake, desert cats, cobra, jackals, hares, Indian fox, desert fox, hyenas, and so on. Take pleasure of an overnight stay in Dasada.'),
(1132, 224, 'Ahmedabad-Departure', 'In the morning after breakfast, get transferred to the Ahmedabad airport to board the flight for your onward journey.'),
(1133, 225, 'Rajkot - Dwaraka', '\"On arrival at the Rajkot airport in the morning, meet our representative who will take you to Dwaraka. In the evening, you will arrive in Dwaraka and check in at your already booked hotel. Later, we will leave to visit the temple and take part in the evening Aarti. An overnight stay in the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1134, 225, 'Dwaraka - Porbandar', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will visit the Dwarkadhish temple. After visiting the temple, we will drive to Porbandar. Porbandar is a picturesque old sea port situated on the western coast of Gujarat. It was the birth place of Mahatma Gandhi. Enjoy an overnight stay in the hotel in Porbander.'),
(1135, 225, 'Porbandar - Veraval', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will visit the Kirti Mandir or the Gandhi home in Porbandar. In this the Mahatma Gandhi, the father of the nation was born in 1869. There are 17 rooms and three storeys in this house. After visiting the Porbandar, we will drive to Veraval and have an overnight stay in the hotel.'),
(1136, 225, 'Veraval - Somnath', 'In the morning, we will drive further to visit the legendary shore temple of Somnath. This temple is one of the twelve most sacred shrines dedicated to the Lord Shiva and a Jyotirlinga. Later, return back to the hotel in Somnath for an overnight stay.'),
(1137, 225, 'Somnath - Rajkot', 'Today, we will drive to the Rajkot airport to board the flight for the onwards journey.'),
(1138, 226, 'Arrival in Bhuj - Dhordo', 'On arrival at Bhuj airport/railway station, meet our representative who will transfer you to the Dhordo well known as the tent city for the Utsav. Check-in at your allotted tent in Dhordo. Enjoy delicious lunch and the rest of the day is free at leisure. One can also go for shopping during leisure time at the handicraft bazaar. The different handicrafts from the star attraction of Kutch are beautifully designed and they mainly include terracotta, patchwork and embroidered items. In the evening, enjoy tea and snacks at the dining hall. Post dinner, you can enjoy cultural programs that are held in the camp area. Have dinner and enjoy a comfortable overnight stay at the camp city, Dhordo.'),
(1139, 226, 'In the Camp', 'Start your day with meditation and let your soul intermingle with nature. Thereafter, have some healthy breakfast. Enjoy the rest of the day, exploring the colours of the beautiful place. Step out to have a look at the ethnic stuff designed by the local artisans. You can also take a short trip to the Indo - Pak Border. In the evening, grab the opportunity to dance with the local folk dancers. Later return back to the hotel to enjoy a comfortable night stay in Dhordo.'),
(1140, 226, 'Depart for Bhuj', 'After breakfast in the morning, bid farewell to this unique and beautiful Rann Utsav tour. Thereafter, we will transfer you to the Railway station / Airport in Bhuj for onward journey.'),
(1141, 227, 'Mumbai', 'On arrival at the Mumbai airport, our representative will be there to meet you and transfer you to your already booked hotels. Check-in at the hotel. Rest of the day is free at leisure. In the evening, you may take a leisurely walk to the nearby market of Mumbai. Enjoy an overnight stay in the hotel in Mumbai.'),
(1142, 227, 'Mumbai', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will proceed to enjoy a half day tour to Elephanta caves. These caves are located at a distance of 9 Kms from the Gateway of India. To reach Elephanta caves, one need to board a ferry from the Gateway of India. The Elephanta caves comprise of seven caves. Out of all the caves, the cave of Mahesh Murit is of great importance. This rock-cut cave temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva where he is shown as a creator, protector and destroyer. After the excursion to Elephant caves return back to Mumbai for a sightseeing tour. Some of the major tourist attractions we will be visiting include Hanging Gardens, Marine Drive, Dhobi Ghat, Juhu Beach, Gateway of India and the Prince of Wales Museum. In the late evening, return back to the hotel for dinner followed by an overnight stay.'),
(1143, 227, 'Mumbai - Bhuj', 'Today morning, our representative will transfer you to the Mumbai airport to take a flight to Bhuj. On reaching Bhuj, check-into the hotels. Spend the afternoon resting and relaxing in your hotel room. Later, you can visit to Kutch Museum, the oldest museum of Gujarat and Palace of Rao Pragmalji. Therefater, return back to the hotel for dinner and an overnight stay.'),
(1144, 227, 'Bhuj', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will proceed to explore the Bhuj city famous for its Hindu temples, palaces and wooden pavilions. The major tourist attractions of Bhuj that we will cover in our tour include Prag Mahal, Kakkad Bhit Yaksha, Swaminarayan temple, Aina Mahal, Kachchh Museum and the Bhartiya Sanskruti Darshan. Also, we will enjoy a sightseeing tour to Bunny Villages to watch traditional desert villagers and their way of living. In the evening, return back to the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1145, 227, 'Bhuj', 'Today early in the morning, we will drive to Mandvi to visit summer palace of Bhuj Maharaj. Enjoy the entire day excursion to Mandvi beach, one of the finest beaches on the coastline of Gujarat. The major tourist attractions of Mandvi village include the Swaminarayan temple, Vijay Vilas Palace, Topansar Lake and Bandini Bazaar. You can explore these places and return back to the hotel for a relaxing night stay.'),
(1146, 227, 'Bhuj - Gondal', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will drive straight to Gondal. En-route, we will be visiting Dhamadka. thereafter, resume the drive to Gondal. The major tourist attractions of Gondal include Shri Swaminarayan Mandir, Orchard Palace, Riverside Palace, Naulakha Palace, Huzoor Palace and the Bhuvaneshwari temple. In the evening, we will visit the Veri Lake, an ideal place for watching birds like flamingo, spoonbill, crane and white ibis from the close quarters. Take pleasure of an overnight stay in the hotel in Gondal.'),
(1147, 227, 'Gondal - Sasangir', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will proceed to Sasangir. En-route, we will stop at Junagadh to visit the major tourist hotspots like Bhavnath temple, Damodar Kund, Akshar Mandir and the Darta Hill. Thereafter, we will continue driving to Sasangir. On reaching Sasangir, check-in at the wildlife resort. After resting for a while, we will proceed to enjoy an elephant safari to explore the exotic wildlife at Gir National Park. In the evening, return back to the hotel for enjoying dinner followed by an overnight stay.'),
(1148, 227, 'Sasangir', 'Today in the morning, we will leave early in the morning to explore the Gir National Park. The Gir National Park was built to conserve the Asiatic lion-classified as one of the World\'s most threatened species. The day is fixed for exploring the Gir National Park. Later, we will visit the Kamleshwar Dam situated in the centre of Sasan-Gir National Park. Enjoy an overnight stay in the wildlife resort.'),
(1149, 227, 'Sasangir - Diu', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will drive down to Diu. En-route, we will stop to visit Somnath - the temple city. Somnath is also the home to one of the 12 Jyotirlings of India. After visiting Somnath, we will continue our drive towards Diu. On arrival, check-in at the hotels. Rest and relax for a while. Thereafter, we will process for the sightseeing tour of Diu. The major tourist attractions of Diu include Bunder Chowk, St. Paul\'s Church. An overnight stay in the hotel.'),
(1150, 227, 'Diu', 'Today post breakfast, we will visit the other major tourist attractions of Diu including Gangeshwar Temple, Diu Museum, Ghoghla Beach, Gomtimata Beach, Diu Fort, Fortress of Panikota, Nagoa Beach and Jallandhar Beach. Later in the evening, return back to the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1151, 227, 'Diu – Bhavnagar', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will leave Diu to reach Bhavnagar. On arrival at Bhavnagar, check-in at your pre-booked hotel. After relaxing for a while, we will visit the major tourist hotspots like the Nilambagh, the Gangajalia temple and the Gandhi Smriti Memorial. Also, we will visit the Takhteshwar temple and the Lock Gate. In the evening, enjoy an excursion to Gaurishankar Lake, the beautiful picnic spot. Thereafter, return to the hotel to enjoy wholesome dinner followed by an overnight stay.'),
(1152, 227, 'Bhavnagar - Uteliya', 'In the morning, we will drive straight to Uteliya. En-route, we will visit Palitana- the most sacred sites of Jainism. This place is scattered with a lot of temples in the Shatrunjaya hill. Further, we will proceed to climb the 600-meter Shatrunjaya hill on foot to enjoy the temple excursion. Afterward, we will resume the drive to Uteliya. On reaching Uteliya, check-in at the hotel. After taking some rest, we will leave to visit the famous Uteliya Palace featuring five domes, pillared galleries, balconies and porticoes. Later, return back to the hotel for dinner and an overnight stay.'),
(1153, 227, 'Uteliya - Zainabad - Dasada', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will proceed for Dasada. En-route, we will visit Zainabad. Located on the periphery of the Little Rann of Kutch, Zainabad is a beautiful place. Explore the Wild Ass Sanctuary in Zainabad and enjoy watching Asiatic Lions in their real habitat at close quarters. Later, we will drive straight to Dasada. On reaching Dasada, check-in at the hotel. While staying at Dasada, enjoy a cross-desert safari across the Little Rann of Kutch in open vehicles. In winter, it is also home to migratory birds such as flamingos, MacQueen\'s Bustard etc. An overnight stay in the hotel.'),
(1154, 227, 'Dasada - Vadodara', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will proceed to Vadodara by surface. On reaching Vadodara, check-in at the hotel. After straitening your backs for a while, embark on a sightseeing tour of Vadodara. The major tourist attractions of Vadodara include Pratap Vilas Palace, Nazarbaug Palace, Laxmi Vilas Palace and the Makarpura Palace. Later in the day, we will pay a visit to the Aurobindo Ashram and Kanderao Museum. Enjoy an overnight stay in the hotel in Vadodara.'),
(1155, 227, 'Vadodara', 'Today post breakfast, we will proceed to explore the other major tourist attractions of Vadodara. The major attractions to be visit include Hazira Maqbara, EME temple, Mandvi City, Kala Goda, Nyay Mandir. In the afternoon, we will be visiting some of the famous museums of Vadodara covering Maharaj Fateh Singh Museum, Vadodara Museum and the Picture Gallery. An overnight stay in the hotel.'),
(1156, 227, 'Vadodara - Ahmedabad', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will leave for Ahmedabad. On arrival in Ahmedabad, check in at the hotel. Rest and relax for the afternoon. After lunch, we will go for the sightseeing tour of Ahmedabad to visit the Calico Museum of Textile. This is one of India\'s finest specialized museums. Later in the evening, enjoy an excursion to Kankaria Lake. Enjoy an overnight stay in the hotel in Ahmedabad.'),
(1157, 227, 'Ahmedabad', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will visit the magnificent Mosque of Siddi Saiyad for its exquisite stone carvings. Later in the day, we will visit the major tourist attractions of Ahmedabad covering the white-marbled Hathee Singh\'s temple, the beautiful Jama Masjid, Dada Hari Baoli, Sabarmati Ashram and Shaking Minarets. In the evening return back to the hotel to enjoy an overnight.'),
(1158, 227, 'Ahmedabad - Mumbai', 'Today, we will leave early in the morning after breakfast for Ahmedabad airport to board the flight to Mumbai. On reaching Mumbai airport, board a flight for onward destination.'),
(1159, 228, 'Ahmedabad - Junagadh - Gir National Park', '\"On arrival at Ahmedabad airport/railway station, meet our representative who will be there for your welcome. Thereafter, you have two options for getting to Gir National Park i.e either you can directly drive to Gir from Ahmedabad which takes around six hours to reach or you arrive at Junagadh from Ahmedabad and then you move to the Gir Birding Lodge. In the morning, we will go for nature walks along with a guide, followed by Safari for wildlife sights, bird watching and the famous lion tracking. Later return back to the lodge in the evening and enjoy a pleasurable overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1160, 228, 'Jungle Safari at Gir National Park', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will proceed for the Safari. Encourage yourself within the jungles of the park and track down Lions, leopards and look out for other wild animals and birds. You spend an extensive time in Safari. Later in the evening return back to the lodge for a warm dinner and to retire for the day.'),
(1161, 228, 'Gir National Park - Junagadh - Ahmedabad', 'Today wake up early in the morning and enjoy Safari for viewing the wild animals that are mainly spotted during this time. Thereafter proceed to visit the crocodile farm and Devaliya after lunch. If you are directly going to Ahmedabad, then you start your journey back there. If you are taking the train, then head out for Junagadh a bit later.'),
(1162, 229, 'Ahmedabad (Arrival)', '\"On arrival in Ahmedabad, get greeted by our tour representative who will transfer you to your pre-booked hotel. Check in at the hotel for a relaxing overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1163, 229, 'Ahmedabad', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will leave to visit the Calico Museum- primary textile museum of India, showcasing amazing artworks; Swaminarayan Temple- oldest temple of Swaminarayan. Thereafter, we will proceed to Akshardham Temple (Gandhinagar), a temple dedicated to Swaminarayan, with brilliant architecture spread over and area of 23 acres; and Adalaj Stepwell- a \'water building\' (a five story well) dating back to the 15th century. Return back to the hotel by late evening and enjoy an overnight stay.'),
(1164, 229, 'Ahmedabad - Dasada', 'After breakfast in the morning, we will leave for Dasada. En-route, we will stop in Modhera- mainly famous for ancient Sun Temple, dedicated to Hindu\'s Sun God; and Patan- dotted with temples, mosques and other structures dating back to the era bygone. On arrival in Dasada, check in at your already booked hotel. In the afternoon, we will depart in jeep for little Rann of Kutch. Rann of Kutch is a salt marsh located in the Thar Desert. This is the largest salt desert of the world. By late evening, return back to the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1165, 229, 'Dasada - Bhuj', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will drive to Bhuj. En-route, we will stop at the collector office to get the permit license for visiting Banny Village (for foreigners). After visiting Bhuj\'s attractions like Pragmahal Palace, Aina Mahal, Bhujio Hill and Hamirsar Lake, check in at the hotel and have a pleasurable overnight stay.'),
(1166, 229, 'Bhuj', 'After refreshing breakfast, you reach the villages of Banny. These villages showcases and have adapted the Gujarati culture as a significant part of themselves. By evening, you return to the hotel and stay overnight.'),
(1167, 229, 'Bhuj - Rajkot', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will drive to Rajkot. En-route, we will halt in Morbi and Wankaner- both influenced and ornamented with European architecture and culture. By afternoon, you reach Rajkot and check in to your hotel. In a short while, we will proceed for the sightseeing tour that includes Rotary Doll Museum. Thereafter, return back to the hotel and stay overnight.'),
(1168, 229, 'Rajkot - Sasangir', 'In the morning after breakfast, check out and leave for Sasangir. On the way, we will stop at Shri Jalaram Bappa temple for Darshan and Junagarh to visit- Uparkot Fort (built by Chandra Gupt Maurya, dating back to 319 BC) and Mahaprabhuji\'s Baithak. Thereafter, continue our journey to Sasangir. We will reach our destination by late evening. Check in at the hotel in Sasangir and enjoy an overnight stay.'),
(1169, 229, 'Sasangir - Somnath - Diu', 'After breakfast, we will leave for wildlife Safari in Sasangir National Park- covers an area of 1412 km sq and is the only home of Asiatic Lions. In the afternoon, head towards Diu and stopover in Somnath. Somnath has a temple that is the first out of the ten Shiva\'s Joyotirlings. Diu is amongst the least populated districts of India and as it is a historical part of Saurashtra region, this makes it a significant place to visit. Later, reach Diu, check in at the hotel and have an overnight stay.'),
(1170, 229, 'Diu', 'In the morning after breakfast, you are free to explore Diu and its famous beaches like Nagoa Beach. By late evening, return back to the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1171, 229, 'Diu - Bhavnagar', 'Today early in the morning you can enjoy alluring view of the sunrise in the beach. Thereafter, return to the hotel for breakfast and then leave for Bhavnagar. On reaching Bhavnagar, check in to hotel room for an overnight stay.'),
(1172, 229, 'Bhavnagar - Palitana - Baroda (Vadodara)', 'After early morning breakfast, we will drive to Baroda. En-route, we will stopover at Palitana. In Palitana, we will visit Shatrunjaya Temple for Darshan. Further, we will head towards Baroda. Check in at the hotel in Baroda on reaching and stay overnight.'),
(1173, 229, 'Baroda (Vadodara)', 'In the morning after breakfast, get ready to proceed for the city tour that may include Sayaji Bag, Nazarbaug Palace, Kirti Stambh and/ or Baroda Museum. Later, we will drive to Champaner- a historical village embellished with ancient forts, minars, mosques and other things. Following Champner is the visit to Chotta Udaipur. By late evening, return to your hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1174, 229, 'Baroda – Mumbai- Departure', 'Today after breakfast, we will leave for Baroda airport and further to Mumbai International Airport to catch international flight for onward destination.'),
(1175, 231, 'Arrive Mumbai', 'On arrival at Mumbai international airport you will be welcome by our representative and escorted to your pre-booked hotel in Delhi. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1176, 231, 'Mumbai - Rajkot (By flight) - Gir National Park (164 km)', '\"Morning transfer to the airport to board the flight for Rajkot, on arrival at Rajkot airport meet with our representative and drive to Gir National Park. On arrival check in at the wildlife resort. After lunch jungle safari to the national park for wildlife viewing. Overnight stay at resort.\r\nGir National Park & Wildlife Sanctuary is a 1412 sq km hilly tract of dry deciduous forests, acacia scrub, evergreen and semi-evergreen flora and grasslands, fed by rivers and streams. Among the many water-bodies in the reserve is the Kamleshwar Dam, known for its large crocodile population.\r\nOriginally protected by the Nawab of Junagadh, after British viceroys brought to his attention the plight of the lion in Asia, the sanctuary is the jewel of Gujarat\'s ecological resources.\"'),
(1177, 231, 'Gir National Park', '\"Morning & afternoon Jungle safari to the national park for wildlife viewing. Overnight stay at resort.\r\nAccording to official census figures, Gir has about 300 lions and 300 leopards, making it one of the major big-cat concentrations in India. Sambar and spotted deer (chital), blue bull (nilgai), chousingha (the world\'s only four-horned antelope), chinkara (Indian gazelle) and wild boar thrive in Gir. Jackal, striped hyena, jungle cat, rusty-spotted cat, langur, porcupine, black-naped Indian hare are among the other mammals of Gir.\r\nGir has a large population of marsh crocodile or mugger, which is among the 40 species of reptiles and amphibians recorded in the sanctuary. The park checklist has 250 birds and about 50 other species (including the endangered lesser florican and the saras crane) are recorded in the grasslands along the periphery of the sanctuary.\"'),
(1178, 231, 'Gir National Park', '\"Morning & afternoon Jungle safari to the national park for wildlife viewing. Overnight stay at resort.\r\n\"'),
(1179, 231, 'Gir - Rajkot (164 km) - Mumbai - Nagpur', 'Early morning checkout from the resort & drive to Rajkot. On arrival transfer to the airport to board the flight for Nagpur via Mumbai. On arrival at Mumbai Nagpur airport meet with our representative and transfer to the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1180, 231, 'Nagpur – Kanha National Park (290 km)', '\"Today after breakfast at the hotel, we will be heading for Kanha National Park. The journey by road will take approx 6 hrs to reach Kiplings country, an outstanding wildlife reserve of India. Situated within two main valleys, Halon in the east and Banjar in the west, and the grassy \'maidans\', dotted with clumps of forest harbor large numbers of herbivores. The hills offer support sizeable plateaus (locally called \'Dadars\') and the characterized by extensive grasslands and scant trees. \r\nOn arrival at the national park we will check in at the wildlife resort. After fresh-n-up & lunch we will ready to enter the Kanha national park for first time accompanying with the naturalist. overnight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1181, 231, 'Kanha National Park', '\"We will continue with our scheduled jungle safari to the national park for wildlife viewing both morning & evening. Overnight stay at resort.\r\nKanha Tiger Reserve created in 1974 under Project Tiger. The park is the only habitat of the rare hard ground barasingha (Cervus Duvauceli Branderi). In the 1930s, the Kanha area was divided into two sanctuaries: Hallon and Banjar, of 250 sq km and 300 sq km each. Though one of these was subsequently disbanded, the area remained a protected one until 1947. Depletion of the tiger population in the years that followed led to the area being made an absolute sanctuary in 1952. By a special statute in 1955, Kanha National Park came into being. Since then, a series of stringent conservation programmes for the protection of the park\'s flora and fauna has given Kanha its deserved reputation for being one of the finest and best administered National Parks in Asia, an irresistible attraction for all wildlife lovers and a true haven for its animal and avian population.\r\nKanha national park is habitat for following wildlife mammals like tiger, bison, gaur, sambar, chital, barasingha, barking deer, black deer, black buck, chousingha, nilgai, mouse deer, sloth bear, jackal fox, porcupine, hyena, jungle cat, python, pea fowl, hare, monkey, mongoose, tiger, and leopard.\r\n\"'),
(1182, 231, 'Kanha National Park – Bandhavgarh National Park', 'Morning jungle safari to the national park, later after breakfast drive to Bandhavgarh National park. On arrival check in at the wildlife resort. Overnight stay at resort. Bandhavgarh Tiger Reserve is mainly known for its Royal Bangal Tigers. It has a typical central Indian fauna & home of more than 22 species of mammals. Common langur and rhesus macaque represent the primate group. Among the carnivore species jackal, Bengal fox, sloth bear, rattle, grey (small Indian) and ruddy mongoose, striped hyena, wolf, wild dog, jungle cat, leopard and tiger are prominent. Ungulates (animals which walk on tips of their toes) include chital, sambar, barking deer, chinkara, chousingha, nilgai and wild pig. Porcupine, lesser bandicoot and three-striped palm squirrel are among the rodents. Small Indian civet and toddy cat are also found here though seen rarely being nocturnal. Another nocturnal animal, the rufous-tailed hare is also seen usually during dusk. Some of its mammals have been listed as threatened animals by IUCN in their red list like the wild dog, Bengal fox, sloth bear, leopard and tiger.'),
(1183, 231, 'Bandhavgarh National Park', '\"Today we will enter twice to the national park for our morning & afternoon scheduled Jungle safari for its wildlife. Overnight stay at wildlife resort.\r\nSpread at vindhya hills in Madhya Pradesh, Bandhavgarh National Park consists of a core area of 105 sq km and a buffer area of approximately 400 sq km of topography varies between steep ridges, undulating, forest and open meadows. Bandhavgarh National Park is known for the Royal Bengal Tigers. The density of the Tiger population at Bandhavgarh is the highest known in India. It was the former hunting preserve of the Maharaja of Rewa and at present is a famous natural hub for White Tigers. \r\nBandhavgarh was declared a national park in 1968. Since then many steps have been taken to retain Bandhavgarh National Park as an un-spoilt national habitat for a variety of wildlife peculiar to the area. These includes gaur (Indian bison), sloth bear, leopard, porcupine, wild boar, sambar and spotted deer, among others and of course, the tiger.\"'),
(1184, 231, 'Bandhavgarh National Park', 'We will still enjoy hunting wildlife with big camera\'s on the consequent day. For the same we will enter twice here on third day for its morning & afternoon season. Overnight stay at resort.'),
(1185, 231, 'Bandhavgarh - Katani (100 km) - Agra (By train)', 'Today we will have an excursion to Bandhavgarh fort. This fort is in ruins now but the strong high walls of the fort tell a saga of valour and splendour. The fort blends with the wilds of the park and has become a part of the park. No one knows when the fort was constructed but scripts as old as Shiva Purina have mention the fort which is believed to be almost 2000 years old. The park in itself is historically very important. The signs of early habitation can be seen in the caves excavated from the cliffs to the north of the fort. Brahmi inscriptions here date back to the 1st century BC. Later after lunch drive to Katani on arrival transfer to railway station to board the train for Agra. Overnight stay on board.'),
(1186, 231, 'Arrive Agra', '\"On arrival at Agra railway station meet with our representative and transfer to the hotel. After fresh-n-up visit the famous Taj Mahal built by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan as a memorial to his queen Mumtaz Mahal, made out of white marble took 22 years to complete (1630-1652 AD).\r\nLater visit Agra fort. Built principally as a military establishment by Akbar in 1565, the red sandstone Agra fort was partially converted into a palace during Shah Jahan\'s time. Though the principal structure was built by Akbar. Overnight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1187, 231, 'Agra - Delhi (204 km)', '\"Morning after breakfast drive to Delhi. On arrival check in at the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1188, 231, 'Delhi', 'Morning after breakfast city sightseeing tour of Delhi visiting Raj Ghat and Shanti Vana - the cremation sites of Mahatma Gandhi and Jawaharlal Nehru, Jama Masjid and drive past Red Fort and Chandni Chowk, Qutub Minar built by Qutub-ud-Din Aibek in 1199, Humayun\'s Tomb, India Gate (War Memorial Arch ). Also drive past President\'s House, Parliament House, and Government Secretariat Buildings & Connaught Place shopping centre. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1189, 231, 'Delhi Depart', 'Breakfast at the hotel and transfer to the international airport to board the flight for onward destination.'),
(1190, 232, 'Ahmedabad – Sasan-Gir', '\"We will drive to Sasan Gir in the morning. On arrival, check into at the wildlife resort. Enjoy lunch and dinner at the hotel.\r\nSasan Gir is one of the popular wildlife national parks that offer home to many Asiatic Lions. It also offer habitat to a variety of smaller animals and birds. Other predators recorded in the park include the Panther and the Hyena, The Indian Deer, Sambar, Chital (spotted deer), Nilgai (blue bull), Chinkara, the Chowsingha (four horned antelope), the bear and the long tailed Langur.\"'),
(1191, 232, 'Sasan-Gir', '\"We will explore the Gir National Park for Wildlife watching in the morning. We will also enter the national park again in the afternoon for its second view. The wildlife safaris are organized in the sanctuary thrice in a day, two scheduled rides in the morning season while the last one will be organized late in the afternoon.\r\nThe forest of Gir national park is dry, deciduous and is situated in the semi-arid western part of India. The topography made up of succession of rugged ridges, isolated hills, deep ravines, plateaus, valleys and interspersed with large patches of grasslands.\r\nApart from the mammals, the park has a large population of marsh crocodile or mugger that is among the 40 species of reptiles and amphibians recorded in the sanctuary. Gir National Park is also a paradise for bird watchers with a check-list of more than 250 birds.\r\nAn overnight stay in Sasan Gir.\"'),
(1192, 232, 'Sasan-Gir - Ahmedabad', 'We will again visit the Gir National park for the scheduled jungle safari early in the morning. Later, we will return back to the resort for fresh-n-up. After breakfast, we will leave for Ahmedabad. En-route, we will stop at Junagadh to visit the Uperkot fort, one of the ancient forts built by Chandra Gupta. The fort has been rebuilt and extended many times. Further, we will continue our drive to Ahmedabad. On arrival at Ahmedabad, we will drop you at your desired location.'),
(1193, 233, 'Arrival - Delhi', 'On arrival at the Delhi airport, meet our representative \"Welcome\" than transfer to the hotel, overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1194, 233, 'Delhi - Ahmedabad - Dasada', 'Transfer to domestic airport, time to catch the flight for Ahmedabad, Arrive Ahmedabad by flight. then drive in the Little Rann of Kutch, en-route see Egyptian and griffon vultures could be seen and wetlands that are good for resident birds. falcon, shikra, blue throat, rosy starling, black ibis, white pelican, grey and pond heron, pied, common and white-throated kingfisher, and other birds come into the property. After lunch, depart for a drive in the Little Rann of Kutch, a sanctuary for the Indian wild ass. An ancient seabed turned by geological forces into saline desert plains, the Rann has grassy patches that offer good bird-watching. Crested and Sykes larks, Oriental skylark, bimaculated lark, greater short-toed lark, singing and Indian bushlarks, ashy-crowned and black-crowned sparrow-larks, are likely sightings and greater hoopoe lark is possible. Desert and variable wheatears, southern grey, long-tailed, rufous-tailed and bay-back shrike, common woodshrike are also likely sightings and the desert warbler is among the many winter visiting warblers. We will also look for chestnut-bellied and spotted sandgrouse, Indian courser (cream-coloured visits occasionally), quails, yellow-legged and barred buttonquails, grey francolin, wryneck, brown-rock chat, pied bushchat, rufous-tailed scrub robin, blue-headed rock thrush, black redstart and buntings in the scrubby areas. At sunset, it is possible to watch marsh, Montagu and pallid harriers, aquila eagles, falcons and buzzards heading for their roosting sites. Among the mammals of the Rann other than the wild ass, there are chances of seeing nilgai, chinkara gazelle, white-footed desert and Indian foxes, the wolf, overnight stay.'),
(1195, 233, 'Dasada', '\"Morning after breakfast, drive to the bets, elevated patches in the Rann covered with scrub and grass. In winter, this is a likely area for Macqueen\'s bustard. Long-legged, common and white-eyed buzzard, booted eagle, Bonelli\'s eagle. short-toed snake eagle, are often seen during the drive.\r\nEvening visit to Nawa Talao, a lake where demoiselle and common cranes gather in large flocks during the winter months. Greater and lesser flamingo are seen in large numbers as are great white pelican with spot billed and dalmatian recorded. Painted, openbill, wooly-necked, white, black and black-necked stork could be seen as also black, glossy and black-headed ibis. Northern pintail, common teal, spot-billed duck, mallard, gadwall, wigeon, garganey, shoveler, cotton pygmy goose, pochards, tufted duck, lesser whistling duck, brahminy and comb duck are among the many visitors to the lake. Waders include pratincoles, lapwings, sandpipers, ruff and other birds in good numbers, overnight stay.\"'),
(1196, 233, 'Dasada - Jamnagar', 'Morning after breakfast walk in Dasada village. This can yield a reasonably good bird list including yellow-legged green pigeon, paradise flycatcher, fantails, red-breasted flycatcher, white-eye, prinias and warblers. After breakfast, depart for Jamnagar, six hours away. This is an interesting route passing agricultural fields and lakes. Birds of open-country like roller and black-shouldered kite could be seen. Arrive at Hotel President in time for lunch. On this day, we will also try to get permits to enter the Marine National Park the next day. Evening visit to Khijadiya Bird Sanctuary, where there are fairly good chances of seeing Indian skimmer. This sanctuary is a breeding area for many species of birds that do not nest elsewhere in peninsular India. Great-crested grebe, black-necked stork, Caspian tern and many other birds can be seen besides most of the species recorded in the Little Rann area. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1197, 233, 'Jamnagar', 'Morning after breakfast Visit coastal areas along the Gulf of Kutch, one of the finest birding stretches along the Indian coastline. see crab-plover, Kentish plover, oystercatcher, ruddy turnstone, broad-billed sandpiper, sanderling, dunlin, curlew sandpiper, black-headed gull, Pallas\'s gull, Temminck\'s stint, lesser-crested tern, gull-billed tern, common tern, little tern, black-bellied tern, whiskered tern, whiskered tern, darters, western reef egret and other birds could be seen on this route. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1198, 233, 'Jamnagar - Gir National Park', 'Morning after breakfast, Depart for Porbandar, This coastal city is good for watching and photographing birds at close range. Besides large flamingo and crane flocks, this area also receives yellow-legged gull, heuglin\'s gull, sandwich tern, black-bellied tern, etc. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1199, 233, '\"Gir Bird Watching Tours in Gujarat Morning afternoon jungle safari to the national park. \"', '\"Wildlife in Gir:\r\nHere population of panther (leopard), sambar, chital (spotted deer), nilgai (blue bull antelope) and wild boar. Gir is also one of the major habitats of chousingha (the world\'s only four-horned antelope) and chinkara (Indian gazelle) that are hard to spot in the teak forests along the game drive trails. Among the many birds of Gir, changeable hawk eagle, crested serpent eagle, Bonelli\'s eagle, Peregrine falcon, laggar falcon, shikra, painted sandgrouse, quails, black-hooded and golden oriole, marshall\'s and common iora, Asian paradise flycatcher, tickell\'s blue, red-throated, verditer and Asian brown flycatchers, yellow-crowned, brown-capped pygmy, black-rumped flameback woodpeckers, green and blue-cheeked bee-eaters, coppersmith barbet, common, lesser pied and white-throated kingfisher, blossom-headed parakeet, hoopoe, black, ashy and white-bellied drongos, rufous treepie, large cuckoo shrike, small minivet, red-vented and white-eared bulbul, tawny-bellied, yellow-eyed, jungle and large grey babblers, grey-breasted, ashy, rufous-fronted, plain, jungle and graceful prinias, zitting cisticola, clamorous reed-warbler, booted warbler, greenish warbler, lesser and Hume\'s warbler, orphean warbler and blyth\'s reed warbler, are among the many birds that could be seen here. overnight stay at resort.\"'),
(1200, 233, 'Gir - Bhavnagar', 'Morning after breakfast, drive to Bhavnagar, on arrival check in at the hotel, then visit Bird in Victoria Park (good scrubland birdlife), Gaurishankar Lake and near the ports where Western reef egret nest in good numbers.'),
(1201, 233, 'Bhavnagar - Velavadar - Ahmedabad', 'Early morning with packed breakfast, depart for Velavadar National Park, Known for its large blackbuck antelope population, Velavadar is also one of the few places where the wolf is proliferating in India though they are rarely seen in the daylight. Jackal, jungle cat and hare are more easily seen and Indian fox on the periphery. Sirkeer malkoha, painted francolin, chestnut-bellied and spotted sandgrouse, rufous-tailed, crested and Sykes larks, red-rumped swallows, desert and variable wheatears and other birds are seen and many raptors visit specially short-toed snake eagle, imperial, steppe, tawny, greater and lesser spotted eagles, Laggar falcon, hobby, common kestrel, red-necked falcon, peregrine falcon, white-eyed and long-legged buzzard, black-shouldered kite, Shikra, Eurasian sparrow-hawk and occasionally northern goshawk. Rarities include the Stoilczka\'s bushchat. overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1202, 233, 'Ahmedabad - Delhi - Departure', 'Morning after breakfast, transfer to airport time to catch the flight for Delhi, on arrival Delhi meet our representative and transfer to International airport time to catch the flight for onward destination.'),
(1203, 234, 'DELHI - NAINITAL (320 KMS / 08 HRS. DRIVE)Nainital Tourist Attraction', '\"Drive to Nainital in the morning and on arrival check in at the hotel. evening free for leisure. Overnight stay in hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1204, 234, 'Nainital', '\"After the breakfast, you will head for the famous lake tour of Bhimtal, Sattal, Naukuchiatal, Malli Tal. Overnight stay in Hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1205, 234, 'Nainital', '\"After having the breakfast, visit Snow View Point, Bara Pathar, Tiffin Top, Zoo. In the evening, enjoy shopping at the Mall Road. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1206, 234, 'Nainital - Delhi', 'After early breakfast, drive back to Delhi. On arrival to Delhi, drop at your place.'),
(1207, 235, 'DELHI - NAINITAL (320 KMS / 08 HRS)Nainital Tourist Attraction', '\"Morning pick from Delhi and drive to captivating Nainital. upon arrival Nainital check in at Hotel. evening free for leisure, Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1208, 235, 'Nainital', '\"After breakfast, start the lake tour of Nainital including Naukuchiatal, Bhimtal, Malli Tal and Khurpa Tal. Evening you can either do shopping in the Mall Road or enjoy boat ride in Naini Lake and visit Naina Devi Temple. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1209, 235, 'Nainital-Delhi', 'After breakfast head back to Delhi. Upon arrival at Delhi, drive to your home.'),
(1210, 236, 'Delhi - Ranikhet (340 kms/8hrs)Ranikhet Tourist Attraction', '\"Arrive at the airport and proceed on a memorable drive to the captivating hill station of Ranikhet. After reaching the hill station, check into your hotel and spend a pleasant evening. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1211, 236, 'Ranikhet', '\"Enjoy a full day sightseeing tour of Ranikhet and see the Haidakhan Temple and Chaukhutia Apple Orchard. Visit the magnificent sprawling golf course and try out your hand in this sport. Rest of the day, you can spend the time as you want like shopping in the market or visit the Kumaon Regimental Centre Museum (at your own expense). Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1212, 236, 'Ranikhet - Delhi', 'After breakfast drive back to Delhi and drop at your place.'),
(1213, 237, 'Delhi - Kausani (410 kms/10 hrs)Kausani Tourist Attraction', '\"Morning upon arrival at Delhi Airport or Railway station or your desired location. you will picked up by our representative. “Welcome” and transfer to Kausani by road. Upon arrival at Kausani check into your pre-booked Hotel, evening free for leisure, Overnight stay at the Hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1214, 237, 'Kausani', '\"In the morning witness the beautiful sunrise in the snow-capped Himalayas. After the delicious breakfast, proceed to explore the mesmerizing beauty of Kausani region. Visit Anasakti Ashram it is Known as Gandhi Ashram, Laxmi Ashram, Sumitranandan Pant Gallery, Kausani Tea Estate. Evening free at leisure overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1215, 237, 'Kausani', '\"Morning after breakfast day visit to Bageshwar upon arrival visit Bagnath Temple, The temple was built in 1450 by Kumaon ruler, Laxmi Chand, at the confluence of Gomati and Sarayu Rivers. En-route also visit the Baijnath Temple which is located on the bank of River Gomti, evening back to Hotel for overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1216, 237, 'Kausani', '\"After breakfast drive back to Delhi our car will drop you at Airport or Railway station or any other place of your desire for onward destination.\r\n\"'),
(1217, 238, 'Delhi - Corbett (270 kms/6 hrs)Corbett National Park Tour', 'Arrive at the airport and transfer by road to the Corbett. After arriving, check into the hotel, have the scrumptious breakfast and visit the Girija Devi Temple. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1218, 238, 'Corbett', '\"After breakfast depart for the jungle safari. Arrive at the hotel in the afternoon; then again proceed for the jeep safari. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1219, 238, 'Corbett – Delhi', 'After breakfast, depart for Delhi and upon reaching drop at your respective place.');
INSERT INTO `tour_daywise` (`itinerydata_id`, `tour_id`, `itinerydata_title`, `itinerydata_description`) VALUES
(1220, 239, 'Delhi - Nainital (7 hrs drive)Nainital Tourist Attraction', '\"In the morning drive to Nainital and upon arrival transfer to a hotel. You can unwind at the hotel, go for a walk to catch a glimpse of the scenic beauty or can enjoy boating in Naini Lake. Return to the hotel for overnight stay.\r\nLocated at an elevation of 1,938 meters (6,358 feet) above sea level, Nainital is a splendid hill station in Uttarakhand. It cuddles a beautifully pear-shaped lake, which is about 2 miles in circumference.\r\n\"'),
(1221, 239, 'Nainital', '\"Post breakfast, we will be taking you for a sightseeing tour of Nainital. We will be visiting the most famous tourist charms of the place. You will be free to explore the local markets and grab some memories to be cherished forever.\r\n\"'),
(1222, 239, 'Nainital - Kausani Tourist Attraction', '\"Early in the morning after breakfast, we will leave for Kausani via Ranikhet. In Ranikhet, we will be visiting Chaubatia, Kalika and Upat. Spend the day in leisure, followed by dinner and overnight stay in a hotel at Kausani.\r\nKausani\r\n117 kilometers from Nainital, Kausani is located at a height of 1890 meters in the Bageshwar district of Uttarakhand. Because of its exceptional natural splendor, Mahatma Gandhi named Kausani as the “Switzerland of India”. Kausani provides an exceptional vista of various Himalayan peaks like Trisul, Nanda Devi and Panchchuli. Moreover, it stands on the top the ridge amidst dense Pine trees overlooking Someshwar valley on one side and Garur and Baijnath Katyuri valley on the other on Almora-Bageshwar-Didihat Highway.\"'),
(1223, 239, 'Kausani', 'This day is completely dedicated for local sightseeing and leisure activities at Kausani. Come back to hotel for dinner and overnight stay.'),
(1224, 239, 'Almora Tourist Attraction', '\"In the morning after breakfast, we will head off for Almora. You can enjoy the picture perfect scenery of the place, followed by dinner and overnight stay in the hotel.\r\nAlmora\r\nAlmora is a municipal board, a cantonment town in the Almora district in the state of Uttarakhand, India. Situated at a height of 1638 meters (5,500 feet) on a ridge at the southern edge of the Kumaon Hills, it is famous for cosseting the beauty of nature. Further, it is also recognized for its cultural richness, unique handicrafts, tempting delicacies and fascinating wildlife. All this is quite enough to entice tourists from far and wide.\r\n\"'),
(1225, 239, 'Departure Almora', 'Drive back to Delhi after breakfast. On arrival, we will transfer you to airport or railway station for your journey back home.'),
(1226, 240, 'Delhi- Nainital (7 hrs drive)Nainital Tourist Attraction', '\"In the morning drive to Nainital. Upon arrival, transfer to hotel. For the rest of the day you are free either to relax, or to go on a sighting tour of local spots, or visit the Mall Road, or boat ride in Naini Lake. Return to the hotel for an overnight stay.\r\nNainital\r\nLocated at a height of 1,938 meters (6,358 feet) above sea level, Nainital is among the center of attractions in Uttarakhand. This hill station cuddles oodles of natural wonders in its arms and perhaps, that’s why tourists from different nooks and corners of the globe visit the place.\r\n\"'),
(1227, 240, 'Nainital', '\"This day is dedicated completely for sighting the exquisiteness cosseted in Nainital. In the morning post breakfast, we will take you to the most famous and visited tourist destinations of the hill station. You are free to shop and bag wonderful memories for taking back home.\r\n\"'),
(1228, 240, 'Nainital-Mukteshwar (01 ½ hrs drive)Mukteshwar Tourist Attraction', '\"Post breakfast, we will drive to Mukteshwar. On the way, we will be visiting Bhimtal. Upon arrival, transfer to the hotel and relax for rest of the day. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1229, 240, 'Mukteshwar-Delhi (08 hrs drive)', 'Early morning, after you enjoy a scrumptious breakfast, we will drive back to Delhi. On reaching Delhi, we will transfer you to airport or railway station for your journey back home.'),
(1230, 241, 'Delhi- Nainital (7 hrs drive)Nainital Tourist Attraction', '\"Drive to a beautiful paradise on earth- Nainital, positioned among the Kumaon hills in the Indian state of Uttarakhand. On arrival, check in to a hotel. In the evening you can explore beautiful sights or pay a visit to Mall Road. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1231, 241, 'Nainital', '\"After having a breakfast set off to the charming destinations of Nainital. The important places you will cover today are Laxman Lake, Hanuman Lake, Bhimtal, Sita Lake and Nal Damyanti Lake. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1232, 241, 'Nainital- RanikhetRanikhet Tourist Attraction', '\"Check out from hotel after having a delectable breakfast. Travel to Ranikhet, on the way visit the Kainchi Dham. Check in at a hotel. Relax and enjoy a scrumptious lunch, and then we will take you to Haidakhan Babaji Ashram at Chilyanaula, wherein you are free to enjoy for the rest of the day. Overnight stay at a hotel in Ranikhet.\r\n\"'),
(1233, 241, 'Ranikhet', '\"In the morning post a healthy breakfast, we will take you for a sightseeing tour of Ranikhet. We will take you to the Ranikhet Golf Course, which is a beautiful 9-hole golf course field cuddled by the vistas of various mountain slopes. Further, we will take you to the apple orchards. Later return to the hotel for an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1234, 241, 'Ranikhet - Delhi', '\"Early morning after breakfast, we will drive back to Delhi. On reaching we will transfer you to airport or railway station for your journey back home.\r\n\"'),
(1235, 241, 'Delhi- Nainital (7 hrs drive)Nainital Tourist Attraction', '\"Drive to a beautiful paradise on earth- Nainital, positioned among the Kumaon hills in the Indian state of Uttarakhand. On arrival, check in to a hotel. In the evening you can explore beautiful sights or pay a visit to Mall Road. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1236, 241, 'Nainital', '\"After having a breakfast set off to the charming destinations of Nainital. The important places you will cover today are Laxman Lake, Hanuman Lake, Bhimtal, Sita Lake and Nal Damyanti Lake. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1237, 241, 'Nainital- Ranikhet - Ranikhet Tourist Attraction', '\"Check out from hotel after having a delectable breakfast. Travel to Ranikhet, on the way visit the Kainchi Dham. Check in at a hotel. Relax and enjoy a scrumptious lunch, and then we will take you to Haidakhan Babaji Ashram at Chilyanaula, wherein you are free to enjoy for the rest of the day. Overnight stay at a hotel in Ranikhet.\r\n\"'),
(1238, 241, 'Ranikhet', '\"In the morning post a healthy breakfast, we will take you for a sightseeing tour of Ranikhet. We will take you to the Ranikhet Golf Course, which is a beautiful 9-hole golf course field cuddled by the vistas of various mountain slopes. Further, we will take you to the apple orchards. Later return to the hotel for an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1239, 241, 'Ranikhet - Delhi', '\"Early morning after breakfast, we will drive back to Delhi. On reaching we will transfer you to airport or railway station for your journey back home.\r\n\"'),
(1240, 242, 'Delhi-Corbett National Park (260 km; 06-07 hrs)Jim Corbett National Park Tour', '\"In the morning drive from Delhi to Jim Corbett National Park. Upon arrival transfer to a wildlife resort and unwind yourself, followed by dinner and overnight stay.\r\nThe Jim Corbett National Park\r\nEstablished in the year 1936, Jim Corbett National Park is the first national park in the Asian continent. The park has got its name from a hunter turned conservationist Edward James Corbett. He was the one who contributed a lot towards the establishment of the park. Further, this park was set up to save the critically endangered feline species – the Royal Bengal Tiger. It was the very place where Project Tiger was launched in 1973. Presently Corbett is a home to various species of fauna and flora.\r\n\"'),
(1241, 242, 'Dhikala Forest Lodge', 'Early in the morning we will take you for a wildlife safari into the Corbett National Park. The early hours of morning are best for sighting tigers. Later, return back to the resort for breakfast. Post breakfast, we will take to Garjiya Devi Temple along the Kosi River. Again return to the resort for lunch. In the afternoon, we will drive towards Dhangadi gate, which is the entry gate for Dhikala Zone. Upon arrival check into the Dhikala Forest lodge for an overnight stay.'),
(1242, 242, 'Dhikala Forest LodgeA Tiger at Dhikala', 'This entire day is dedicated to wildlife tour via different modes. Early in the morning enjoy elephant safari in the park for sighting various wild beings. Return to the lodge for having breakfast and then we will take you for jeep safari to crocodile point, wherein you can witness the predatory reptile. Come back to the lodge for lunch. Later, we will take you to the watchtower overlooking a water hole. Return back to the lodge by evening and enjoy the screening of various wildlife films and documentaries; followed by dinner and overnight stay.'),
(1243, 242, 'Dhikala Forest Lodge - Nainital (80 km; 03 hrs)', '\"Check out from the Dhikala Forest Lodge early in the morning and drive towards Bhuvankhal. Witness the sun kissing the sky at Bhuvankhal and then continue driving towards Nainital. On reaching Nainital, check into a hotel and relax. Later, in afternoon we will take you on a lake tour of Nainital. The tour will include visit to Naukuchia Tal, Bhimtal, Sattal and Khurpa Tal. Further, in the evening take pleasure in boat ride on the Naini Lake. Return to the hotel for dinner and overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1244, 242, 'Nainital-Delhi', '\"Post breakfast, drive back to Delhi from Nainital. On reaching Delhi, we will transfer you to airport or railway station and you can return to home.\r\n\"'),
(1245, 243, 'Delhi-Nainital (7 hours drive)Nainital Tourist Attraction', 'Start the trip by road from Delhi to Nainital. After making it to Nainital, which is a charming hill station in Uttarakhand, check into a hotel. Freshen up and go out to scout the scenic places or enjoy boating in Naini Lake. Located at an elevation of 6358ft above sea level, it is a paradise for both young and old alike.'),
(1246, 243, 'Nainital', '\"After having scrumptious breakfast, we will take you for a sightseeing tour, which includes the most important places. While exploring the places don’t forget to buy exquisite items from the famous shops of the place.\r\n\"'),
(1247, 243, 'Nainital- Corbett (2 hours drive)A Tiger at Dhikala', '\"A morning drive to Corbett National Park where you can relish elephant ride, which takes you deep in the woods and offers you a glimpse of a variety of animal species such as barking deer, chital, Indian grey mongoose, langur, Indian pangolins and Himalayan black bears. It is the perfect place for both nature lovers and wildlife enthusiasts. Evening will be spent at the luxury hotel where you can take pleasure in an array of recreational facilities.\r\n\"'),
(1248, 243, 'Corbett', '\"Leave after breakfast for a jeep safari to explore the wild animals in the jungle. In the afternoon you will be taken to Corbett Museum and Garjiya Devi Temple. Further, you will also enjoy bird watching tour at Corbett. Dinner and night stay in the retreat.\r\n\"'),
(1249, 243, 'Corbett - Mussoorie (6 hrs drive)Mussoorie Tourist Attraction', 'Leave after breakfast for Mussoorie. Check into a hotel situated amid the picturesque surroundings. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1250, 243, 'Mussoorie', 'After having delicious meal, head off to the famous attractions of Mussoorie like Mall Road, Gun Hill Point and Kempty Falls. Return to hotel for a comfortable overnight stay.'),
(1251, 243, 'Mussoorie- Delhi', '\"Drive back to Delhi after breakfast. We will leave you to the closest airport or railway station for your trip back home.\r\n\"'),
(1252, 244, 'Delhi - Corbett (270 km; 6 hrs)Jeep Safari in Corbett National Park', 'Arrive at Delhi airport or railway station, and there our representative will meet you. We will then drive towards Jim Corbett National Park. Upon arrival check into the hotel and unwind yourself. Later, we will take you to Garjyia Devi Temple. Return to the hotel for overnight stay.'),
(1253, 244, 'Corbett', 'Early morning after breakfast we will take you for jungle safari. Many of the wild creatures are more active during dawn. Later, return to the hotel for lunch and thereafter enjoy jeep safari in various nooks and corners of the park. Come back to the hotel by evening for dinner and overnight stay.'),
(1254, 244, 'Corbett - Nainital (80 km; 3hrs)Nainital Tourist Attraction', 'Drive to Nainital in early morning. Upon arrival, check into a hotel and unwind yourself. Thereafter, we will take you to various tourist charms of the place like the Hanuman Giri, Golf Course and Naina Devi Temple. Later, return to the hotel for a comfortable overnight stay'),
(1255, 244, 'Nainital', '\"The entire day is dedicated for visiting the famous lakes of Nainital. We will take you to Naukuchia Tal, Malli Tal, Bhim Tal, Sattal and Khurpa Tal. In the second half of the day you can enjoy boat ride on the Naini Lake. Reach the hotel by evening for having a delectable dinner and comfy overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1256, 244, 'Nainital – Mussoorie (295 km; 8hrs)Mussoorie Tourist Attraction', 'Post breakfast, we will drive to Mussoorie. On reaching, transfer to a hotel and spend rest of the day either at leisure or you can visit the Mall Road.'),
(1257, 244, 'Mussoorie', '\"Today we will make you wander amid various famous tourist charms of Mussoorie. Post breakfast, we will take you to different destinations such as Kempty Fall, Mussoorie Fall, Van Chetna Kendra, Camel Back and Surkanda Devi Temple. We will get back to the hotel by evening for an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1258, 244, 'Mussoorie - Delhi, Departure (315 km; 8hrs)', 'After breakfast drive back to Delhi and on arrival you will be transferred to airport or railway station for your journey back to home.'),
(1259, 245, 'Delhi- Nainital (7 hrs drive)Nainital Tourist Attraction', '\"Drive from Delhi to Nainital in the morning. Upon arrival, check into a hotel. Relax for some time, thereafter, it is completely you call that whether you wish to please your eyes with the scenic beauty of the place or enjoy boat ride on Naini Lake. Return to the hotel by evening for having dinner and overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1260, 245, 'Nainital', '\"After breakfast, we will take you to some of the most picturesque spots of Nainital. This sightseeing tour will make you explore different beautiful lakes and landscapes cuddled in the place. The tour will also include a visit to the local market, wherein you can shop some popular handicrafts.\r\n\"'),
(1261, 245, 'Nainital – Kausani', '\"Post breakfast, we will head off for Kausani. En-route, we will let you explore the exquisiteness of Ranikhet. The places that we will be visiting in Ranikhet are Chaubatia, Kalika and Upat. Later, on reaching Kausani, you will be transferred to a hotel for a comfortable overnight stay.\r\nKausaniKausani Tourist Attraction\r\n117 kilometers from Nainital, Kausani is located at a height of 1890 meters in the Bageshwar district of Uttarakhand. Because of its exceptional natural splendor, Mahatma Gandhi named Kausani as the “Switzerland of India”. Kausani provides an exceptional vista of various Himalayan peaks like Trisul, Nanda Devi and Panchchuli. Moreover, it stands on the top the ridge amidst dense Pine trees overlooking Someshwar valley on one side and Garur and Baijnath Katyuri valley on the other on Almora-Bageshwar-Didihat Highway.\"'),
(1262, 245, 'Kausani', '\"Today we will make you wander amid various popular tourist attractions of Kausani. You will be enjoying local sightseeing and various leisure activities. Return to the hotel by evening for dinner and overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1263, 245, 'Almora Tourist Attraction', '\"Early in the morning after breakfast, we will take you to the cultural heart of Kumaon, Almora. On reaching, check into a hotel. Later, you can visit some local areas to experience the exquisiteness of Almora. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\nAlmora\r\nAlmora is a municipal board, a cantonment town in the Almora district in the state of Uttarakhand, India. Situated at a height of 1638 meters (5,500 feet) on a ridge at the southern edge of the Kumaon Hills, it is famous for cosseting the beauty of nature. Further, it is also recognized for its cultural richness, unique handicrafts, tempting delicacies and fascinating wildlife. All this is quite enough to entice tourists from far and wide.\r\n\"'),
(1264, 245, 'Almora – Binsar', '\"After breakfast, we will drive towards Binsar. Upon arrival, transfer to a hill resort. Later, we will take you to the Binsar Wildlife Sanctuary. Herein you can bask in the wilderness of the woods. Later, return to the hotel for overnight stay.\r\nBinsarBinsar Tourist Attraction\r\nBinsar is a steep hamlet, located on the top of the Jhandi Dhar Hills. This entire region is enveloped by dense woods of Oak, Rhododendron, Pine and Deodar. The place is popular for having the splendid Binsar Wildlife Sanctuary.\"'),
(1265, 245, 'Binsar', 'Early morning after breakfast, we will take you to the famous shrines located in and around Binsar like Bineshwar Mahadev Temple and Jageshwar Temple Complex. Later, come back to the hotel for lunch. After lunch you are free for enjoying some scenic spots of Binsar. The awe-inspiring vistas of various Himalayan peaks like Nanda Devi, Kedarnath, Chaukhamba, Trishul, Panchchuli and Nanda Kot will be waiting to soothe your eyes. Return to the hotel for dinner and overnight stay.'),
(1266, 245, 'Binsar – Delhi (8 hrs drive)', 'After breakfast in the morning, drive back to Delhi. On arrival you will be transferred to airport or railway station for your journey back home.'),
(1267, 247, 'Delhi - Nainital (7 hrs drive)', '\"Drive to Nainital in the morning. On reaching, check into a hotel. Relax for the rest of the day. Further, if you wish you can also go for a sighting tour of local spots, or visit the Mall Road, or can enjoy boat ride in the Naini Lake. Return to the hotel for an overnight stay.\r\nNainitalNainital Tourist Attraction\r\nLocated at a height of 1,938 meters (6,358 feet) above sea level, Nainital is among the center of attractions in Uttarakhand. This hill station cuddles oodles of natural wonders in its arms and perhaps, that’s why tourists from different nooks and corners of the globe visit the place.\"'),
(1268, 247, 'Nainital', 'Today you will be visiting the famous tourist charms of Nainital like Bhimtal, Naina Peak, Astronomical Observatory, Land\'s End, The Mall Road, Dorothy Seat and Tiffin Top, Raj Bhavan, Snow View Point, St. John\'s Church. You can also enjoy shopping at the local market.'),
(1269, 247, 'Nainital - Corbett (2 hrs drive)', '\"Early in the morning after breakfast, we will proceed for the Jim Corbett National Park. En-route, we will stop at Khurpatal and Corbett Falls. You are free to click some memories here. Check into a wildlife resort upon arrival and spend the rest of the day at leisure.\r\nThe Jim Corbett National Park  Elephant Safari in Corbett National Park\r\nEstablished in the year 1936, Jim Corbett National Park is the first national park in the Asian continent. The park has got its name from a hunter turned conservationist Edward James Corbett. He was the one who contributed a lot towards the establishment of the park. Further, this park was set up to save the critically endangered feline species – the Royal Bengal Tiger. It was the very place where Project Tiger was launched in 1973. Presently Corbett is a home to various species of fauna and flora.\"'),
(1270, 247, 'Corbett', '\"Early in the morning, you will enjoy jeep safari in the park. Return to the hotel for relaxing and having lunch. Post lunch in the afternoon, we will take you to the Garjiya Devi Temple and Corbett Museum. The Corbett Museum is the place where the hunts, hunting equipments and many other articles of E. James Corbett are preserved. It was originally the home of Jim Corbett. Dinner and overnight stay at the wildlife resort.\r\n\"'),
(1271, 247, 'Corbett – Delhi (6 1/2 hrs drive)', '\"In the morning we will drive back to Delhi. On reaching you will be transferred to airport or railway station for your journey back home.\r\n\"'),
(1272, 248, 'Delhi - Corbett (260 km, 06 hrs drive)', '\"In the morning we will pick you up from Delhi and then will drive towards Jim Corbett National Park. Upon arrival, transfer to a wildlife resort. For the rest of the day you are free to unwind yourself. Dinner and overnight stay at the resort.\r\nThe Jim Corbett National Park \r\nLocated in the foothills of Uttarakhand, Jim Corbett is the first national park established in Asia. Honored as a national park in 1936, this wildlife destination got its name from Edward James Corbett. He was a British hunter, who later turned into conservationist and contributed in the establishment of Corbett National Park. Presently, Corbett provides a safe and healthy habitat to one of the most beautiful beasts of the woods – the Royal Bengal Tigers. Wildlife enthusiasts pay a visit to Corbett just to get a glimpse of the big cats.\r\n\"'),
(1273, 248, 'Corbett', 'Early in the morning, you will enjoy jeep safari amid the dense woods of the Corbett National Park. Later, return to the hotel for lunch. Post lunch, we will take you to the Garjiya Temple and Corbett Museum (this museum was originally the home of E. James Corbett and has preserved the memories of the hunter turned conservationist). Come back to the resort for dinner and overnight stay.'),
(1274, 248, 'Corbett – Nainital', '\"In the morning, we will proceed towards Nainital. During the journey, we will visit the Kurpatal and Corbett Falls. Check into a hotel on arrival. Relax for the day. You are free to explore some of the local sightseeing spots like Mall Road or you can enjoy boat ride on Naini Lake. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\nNainital\r\nSituated at a height of 1,938 meters (6,358 feet) above sea level, Nainital is one of the must visit destinations of India. It is a beautiful hills station, which is known for holding the virgin beauty of Mother Nature. Visitors are left spell bound after witnessing the unmatched exquisiteness of Nainital.\r\n\"'),
(1275, 248, 'Nainital', '\"Though one single day is not enough to soak in the true essence of Nainital, we will try our best to make you explore every famous tourist hot spot of the place. During this sightseeing tour, you can also bag some famous and exclusive items from the local market.\r\n\"'),
(1276, 248, 'Nainital – Kausani', '\"After breakfast, we will head towards Kausani via Ranikhet. In Ranikhet, we will be paying a visit to Chaubatia, Kalika and Upat. Spend the day in leisure, followed by dinner and overnight stay in a hotel at Kausani.\r\nKausani\r\n117 kilometers from Nainital, Kausani is located at a height of 1890 meters in the Bageshwar district of Uttarakhand. Because of its exceptional natural splendor, Mahatma Gandhi named Kausani as the “Switzerland of India”. Kausani provides an exceptional vista of various Himalayan peaks like Trisul, Nanda Devi and Panchchuli. Moreover, it stands on the top the ridge amidst dense Pine trees overlooking Someshwar valley on one side and Garur and Baijnath Katyuri valley on the other on Almora-Bageshwar-Didihat Highway.\"'),
(1277, 248, 'Kausani – Auli', 'In the morning after breakfast, we will drive towards Auli via Joshimath (255 km; 9 - 10 hrs). Upon arrival proceed to your mountain resort by a rope trolley. Rest of the evening is at leisure for individual activities, followed by overnight at the resort.'),
(1278, 248, 'Auli', '\"Auli welcomes you with the enchanting vistas of Western Himalayas. For the entire day you are free to bask in the magnificence of the place. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1279, 248, 'Auli – Rudraprayag', '\"Early in the morning after breakfast, we will proceed for Rudraprayag. This place has been named after Lord Shiva (Rudra) and is famous for having various shrines. Moreover, it is blessed with various natural marvels like lakes and glaciers that create a wonderful sight for nature lovers. Upon arrival, check into a hotel. Spend the rest of the day at leisure, or you can indulge in some individual activities, followed by an overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1280, 248, 'Rudraprayag – Haridwar', 'The first half of the day is dedicated to temple tour. We will be taking you to different shrines located in and around Rudraprayag. Thereafter, we will drive to Haridwar. Upon arrival check into a hotel and enjoy an overnight stay.'),
(1281, 248, 'Haridwar – Delhi', 'In the morning, we will be visiting the Ganga ghat and famous temples of Haridwar. Later, we will drive back to Delhi. On reaching, we will transfer you to airport or railway station for your journey back home.'),
(1282, 249, 'Delhi-CorbettElephants in Corbett National Park', '\"Morning drive corbett National park, on arrival check in at wildlife resort, Later you can visit Corbett Fall. Evening free at leisure or you can enjoy recreation activities at resort. Dinner and over night stay at corbett.\r\n\"'),
(1283, 249, 'Corbett National Park', '\"Early morning wake up call, be ready for wildlife safari into corbett national park in search for wild animals. Later you can visit corbett Museum and Garjyia Devi temple, After lunch enjoy elephant safari int Buffer area of Corbett National park. Dinner and over night stay at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1284, 249, 'Corbett National Park', '\"Morning drive to mussoorie enroute visit Mansa and Chandi Devi Temple in haridwar. On arrival at Mussoorie check in at pre-booked hotel. Evening free at leisure Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1285, 249, 'Mussoorie Gun Hill, Mussoorrie', 'Morning after breakfast we will take you for a full day sightseeing tour of Mussoorie, tour includes Lal Tibba – The highest point in Mussoorie, located in Landour area, the oldest inhabited place in Mussoorie. Gun Hill – The second highest point in Mussoorie, offers a panoramic view of the Himalayas. Municipal Gardens – Also known as Botanical Gardens of Mussoorie has an artificially created lake, which is a perfect picnic spot with boating facilities. Kempty Falls – 15 kms from Mussoorie on the Yamunotri Road is the most fascinating and the biggest waterfall. Camel’s Back Road – The place offers a picturesque view of the sunset and a life like resemblance of a sitting camel. Municipal Garden – An artificially created lake is a perfect picnic spot with boating facilities. Overnight stay at Mussoorie.'),
