(1679, 296, 'Delhi Dept', 'Transfer to International Airport on time to catch your flight for onward destination.'),
(1680, 297, 'Arrive Mumbai', 'Upon arrival at Mumbai International airport meet with our representative and transfer to the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1681, 297, 'Mumbai', '\"After breakfast we will visit Haji Ali Dargah Sharif.\r\n09:30 am. Drive to towards Marine Drive Mumbai is an island gifted with a vast and beautiful sea coast of the Arabian Sea. Earlier being the major port, now the trade activities have been centralized in one area.\r\nThe highlights of your tour covers visit to, Haji Ali Dargah Shariff. This early 18th century shrine contains the tomb of Hazrat Haji Ali, a Muslim Sufi saint. There are two local legends which claim to trace the hazrat\'s antecedents. One story has it that Haji Ali was a rich, local businessman who gave up materialism after a visit to Mecca and then took up meditation.\r\nFurther drive to Mama Haji Ali Dargah Shariff. Amir-Bahar Haji Ismail Hashim Bahadur, A Great Captain and Navigator Of Indian Seas who died on 20th September 1912, And was buried in this Tomb.\r\nAlso visit to Makhdoom Shah Dargah. The dargah of Makhdoom Ali Mahimi (1372-1431), the secular Sufi saint, is popular as the Mahim dargah. Reported to be at least 350 years old, the Dargah sharif has five domes, the only dargah in Mumbai to have more than one dome.\r\nBy the afternoon drive back to Mumbai & enjoy local city sightseeing tour. Overnight stay at hotel\"'),
(1682, 297, 'Mumbai - Jaipur', 'After breakfast transfer to the airport to board the flight for Jaipur. Upon arrival meet with our representative & transfer to the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1683, 297, 'Jaipur', '\"Morning visit Amber Fort. Amber Fort was the ancient capital of the State. Visit the Sheesh Mahal or the Hall of Victory glittering with mirrors. Ascend the Fort on Elephant back.\r\nAfternoon tour of Jaipur. Jaipur - the capital of Rajasthan was given a colour coat of pink a century ago in honour of a visiting Prince and ever since, it has retained this colour. Built by Maharaja Jai Singh, the notable astronomer, this city is 260 years old. Visit Maharaja\'s City Palace, the Observatory & Ram Niwas Gardens. Drive past Hawa Mahal & through the pink rose residential & business areas. Overnight at Hotel.\"'),
(1684, 297, 'Jaipur - Ajmer - Jaipur', '\"After breakfast drive to Ajmer and pay a visit to the Dargah of Khwaja Moinuddin Chisti. In the evening return back to Jaipur for an overnight stay.\r\nAjmer is a popular pilgrimage center for the Hindus as well as Muslims. Especially famous is the Dargah Sharif-tomb of the Sufi saint Khwaja Moinuddin Chishti, which is equally revered by the Hindus and Muslims.\"'),
(1685, 297, 'Jaipur – Agra', '\"Morning drive to Agra. En-route visit Fatehpur Sikri - This magnificent fortified ghost city, 40 km west of Agra, was the short-lived capital of the Mughal empire between 1571 and 1585, during the reign of Emperor Akbar. Akbar visited Sikri to consult the Sufi saint Shaikh Salim Chishti, who predicted the birth of an heir to the Mughal throne.\r\nFurther drive to Agra. Upon arrival check in to the hotel. overnight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1686, 297, 'Agra - Fatehpur Sikri - Jaipur', '\"Morning visit Taj Mahal at sunrise. Back to hotel for breakfast, then proceed visit Red Fort & Sikandra, Akbar\'s Tomb.\r\nTaj Mahal: The crowning jewel of Indo-Islamic architecture, the Taj Mahal is one of the world\'s most beautiful and beloved structures. The monument was built in Agra, India, for Mumtaz Mahal, the favorite wife of Mughal emperor Shah Jahan. Construction of the tomb began in 1632 and employed more than 20,000 laborers for 20 years.\"'),
(1687, 297, 'Agra - Delhi', 'After breakfast drive to Delhi. Upon arrival check into the hotel. overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1688, 297, 'Delhi', '\"In the morning, go for a sightseeing tour of Delhi. Visit Raj Ghat (the cremation sites of Mahatma Gandhi), Shanti Vana (the cremation sites of Jawaharlal Nehru) and Jama Masjid. Drive past Red Fort and Chandni Chowk.\r\nIn the afternoon visit Qutub Minar (built by Qutub-ud-Din Aibek in 1199), Humayun\'s Tomb, India Gate (War Memorial Arch), Also drive past President\'s House, Parliament House, Government Secretariat Buildings and Connaught Place shopping centre. Stay overnight at the hotel.\"'),
(1689, 297, 'Delhi - Lucknow', 'After breakfast transfer to the airport to board the flight for Lucknow. Upon arrival check in at the hotel. evening free at leisure. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1690, 297, 'Lucknow - Faizabad - Lucknow', 'Morning after breakfast full day excursion to Faizabad visiting Fort Calcutta, Mausoleum of Bahu Begum, Mausoleum of Shuja-ud-daulah and Moti Mahal. Later return to the hotel for overnight stay.'),
(1691, 297, 'Lucknow', '\"After breakfast full day city sightseeing tour of Lucknow visiting Hazratganj Market, 1857 Memorial Museum, Juma Masjid, Sikander Bagh, Chota Imambara, Shah Najaf Imambara, Rumi Darwaza, Taluqdar Hall, Husainabad Clock Tower, Kaiserbagh Palace, Begum Hazrat Mahal Park, Aminabad, Bara Imambara, Chattar Manzil, Moti Mahal & Farangi Mahal etc.\r\nOvernight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1692, 297, 'Lucknow - Mumbai', 'Transfer to the airport to board the flight for Mumbai. Upon arrival check into the hotel. rest of the day free to explore the market. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1693, 297, 'Departure', 'Transfer to the International airport to board the flight for onward destination.'),
(1694, 298, 'Arrive Delhi', 'Upon arrival at Delhi international airport meet with our representative and transfer to the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel'),
(1695, 298, 'Delhi        jama masjid', '\"After breakfast we have full day city sightseeing tour of Delhi visiting Red Fort, Jama Masjid, humayun\'s Tomb, Safdarjang Tomb, Hazrat Nizamuddin Auliya, Lodhi Tomb and Qutub Minar. Return to hotel for overnight stay.\r\n \r\nRed Fort: The Red sandstone walls of the massive Red Fort (Lal Qila) rise 33-m above the clamour of Old Delhi is one of the most magnificent places in the world. The Fort was built by Mughal emperor Shah Jahan in 1838 is a reminder of the magnificent power and pomp of the Mughal emperors. Lahore gate, the main gate of Red Fort attracts a major crowd on each Independence Day.\r\n\r\n Jama Masjid: This great mosque of Old Delhi is the largest in India, with a courtyard capable of holding 25,000 devotees. The highly decorative mosque has three great gates, four towers and two 40 m-high minarets constructed of strips of red sandstone and  white marble.\r\n\r\njama masjid Humayun’s Tomb: This magnificent garden tomb is the first substantial example of Mughal architecture in India. It was built by Bega Begum in 1565 AD, around nine year later of demise of her husband Humayun.\r\n\r\n Safdarjang Tomb: This is the last enclosed garden tomb in Delhi in the tradition of Humayun\'s Tomb and was built in 1753- 54 as mausoleum of Safdarjung, the viceroy of Awadh under the Mughal Emperor, Muhammed Shah.\r\n\r\n Hazarat Nizamuddin Auliya: The Tomb represent to the one of the greatest  and most influential Sufi saint of Indian Sub-continent, by whose order Hazrat Amir Khusro (R.a) Invented a new language to break down barriers between south and north India (Including Pakistan, Bhutan, Nepal, Rangoon, Bangladesh and  border area of Afghanistan), for better understanding and  to serve Humanity in a unified way. Hazarat Nizamuddin was a Sufi far beyond the boundation of time, caste, creed, color, region or race.\r\n\r\n Lodhi Tomb: The tombs of Muhammad Shah and Sikandar Lodhi are the good examples of octagonal tombs. Shish and Bara Gumbad are square tombs with imposing dome, turrets on corners and facades giving false impression of being double storied.\r\n\r\n Qutub Minar: Qutub Minar is built by Qutab-ud-din Aibak as a victory tower immediately after the defeat of Delhi\'s last Hindu kingdom. This soaring, 73 m-high tower has five distinct storeys, each marked by a projecting balcony and tapers from a 15 m diameter at the base to just 2.5 m at the top.  A 7 m-high iron pillar stands in the courtyard of the mosque. It is said that if you can encircle it with your hands while standing with your back to it your wish will be fulfilled.\"'),
(1696, 298, 'Delhi - Ajmer', '\"Morning transfer to the railway station to board the Shatabdi train for Ajmer. Upon arrival at Ajmer railway station meet with our representative and transfer to the hotel. \r\n After fresh-n-up we will visit Dargah Shareef, Adhai Din Ka Jhonpra, Ana Sagar Lake etc. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n Dargah Sharif: The shrine of Khwaja Moinuddin Chishti. In 1256 AD, at the age of 114, the saint entered his cell to pray in seclusion for six days after which he passed away. It is now a sacred centre of pilgrimage. Devotees of all sects and faiths come here as the saint’s blessings. Each year, the followers of the master congregate here from all parts of the world on the occasion of the annual festival of Urs to pay their obeisance to seek the Saint’s blessings for fulfillment of wishes.\r\n Adhai Din Ka Jhonpra: A mosque originally an ancient Sanskrit College & within a temple enclosure. Proceed to Emperor Akbar’s Royal Palace made of red sand stone – housing a museum with a rich collection of Mughal & Rajput armour. This is a masterpiece of Indo - Islamic architecture. It is a relic of an old mosque consisting of a quadrangle with a front screen wall of seven pointed arches.\r\nAna Sagar Lake: Ana Sagar lake is an artificial lake and named after Anaji Chauhan.\"'),
(1697, 298, 'Ajmer - Jaipur', 'After breakfast we will leave for Jaipur. Upon arrival check into the hotel. After fresh-n-up we will proceed for sightseeing tour of Jaipur visiting its massive forts, palaces and Temple. In Jaipur we will visit the City Palace, Palace of Winds, Natural observatory etc. In the evening return to the hotel for overnight stay.'),
(1698, 298, 'Jaipur - Fatehpur Sikri - Agra ajmer', '\"This morning we will opt for an excursion to the massive fort of Amber, located 11 km from the city. The Amber Fort was built by Raja Shri Maan Singh JI Saheb in 16th century. Maan Singh, one of the first war chiefs or the trusted general of the Emperor Akbar.\r\n Later we will drive to Agra. En-route to Agra we will stop to visit Fatehpur Sikri, the Mosque built by Emperor Akbar in the memory of Sheikh Salim Chishti. Further continue drive to Agra. Upon arrival check into the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel\"');
INSERT INTO `tour_daywise` (`itinerydata_id`, `tour_id`, `itinerydata_title`, `itinerydata_description`) VALUES
(1699, 298, 'Agra - Sikandra - Delhi', '\"Today we will visit the famous Taj Mahal at dawn. Taj Mahal was built by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan as a memorial to his queen Mumtaz Mahal, made out of white marble took 22 years to complete (1630-1652 AD).\r\n After visit we will return to the hotel for fresh-n-up and breakfast. After breakfast we will visit the Agra fort, built by Akbar in 1565 as a military establishment. The Fort was made by red sandstone. During the reign of Shah Jahan it was partially converted into a palace.\r\n Further we will Itimad-ud-Daulah\'s Tomb or Baby Taj, this exquisite marble tomb was made by Emperor Jahangir\'s queen, Nur Jahan , in the memory of her father Mirza Ghiyas Beg during 1622-1628 A.D. Built entirely in white marble and inlaid with semi-precious stones, this mausoleum on the bank of the Yamuna River, exhibits a strong Persian influence.\r\n Later in the afternoon drive to Delhi, en-route we will visit Sikandra, the mausoleum of Emperor Akbar. It represents his philosophy and secular outlook, combining the best of Hindu and Muslim architectures in a superlative fusion. Completed in 1613 A.D.\r\nFurther continue drive to Delhi. Upon arrival check into the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1700, 298, 'Delhi - Departure', 'Transfer to the International airport on time to board the flight for onward destination.'),
(1701, 299, 'Delhi', 'Upon arrival at Delhi International airport meet with our company representative at the airport arrival lounge. After meet and greet we will transfer you to the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1702, 299, 'Delhi', '\"After breakfast we will go for a full day temple tour of Delhi visiting Laxmi Narayan Temple, Hanuman Mandir, Gauri Shankar Temple, India Gate, Qutab Minar, Chattarpur Temple, Bahai Temple and Akshardham Temple.\r\nlaxmi-narayan-temple-delhiLaxmi Narayan Temple: Laxmi Narayan Temple or Birla Mandir, is one of Delhi\'s major and oldest temples. The temple is dedicated to Goddess Laxmi, the goddess of prosperity and the lord Narayana, the preserver. The temple was built by the industrialist G.D. Birla in 1939 and inaugurated by Mahatma Gandhi, the father of nation.\r\nNowadays it is major tourist attraction for the people who comes to visit Delhi, and located in the west of Connaught Place.\r\nVisiting hrs: 04:30am to 1:30pm and 02.30pm to 09.00pm.\r\nHanuman Mandir: Located at Baba Kharak Singh Marg in Connaught Place, is one of the oldest Hanuman Temple in India. It is believed that the temple was built by Raja Jai Singh around 1724 AD.\r\n The Main Idol of Hanumana is facing south with holding a gada in his left hand and his right hand rests on his chest in veneration to the adjacent idols of Rama, Lakshmana and Sita. The deity Hanuman destroys all the evils with his Gada.\r\nGauri Shankar Temple: Located in Chandni Chowk, the Gauri Shankar temple is of 800 year old and dedicated to Goddess  Gauri and lord Shiva.\r\nThe temple has an 800 year old brown Lingam (phallus stone) encased in a marble representation of a female organ. The Lingam is surrounded by snakes made up of silver and represents a cosmic pillar, the centre of universe or life. The temple was built by Apa Gangadhar in promised to Lord Shiva, As Apa Gangadhar injured in a battle and prayed to Lord Shiva for his survival. He survived against all odds and then build the temple. The best time to visit the temple is during the festive of Shivaratri.\r\nchattarpur-templeChattarpur Temple: The Chhatarpur Mandir, a Hindu temple is dedicated to goddess Katyayani. The temple was founded by Sant Shree Nagpal Ji in 1974. He was died in 1998 and his samadhi shrine lies in the premises of the Shiv-Gauri Nageshwar Mandir within the temple complex. The temple has been built in both south and north Indian style of temple architecture.\r\nBahai Temple: Bahai temple or Lotus temple is built in the shape of a lotus flower and is the last of seven Major Bahai\'s temples built around the world. The temple is made up of pure white marble. The architect of Lotus temple, Fariborz Sahba chose the lotus as the symbol common to Hinduism, Buddhism, Jainism and Islam. Lotus temple is the perfect place to meditate and enjoy the silence being in the bustling city of Delhi. It remains closed for visit on Monday.\r\nAkshardham Temple: Having record of the world’s largest comprehensive Hindu Temple. Here once can visit the exhibitions center which features the incidents from the life of Swaminarayan in his teenage and the early history of India. The temple remains closed for visit on Monday.\r\n  Later in the evening transfer to the hotel for overnight stay.\"'),
(1703, 299, 'Pushkar - Jaipur', '\"Today we will visit the Brahma temple again for its morning aarti followed by a visit to the sacred Pushkar lake. Later return to hotel for breakfast.\r\n After breakfast we will leave for Jaipur. Upon arrival check into the hotel. After fresh-n-up we will proceed for sightseeing tour of Jaipur visiting its massive forts, palaces and Temple. In Jaipur we will visit the City Palace, Palace of Winds, Natural observatory, Birla Temple etc. In the evening we will have an excursion to Amber fort.\r\nLater return to hotel for overnight stay.\"'),
(1704, 299, 'Jaipur - Fatehpur Sikri - Agra', '\"After a quick breakfast we will leave for Agra. En-route to Agra we will stop to visit Fatehpur Sikri, the Mosque built by Emperor Akbar in the memory of Sheikh Salim Chishti. \r\n Further continue drive to Agra. Upon arrival check into the hotel. \r\n After fresh-n-up we will visit the Agra fort, built by Akbar in 1565 as a military establishment. The Fort was made by red sandstone. During the reign of Shah Jahan it was partially converted into a palace.\r\nFurther we will visit the famous Taj Mahal at dusk. Taj Mahal was built by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan as a memorial to his queen Mumtaz Mahal, made out of white marble took 22 years to complete (1630-1652 AD).\r\nEvening return to hotel for overnight stay.\"'),
(1705, 299, 'Agra - Jhansi - Orchha - Khajuraho', '\"Early in the morning we will transfer to the Agra railway station to board the Shatabdi train for Jhansi. Upon arrival at Jhansi railway station meet with our representative and leave for Khajuraho.  En-route we will visit Orchha which boasts of its palaces and temples built by its Bundela rulers in the 16th and 17th century. Jahangir Mahal, a tiered palace crowned by graceful chhatris has a spectacular view of soaring temple spires and cenotaphs. \r\n Further continue drive to Khajuraho. Upon arrival check into the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1706, 299, 'Khajuraho', '\"Today we will have full day temple tour of Khajuraho visiting its Eastern & Western group of temples. These temples of Khajuraho were built by the Chandela kings between 950 AD and 1050 AD. Starting our tour with a visit to Eastern group of temples, including the most important temples like the Chausath Yogini Temple dedicated to Goddess Kali, The Mahadev Temple, Chitragupta or Bharatji Temple with a lovely image of 11 headed Vishnu, Vishvanath and Nandi Temples, Lakshmana Temple, Visha Temple of Shiva, which is the largest & most typical of temples. \r\n Further we will visit the Eastern group of temples visiting the Parsvanath Temple - the only Jain Temple surviving at Khajuraho and has excellent sculptures on the outer walls of the Sanctum, the Javeri Temple dedicated to Vishnu. Here we will also visit the temples dedicated to lord Brahma, goddess Yamuna and lord Adinath. \r\n Evening one can enjoy light and sound show (Optional). Overnight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1707, 299, 'Khajuraho - Varanasi', '\"Morning at leisure. In the afternoon we will transfer to the airport to board the flight for Varanasi - the religious capital of Hindus since times immemorial and a place of devotion and worship with hundreds of temples doting the city.\r\n  Upon arrival at Varanasi airport meet with our representative and transfer to the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel\"'),
(1708, 299, 'Varanasi', '\"Morning boat cruise at the river Ganges to observe the way of life of pilgrims by the Ghats. Later we will have an excursion to Sarnath. It enjoys the extraordinary privilege of Lord Buddha delivering his first sermon after attaining enlightenment 2500 years ago. It is about 10 km from Varanasi and holds a number of Buddhist sites that include the famous Dhamekh Stupa, the seat of the holy \'Buddha\'. You can also visit the ruins of Dharmarajika Stupa and Mulagandha Kuti Temple, where Lord Buddha is said to have rested and meditated while in Sarnath. The Ashoka Pillar built by the emperor Ashoka is a must see in Sarnath. The Lion Capital on top of this pillar is now the National Emblem of India and stands apart for its excellent artistry and carvings. \r\n In the evening visit aarti darshan (light offering) at river bank. After aarti visit return to the hotel for dinner and overnight stay.\"'),
(1709, 299, 'Varanasi - Kathmandu', 'Morning transfer to the airport to board the flight for Kathmandu the capital of Nepal. The  Kathmandu valley is the political and cultural heart of the Kingdom. The urban sprawl that makes up modern Kathmandu is in fact two cities, Patan and Kathmandu. Upon arrival check into the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1710, 299, 'Kathmandu', 'Today after breakfast we will proceed for temple tour of Kathmandu visiting the Pashupatinath temple a UNESCO world heritage sites. This is the place where holy sadhus pray and cremations on the Bagmati River are carried out. It is one of the most  significant Hindu temple and oldest in Kathmandu. Pashupatinath Temple\'s existence dates back to 400 A.D. The richly-ornamented pagoda houses the sacred linga or holy symbol of Lord Shiva. Further we will visit the holiest shrine for the Buddhist culture in Nepal, the Boudhanath stupa, the UNESCO world heritage monument. The Buddhist stupa of Boudhanath Stupa is one of the largest in the world. The influx of large populations of refugees from Tibet has seen the construction of over 50 Tibetan Gompas around Boudhanath. This is the place where all devout Buddhists come for a pilgrimage.  Later return to Kathmandu for overnight stay.'),
(1711, 299, 'Kathmandu', '\"Morning after breakfast we will go for an excursion to Patan, also known as Lalitpur. The city of beauty is separated from Kathmandu by Bagmati River and is the second largest town in the valley. The city is fragmented from other cities due to its substantive architectural ancient masterpieces. Here we will visit the Patan\'s central Durbar Square which is absolutely packed with temples: It’s an architectural center point with a far greater concentration of temples per sq. meter than in Kathmandu or Bhaktapur. Within the city also lies the Tibetan refugee center, home to most of the valley\'s Tibetan population.  While technically refugees, the Tibetans are some of the wealthiest people in the valley because of the carpet industry they operate.  For those looking to bring home a fine Tibetan carpet, this is the place to shop. \r\n While on our return we will visit the Swayambhunath the golden spire of the 5th century Swayambhu stupa is adorned with a colorful fluttering of prayer flags; it crowns a hill overlooking the Kathmandu Valley and offers fantastic views over the city of Kathmandu. Swayambhunath is one of the most recognizable symbols in Nepal and the painted eyes of Buddha watch all who ascend the worn stone steps. \r\n Later transfer to the hotel for overnight stay.\"'),
(1712, 299, 'Kathmandu - Delhi', 'Morning free to enjoy some local shopping in Kathmandu. Later in the afternoon transfer to the international airport to board the flight for Delhi. Upon arrival meet with our representative and transfer to the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1713, 299, 'Delhi - Departure', 'Transfer to the international airport on time to board the flight for onward destination.'),
(1714, 300, 'ARRIVAL AT JAIPUR', 'Upon arrival at the Delhi airport or railway station, meet our representatives, who will transfer you to a hotel. Overnight stay at the Delhi hotel.'),
(1715, 300, 'DELHI LOCAL SIGHTSEEING', 'Today, you will be going for Delhi sightseeing tour. First, visit the medieval Jama Mosque followed by a rickshaw ride and walking tour of Old Delhi. Later go to Humayun’s Tomb, Qutab Minar and drive past Lutyens’ Delhi that houses important Government buildings. Overnight stay at the Delhi hotel.'),
(1716, 300, 'DELHI - AGRA – BHARATPUR', 'Early morning, drive to Agra (3.5 hours) and visit the Taj Mahal, the eternal monument of love. After exploring the beautiful Taj Mahal, drive for another hour to reach Bharatpur. Overnight stay at the Bharatpur hotel.'),
(1717, 300, 'BHARATPUR - 60 TO 70 KILOMETERS (CYCLING)', 'After breakfast, cycle to Deeg, a beautiful garden town with sparkling fountains and meticulous palaces. Overnight stay at the Bharatpur hotel.'),
(1718, 300, 'BHARATPUR - KARAULI - 110 KILOMETERS (CYCLING)', 'Cycle to Karauli, which is located in the heart of rural Rajasthan. The old, holy city of Karauli was officially founded in 1348 AD. However, legend has it that it was established by Raja Bijal pal Jadon, the 88th descendant of Lord Krishna, as far back as 995 AD. Overnight stay at the Karauli hotel.'),
(1719, 300, 'KARAULI - 40-50 KILOMETERS (CYCLING)', 'Today, you will ride in the loop around Kaila Devi National Park, a part of the Project Tiger and buffer zone to Ranthambore National Park. In the evening, we will explore the 500-year-old Karauli city palace. Overnight stay at the Karauli hotel.'),
(1720, 300, 'KARAULI - TALABGAON - 80 KILOMETERS (CYCLING)', 'Today, we will cycle to the rural region of Rajasthan- Talabgaon. It will be a beautiful ride that will pass through the countryside and small villages. Overnight stay at Talabgaon hotel.'),
(1721, 300, 'TALABGAON - JAIPUR - 90-100 KILOMETERS (CYCLING)', 'Post breakfast, cycle to Jaipur, the pink city and the capital of Rajasthan. Overnight stay at the Jaipur hotel.'),
(1722, 300, 'JAIPUR - DELHI - ONWARD JOURNEY', 'Check out from the hotel and drive to Amber Fort, which was constructed in 1592 by Maharaja Man Singh, the Rajput commander of Akbar\'s army. After exploring the Amber Fort, drive to Delhi.'),
(1723, 301, 'DELHI', 'Upon arrival in Delhi, meet our representatives, who will transfer you to a hotel. Rest of the day will be free for leisure. Overnight stay in the Delhi hotel.'),
(1724, 301, 'DELHI SIGHTSEEING', '\"Post breakfast, go for city sightseeing tour. Start your day with a visit to New Delhi attractions like Qutub Minar; Humayun Tomb and Raj Ghat. In the afternoon, proceed to Old Delhi, where you will visit Red Fort, Jama Masjid, and Chandni Chowk. Your tour ends with a drive through Indian Gate (the War monument) and the President House. Overnight stay will be at Delhi.\r\n \"'),
(1725, 301, 'DELHI - JODHPUR BY FLIGHT & JODHPUR TO ROHET BY THE DRIVE', '\"Check out from the hotel and proceed to airport to board a flight to Jodhpur. From Jodhpur Airport, hop in jeeps that will take you to Rohet Garh, also knows as the \'Evergreen Oasis in the Desert\'. In the afternoon, enjoy Jeep Safari through the Bishnoi Village where you can get an experience of Tribal India. Overnight stay in the Rohet Garh hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1726, 301, 'ROHET – POKHRAN', 'After breakfast at the hotel, drive to Pokhran. On the way to Pokhran, enjoy guided sightseeing tour of Jodhpur visit Mehrangarh Fort and Jaswant Thada. Later, continue to drive to Pokhran. Upon arrival in Pokhran, meet our representatives who will transfer you to a hotel. The evening will be free for leisure.'),
(1727, 301, 'POKHRAN - SAFARI THROUGH THE SAND DUNES', 'Today, you will go for safari in porch area. Bhikodai Village, Baniyana Village, Ujala Village, and Falsund Village are the main villages that you will uncover today. After safari tour, go camping at Chaba Village for an overnight stay.'),
(1728, 301, 'SAFARI TOUR', 'During today\'s jeep safari tour, you will visit Bharadie Village, Bhesda, and Rajmathai. After a whole day activity, our night stay will be at Dangri Village.'),
(1729, 301, 'SAFARI TOUR', 'Post breakfast at the camp, begin jeep safari towards Bhikaji ki Dhani. Rasla, Nehadie Dwada, Tadana and Moolana are other important places you will visit. Overnight stay in Moolana camp.'),
(1730, 301, 'SAFARI TOUR', 'Today, you will head towards Sodha ki Dhani, Bamno ki Dhani, Ascha, Jairath, Basanper and Meghwalo ki Dhani. After whole day activity, you will be driven back to Jaisalmer. On arrival, you will be transferred to hotel for overnight stay and dinner.'),
(1731, 301, 'SAFARI TOUR', 'On a ninth day, you will visit the Bhu and Bhopa villages, Narsingh ki Dhani, Digri Village and Chelak Villages. Night stay will be arranged in Devra camp.'),
(1732, 301, 'SAFARI TOUR', 'Drive back to Chelak Village and then to villages like Hapa, Adbala, and Janra. Later, proceed to Khuri Village for overnight camp.'),
(1733, 301, 'SAFARI TOUR', 'While doing jeep safari, you will make your way through Barna Village, Kumar Kotha, Sipla Village, Ghuriya Jamda and Kanoi. Overnight stay will be arranged in sand dunes of Jaisalmer. During sunset, you can also enjoy a camel ride in Sam Sand Dunes.'),
(1734, 301, 'DRIVE TO JAISALMER', 'After breakfast, drive to Jaisalmer. Upon arrival, check in the hotel. Later go for Jaisalmer sightseeing tour. You will visit Jaisalmer Fort, Salim Singh Haveli, and Patwon Ki Haveli. In the evening, you can visit the local markets. Overnight stay in the Jaisalmer hotel.'),
(1735, 301, 'JAISALMER - JODHPUR – DELHI (FLIGHT)', 'After breakfast, drive to Jodhpur airport from where you would board your flight back to Delhi. On arrival in Delhi, meet our representatives who will transfer you to a hotel. The evening will be free for leisure. Overnight stay at the Delhi hotel.'),
(1736, 301, 'DEPARTURE', 'This morning, after breakfast, our representative will escort you to Delhi Airport from where you board your flight back to your destination onwards.'),
(1737, 302, 'ARRIVE DELHI', 'Upon arrival in Delhi, meet Tour My India who will help you transfer to hotel. Overnight stay in the Delhi hotel.'),
(1738, 302, 'DELHI SIGHTSEEING', 'In the morning, proceed for a sightseeing tour of Delhi. Visit Raj Ghat (the cremation sites of Mahatma Gandhi), Shanti Vana (the cremation sites of Jawaharlal Nehru) and Jama Masjid. You will also see Red Fort and Chandni Chowk. In the afternoon, visit Qutub Minar (built by Qutub-ud-Din Aibek in 1199), Humayun\'s Tomb, India Gate (War Memorial Arch) and Lakshminarayan Temple (a modern Hindu Temple). Also, we will be driving past President\'s House, Parliament House, Government Secretariat Buildings and Connaught Place shopping center. Overnight stay at the Delhi hotel.'),
(1739, 302, 'DELHI - MANDAWA (240 KMS)', '\"Check out from the Delhi hotel and drive to Mandawa. En route Mandawa, visit Jhunjhunu. On arrival in Mandawa, meet our representative who will assist you in hotel\'s check process. Overnight stay in the Mandawa hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1740, 302, 'MANDAWA - BIKANER (190 KMS)', 'After breakfast in the morning, go for guided heritage tour in Mandawa Village. Later, drive to Bikaner. On arrival in Bikaner, check-in at the hotel. The evening is free for your leisure activities. Overnight stay in the Bikaner hotel.'),
(1741, 302, 'BIKANER - JAISALMER', '\"In the morning after breakfast, go for Bikaner sightseeing tour. You will visit Bikaner Fort, the Lalgarh Palace, Deshnoke Temple and Junagadh Fort. Later, drive to Jaisalmer. On arrival in Jaisalmer, check-in at the hotel for an overnight stay.\r\n \"'),
(1742, 302, 'JAISALMER - BADA BAGH - BAISAKHI - RAMKUNDA', '\"Begin your day with a camel ride to Bada Bagh. Overnight stay will be organized in the Ramkunda camp.\r\n \"'),
(1743, 302, 'RAMKUNDA - ROOPSE - LUDHARVA - CHATRAYIL', 'After breakfast, proceed to Ludharva via Roopsi, a mixed cast village with mud and stick houses. Enjoy your lunch at Ludharva. Later, visit Jain temple & proceed to Chatrayil, a traditional and typical Muslim village. On arrival in Chatrayil, enjoy dinner and night stay in the camp.'),
(1744, 302, 'CHATRAYIL - SALKHA BERI OF KANOI - SAND DUNES', 'In the morning, proceed to Salkha, a traditional Rajput village. Thereafter, have lunch and proceed to Sand dunes via Beri of Kanoi, a place packed with water wells. Further, after reaching sand dunes, enjoy dinner, desert folk music, and campfire at sand dunes.'),
(1745, 302, 'SAND DUNES - KANOI - MASOORDI - JESEIRI', 'After breakfast in the morning, visit Masoordi via Kanoi. A typical carpenters village. Here, you can see and buy beautifully carved wooden items. On arrival in Masoordi, have lunch and proceed to Jeseiri: water tank surroundings by Oasis and beautiful landscape. Enjoy dinner and an overnight stay at the camp.'),
(1746, 302, 'JESEIRI - DEDHA - DEEGASAR - KULDHARA', 'In the morning, after breakfast, you will proceed to Deegasar via Dedha. Enjoy your lunch at Deegasar. Thereafter, proceed for Kuldhara via a small Rajput Dhani. Overnight stay in Kuldhara camp.'),
(1747, 302, 'KULDHARA - MOOLSAGARS - AMARSAGAR - JAISALMER', 'Today after breakfast, leave for Jaisalmer via Moolsagar and Amarsagar. On arrival in Jaisalmer, check in the hotel. Rest of the day will be free for leisure. Overnight stay in Jaisalmer.'),
(1748, 302, 'JAISALMER', 'After breakfast in the hotel, go for Jaisalmer sightseeing tour. You will visit Jaisalmer Fort, Jaisalmer War Museum, Patwaon-Ki-Haveli and Jain Temple. Overnight stay in the Jaisalmer hotel.'),
(1749, 302, 'JAISALMER - JODHPUR (290 KMS)', '\"After breakfast in the morning, drive to Jodhpur. En-route Jodhpur, visit Mandore. On arrival in Jodhpur, check in at the hotel. Evening free for leisure activities. An overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1750, 302, 'JODHPUR - JAIPUR (330 KMS)', 'After breakfast, go for a sightseeing tour of Jodhpur city. Visit the Mehrangarh Fort, the Jaswant Thada, and the Umaid Bhawan Palace. In the afternoon, you will drive to Jaipur. On arrival in Jaipur, check-in at the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1751, 302, 'JAIPUR', '\"In the morning, you will visit the Amber Fort. Ascend the fort on an Elephant back. In the afternoon, we will go for a sightseeing tour of Jaipur. Later, we will drive past the Hawa Mahal. An overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1752, 302, 'JAIPUR - AGRA (240 KMS)JAIPUR - AGRA (240 KMS)', '\"After breakfast in the morning, we will drive to Agra. En route, visit Fatehpur Sikri. On arrival in Agra, check-in at the hotel. In the afternoon, we will be visiting the Agra Fort, which has the Pearl Mosque, Diwan-e-am (the hall of public audience) and Diwan-e-Khas (the hall of private audience). An overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1753, 302, 'AGRA - DELHI (204 KMS)', 'Visit Taj Mahal after enjoying breakfast at the hotel Taj Mahal built by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan as a memorial to his queen Mumtaz Mahal, made out of white marble took 22 years to complete (1630-1652 AD). Later continue drive to Delhi. On arrival at Delhi drop you at the international airport to connect flight for onward destination.'),
(1754, 303, 'ARRIVE UDAIPUR – MOUNT ABU', '\"Upon arrival at Udaipur meeting and assistance followed by drive to Mount Abu. On arrival check-in at hotel. Evening visit to Sun Set Point back to hotel and overnight stay at hotel.\r\nSun Set Point: Sunset Point located in South West of Nakki Lake provides you a scenic view of the setting sun. Hundreds of people swarm this area in the evening amidst a carnival atmosphere.\"'),
(1755, 303, 'MOUNT ABU', '\"After breakfast visit to Nakki Lake.Brahmakumari Vinavati Ashram, Arbuda Devi, Dilwara Temple.\r\nNakki Lake: Innumerable attributes are crowned on the head of this intriguing lake. For diehard Abuphills it founts from the centre of the earth! On one hand if it is the largest manmade lake at the height of 11,00 meters in India then on the other hand it is romantically called the love lake of Mount Abu.\r\nDilwara Temple: The famous Jain temples, are situated at Dilwara village about 2½ Kms from the beautiful city of Mt. Abu. The temples are carved in marble, the design and accuracy of workmanship is unbelievable.\r\n \"'),
(1756, 303, 'MOUNT ABU - UDAIPUR', 'After breakfast full day city tour of Udaipur, visit City Palace, Saheliyon ki Bari (Gardens of the maids of Honor), Museum and Jagdish Temple. In the evening take a boat ride at Lake Pichola. Later transfer to your hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1757, 303, 'UDAIPUR', '\"After breakfast take a boat ride at Lake Pichola. Next visit City Palace - It was built by the Maharana Udai Singh as the capital of the Sisodia Rajput clan in 1559. Jagdish Temple- Jagdish Temple is a large Hindu temple in the middle of Udaipur in Rajasthan. A big tourist attraction, the temple was originally called the temple of Jagannath Rai but is now called Jagdish-Ji, Saheliyon ki Bari (Gardens of the maids of Honor) and Museum. Evening transfer to the hotel. Stay overnight at the hotel.\r\nUdaipur the \"\"City of Lakes\"\" is one among the most romantic and most beautiful city of India. It is a lovely land around the blue water lakes, edge of the lush hills of the Aravalis. A vision in white soaked in romance and beauty, Udaipur city of Rajasthan state is a fascinating blend of sights, sounds and experiences - an inspiration for the imagination of the painters, poets and writers. Udaipur\'s lakes, gardens, temples and narrow lanes scattered with stalls, carry the flavor of heroic past, epitomizing valor and chivalry.\r\n \"'),
(1758, 303, 'UDAIPUR – DEPART', 'Breakfast at the hotel and transfer to airport to connect flight for onward destination.'),
(1759, 304, 'ARRIVE DELHI', 'Upon arrival at Delhi meeting and assistance followed by transfer to hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1760, 304, 'DELHI', '\"Breakfast at the hotel and proceed for city tour of Delhi. Visit Raj Ghat and Shanti Vana - the cremation sites of Mahatma Gandhi and Jawaharlal Nehru, Jama Masjid - Jama Masjid commissioned by the Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan, it is the largest and best-known mosque in India and drive past Red Fort and Chandni Chowk.\r\nAfternoon visit Humayun\'s Tomb, Qutub Minar built by Qutub-ud-Din Aibek in 1199, Lakshminarayan Temple - a modern Hindu Temple, India Gate (War Memorial Arch ),. Also drive past President\'s House, Parliament House, and Government Secretariat Buildings. Overnight at hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1761, 304, 'DELHI - NAWALGARH', '\"After breakfast drive to Nawalgarh. On arrival check-in at hotel. Evening free to explore the place. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\nNawalgarh is a town in Jhunjhunu district of Indian state Rajasthan. It is part of the Shekhawati region and is midway between Jhunjhunu and Sikar. Nawalgarh is famous for its fresco and havelis and considered as Golden City of Rajasthan. It is also the motherland of some great business families of India.\"'),
(1762, 304, 'NAWALGARH - BIKANER', '\"After breakfast take a walking sightseeing tour of Nawalgarh Havelis, Poddar Haveli, Aath Haveli, Morarka Haveli and Bala Qila. Later drive to Bikaner. On arrival check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\nBikaner founded in 1488, the desert city of Bikaner is located in north-western Rajasthan. The city was founded by Rao Bika with the help of Nehra Jats. Bikaner was well protected from its enemies by the harsh deserts. It was also a major trade centre as it was located on the ancient caravan route which linked Central Asia and North India with Gujarat seaports.\"'),
(1763, 304, 'BIKANER - JAISALMER', '\"After breakfast go for half day tour of Bikaner, visiting the Bikaner Fort (Junagarh Fort) - The fort was originally called Chintamani and was renamed Junagarh or \"\"Old Fort\"\" in the early 20th century when the ruling family moved to Lalgarh Palace outside the fort limits, The Lalgarh Palace - The palace was built between 1902 and 1926 according to Rajput, Mughal and European architectural styles and the Deshnoke Temple (Karni Mata Temple) - Karni Mata, considered as an incarnation of Goddess Durga lived here in the fourteenth century and performed many miracles.\r\nAfternoon drive to Jaisalmer, on arrival check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1764, 304, 'JAISALMER', '\"After breakfast go for full day for sightseeing tour of Jaisalmer. Visit the Jaisalmer Fort- Jaisalmer Fort is one of the largest forts in the world. It is situated in Jaisalmer city in the Indian state of Rajasthan. It was built in 1156 AD by the Bhati Rajput ruler Rao Jaisal, from where it derives it name, Manak Chowk, Havelis, Gadisar Lake - Gadisar Lake is one of the most important tourist attractions in Jaisalmer, Rajasthan, Its charm lies in the fact that it was the only source of water for the Jaisalmer city in the olden days, and the colourful markets. In the afternoon go for an excursion to Sam Sand Dunes. In the evening take a camel safari and enjoy the sunset at sand dunes. Later drive back to Jaisalmer. Stay overnight at the hotel.\r\nJaisalmer was founded by Prince Jaisal Bhatti. The town stands on a ridge of yellowish sandstone, crowned by a fort, which contains the palace and several ornate Jain temples. Centuries ago Jaisalmer\'s strategic position on the camel train routes brought its locals enormous wealth which they spent in building intricately carved palaces and temples in golden-yellow sandstone. These fortresses of Jaisalmer also known as Havelis of Jaisalmer are like a mirage in the barren Thar Desert. On either side of the narrow lanes of Jaisalmer are the sandstone havelis, made up with stone carvings, screen windows, delicate pavilions and balconies.\"'),
(1765, 304, 'JAISALMER - JODHPUR - LUNI', '\"After breakfast drive to Luni, via Jodhpur. On arrival at Jodhpur go for half day city tour, visit the Mehrangarh Fort - Mehrangarh Fort, located in Jodhpur, Rajasthan, is one of the largest forts in India. The fort is situated 400 feet above the city and is enclosed by imposing thick walls, The Jaswant Thada - The Jaswant Thada is an architectural landmark located in Jodhpur. It is a white marble memorial built by Sardar Singh in 1899 in memory of Maharaja Jaswant Singh II and the Umaid Bhawan Palace - Umaid Bhawan Palace is one of the world\'s largest private residences. A part of the palace is managed by Taj Hotels. Named after Maharaja Umaid Singh, grandfather of the present owners of the palace, this monument has 347 rooms and serves as the principal residence of the erstwhile Jodhpur royal family.\r\nLater continue drive to Luni. On arrival check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel\"'),
(1766, 304, 'LUNI - UDAIPUR', '\"After breakfast visit Fort Chanwa - Fort Chanwa is famous for its grace Indian architecture. This entire fort is carved out of the famous red sandstone of Jodhpur. Later drive to Udaipur. On arrival Udaipur check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1767, 304, 'UDAIPUR', '\"In the morning take a boat ride at Lake Pichola. Next visit City Palace - It was built by the Maharana Udai Singh as the capital of the Sisodia Rajput clan in 1559. Jagdish Temple - Jagdish Temple is a large Hindu temple in the middle of Udaipur in Rajasthan. A big tourist attraction, the temple was originally called the temple of Jagannath Rai but is now called Jagdish-Ji, Saheliyon ki Bari (Gardens of the maids of Honor) and Museum. Evening transfer to the hotel. Stay overnight at the hotel.\r\nUdaipur the \"\"City of Lakes\"\" is one among the most romantic and most beautiful city of India. It is a lovely land around the blue water lakes, edge of the lush hills of the Aravalis. A vision in white soaked in romance and beauty, Udaipur city of Rajasthan state is a fascinating blend of sights, sounds and experiences - an inspiration for the imagination of the painters, poets and writers. Udaipur\'s lakes, gardens, temples and narrow lanes scattered with stalls, carry the flavor of heroic past, epitomizing valor and chivalry.\"'),
(1768, 304, 'UDAIPUR - DEOGARH', '\"After breakfast drive to Deogarh. On arrival Deogarh check-in to the hotel. Later visit the surrounding villages and witness their daily lifestyle of living of the villagers. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\nDeogarh is situated on the boundaries of Mewar. The Rawat, chief of Deogarh, was one of sixteen umraos (feudal barons) entitled to wait upon the Maharana of Udaipur, the capital of Mewar.\"'),
(1769, 304, 'DEOGARH - PUSHKAR', '\"After breakfast drive to Pushkar. On arrival Pushkar check-in to the hotel. Evening free to visit surroundings, also evening proceed for Aarti ceremony at Lord Brahma Temple - The temple is one of very few existing temples dedicated to the Hindu creator-god Brahma in India and remains the most prominent among them. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\nPushkar in Sanskrit means blue lotus flower. Hindus believe that the gods released a swan with a lotus in its beak and let it fall on earth where Brahma would perform a grand yagna. The place where the lotus fell was called Pushkar. Pushkar is also famous of their fairs and festivals. Three popular fairs of Pushkar are the Pushkar Fair, Tejaji fair and Nagaur fair and the Pushkar fair the most happening among them.\"'),
(1770, 304, 'PUSHKAR - JAIPUR', '\"After breakfast morning free to explore the temples and Ghats of Pushkar. In the afternoon drive to Jaipur. On arrival check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1771, 304, 'JAIPUR', '\"After breakfast visit the Amber Fort ascend the fort on an Elephant back - Amer, originally, was the capital of the state before Jaipur. It is an old fort, built in 1592 by Raja Man Singh, Maharaja\'s City Palace - City Palace, Jaipur, which includes the Chandra Mahal and Mubarak Mahal palaces and other buildings, is a palace complex in Jaipur, The Observatory (Jantar Mantar) - The Jantar Mantar is a collection of architectural astronomical instruments, built by Sawai Jai Singh who was a Mughal Commander and served Emperor Aurangzeb and later Mughals. Drive past the Hawa Mahal (Palace of Winds) - Its unique five-storey exterior is also akin to the honeycomb of the beehive with its 953 small windows called jharokhas that are decorated with intricate latticework. Evening transfer to hotel. Stay overnight at hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1772, 304, 'JAIPUR - AGRA', '\"After breakfast drive to Agra, en-route visit Fatehpur Sikri - Fatehpur Sikri was founded in 1569 by the Mughal emperor Akbar and served as the capital of the Mughal Empire from 1571 to 1585. Though the city is in ruins, it is a must visit place for those who visit Agra. Fatehpur Sikri is a place where one should spend some time. The sunset over the ruins of this fort is a sight to be cherished.\r\nOn arrival at Agra check-in at hotel. Later visit Agra fort - Agra Fort, is a monument, a UNESCO World Heritage site. The fort is built alongside the Yamuna river and stretches almost 2.5 km. It consists of a wall built in red sandstone and several buildings inside. The wall has 2 gates, the Delhi Gate and the Amar Singh Gate. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1773, 304, 'AGRA - DELHI', '\"Morning visit the famous Taj Mahal - It was built by Mughal emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his third wife, Mumtaz Mahal. Taj Mahal is regarded by many as the finest example of Mughal architecture, a style that combines elements from Persian and Indian architectural styles. This monument is made of white marble and it took 22 years to get constructed.\r\nAfter breakfast drive back to Delhi. On arrival check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1774, 304, 'DELHI DROP', 'After breakfast transfer to the Airport to connect flight for onward destination.'),
(1775, 305, 'DELHI- JAIPUR : ( 260 KILOMETERS ; 06 HOURS)', '\"Upon arrival at Delhi airport and railway station, meet Tour My India (TMI) representatives who will transfer you to your private vehicle that will take you to Delhi. Upon arrival in Jaipur, you will be transferred to hotel. Rest of the day will be free for leisure. Later, return to the hotel for candle light dinner. Overnight stay in Jaipur hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1776, 305, 'JAIPUR ( LOCAL SIGHTSEEING)', 'Post breakfast at the Jaipur hotel, go for Jaipur sightseeing tour. Visit City Palace, Jantar Mantar, and Birla Temple. While doing the Jaipur sightseeing tour, you will drive past the Hawa Mahal. Overnight stay at the Jaipur hotel.'),
(1777, 305, 'JAIPUR', '\"After breakfast, visit the Amer Fort, where you will go for an elephant ride. Later, visit Chokhi Dhani, where take part in activities like camel safari, and tonga ride. Live shows like Ghoomer, Potter Dance, Kalbeliya - the Snake Dance, and Bhopa-Bhopi Dance are organized here on daily basis. Overnight stay at the Jaipur hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1778, 305, 'JAIPUR-DELHI', '\"\r\nAfter breakfast, drive back to Delhi to board a flight train or bus for your journey onward\"'),
(1779, 306, 'ARRIVE UDAIPUR', 'Upon arrival at the Udaipur railway station or airport, you will be transferred to the hotel by our representatives. Rest of the day will be free for leisure. Overnight stay in Udaipur hotel.'),
(1780, 306, 'UDAIPUR', 'After breakfast at the hotel, hop in the private cab, which will take you to City Palace, Sajjangarh Palace and various other attractions of Udaipur. The evening will be free for leisure. A candlelight dinner will be arranged for you against the backdrop of the lake. Overnight stay in Udaipur hotel.'),
(1781, 306, 'UDAIPUR-CHITTORGARH-UDAIPUR (120 KILOMETERS ONE WAY 02 HOURS DRIVE)', '\"After an early breakfast, drive to Chittorgarh, which is 2 hours away from Udaipur. When in Chittorgarh, visit all the famous attractions like Chittorgarh Fort, Meera Temple, Kalika Mata Temple and Ratan Singh Palace. After exploring all the attraction, go back to the hotel in Udaipur for an overnight stay.\r\n \"'),
(1782, 306, 'UDAIPUR', '\"After breakfast at the Udaipur hotel, visit Fateh Sagar Lake, Rana Pratap Memorial, Sahelion Ki Bari, and Bagore ki Haveli. For the evening, you have two options, either go on ropeway ride for dinner at Ivy view restaurant or explore the city. Overnight stay at the Udaipur hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1783, 306, 'UDAIPUR-RANAKPUR-KUMBHALGARH (90 KILOMETERS / 02 HOURS DRIVE)', 'In the morning, you will drive to Ranakpur, which is famous for its temple dedicated to Tirthankara Adinatha. Later, you will visit Kumbhalgarh fort. The evening will be free for leisure. Overnight stay at the Kumbhalgarh hotel.'),
(1784, 306, 'KUMBHALGARH-UDAIPUR (85 KMS-2 HRS)', 'In the morning, you will visit the Kumbhalgarh Sanctuary. After exploring the city, drive to Udaipur. On arrival in Udaipur, you will be transferred to the hotel and later visit the Vintage & Classic Car Collection Museum. The evening will be free for leisure. Overnight stay in the Udaipur hotel.'),
(1785, 306, 'DEPARTURE UDAIPUR', 'After breakfast, you will be transferred to the railway station or airport for your journey onwards'),
(1786, 307, 'ARRIVE DELHI', 'On arrival in Delhi, you will be met by our representative who will help you with check-in at a hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1787, 307, 'DELHI – SAMODE', '\"Today, after the breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Samode. On arrival at Samode, check-in at a hotel. Evening free to explore Samode Village. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1788, 307, 'SAMODE – JAIPUR – SAMODE', '\"In the morning today, after the breakfast, we shall go for an excursion to Amer Fort. We will ride on Elephant’s back. In the afternoon, we will go for tour of the city. We shall visit City palace, Jantar Mantar (observatory), Palace of Winds and the Birla Temple. In the evening check-in to a hotel. Stay overnight at the hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1789, 307, 'SAMODE – NAGAUR', 'Today, post breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Nagaur. On arrival at Nagaur check-in at a hotel. In the afternoon, we will take a city tour and shall visit Nagaur Fort, Tarkeen Dargah and Jain Temple. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1790, 307, 'NAGAUR – JAISALMER', '\"After the breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Jaisalmer. On arrival, check-in at a hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\nFounded by Prince Jaisal Bhatti, Jaisalmer is a city standing on a ridge of yellowish sandstone, crowned by a fort, which is home to spectacular palaces and several Jain temples. The city is situated on the edge of the Great Thar Desert and is a must visit for those who want experience the charm of desert life and rich culture.\"'),
(1791, 307, 'JAISALMER', 'After the breakfast, we shall go for half day sightseeing tour of Jaisalmer. We will visit the Jaisalmer Fort, which is one of the largest forts in the world. The fort was built in 1156 AD by the Bhati Rajput ruler Rao Jaisal, from where it derives its name. Manak Chowk, Havelis and Gadisar Lake, which is one of the most important tourist attractions in Jaisalmer will also be visited by us. In the afternoon, we shall go for an excursion to Sam Sand Dunes. In the evening, we will take a camel safari and enjoy the sunset at sand dunes. Later, we will drive back to Jaisalmer for an overnight stay.'),
(1792, 307, 'JAISALMER – OSIAN', 'After the breakfast at the hotel, we shall drive to Osian. On arrival, check-in at the camp. Evening Camel safari at Dunes. Dinner and overnight stay at Camp.'),
(1793, 307, 'OSIAN – JODHPUR', '\"Today, we will drive to Jodhpur. On arrival at Jodhpur, check-in at a hotel. The evening will be free for leisure activities. Overnight stay in the hotel.\r\nJodhpur was once the capital of the kingdom of Marwar, which was Rajasthan\'s largest princely state. Jodhpur still thrives on textile and craft business and is a great place to see the Rajputana art and architecture.\"'),
(1794, 307, 'JODHPUR – UDAIPUR', '\"Today, post breakfast, we will go for a half day sightseeing tour of Jodhpur city. We shall visit Mehrangarh Fort, which is one of the largest forts in India. The fort is situated 400ft above the city and is enclosed by imposing thick walls. Another place we shall visit is Jaswant Thada, which is an architectural landmark in the city. It is a white marble memorial that was built by Sardar Singh in 1899 in memory of Maharaja Jaswant Singh II. We shall also visit and the Umaid Bhawan Palace, which is one of the world\'s largest private residences. A part of the palace is now managed by Taj Hotels. The palace is named after Maharaja Umaid Singh and this monument has 347 rooms and serves as the principal residence of the erstwhile Jodhpur royal family.\r\nAfter the visit, we shal drive to Udaipur. On arrival at Udaipur, check-in at a hotel. Overnight stay at the hotel.\"'),
(1795, 307, 'UDAIPUR', '\"In the morning, we will take a boat ride at Lake Pichola. Next, we shall visit City Palace, which is situated beside the Lake Pichola and is built by the Maharana Udai Singh. We will also visit Jagdish Temple, which is a large Hindu temple in the middle of the city. Next, we will visit Saheliyon ki Bari (Gardens of the maids of Honor) and the Museum. In the evening, we will check-in at a hotel for overnight stay.\r\nUdaipur, also known as the \"\"City of Lakes\"\" is one among the most romantic and most beautiful cities in India. It is a lovely place that has blue water lakes, majestic palaces, gardens and temples.\"'),
(1796, 307, 'UDAIPUR – CHITTORGARH – BHAINSRORGARH', 'Post breakfast at the hotel, we shall drive to Bhainsrorgarh. En route, we will visit Chittorgarh Fort. On arrival at Bhainsrorgarh, check-in at a hotel. In the evening, we will visit Badoli Temple and go for Sunset Safari (jeep drive to the tribal village). Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1797, 307, 'BHAINSRORGARH – BUNDI', 'After breakfast, we shall drive to Bundi. On arrival in Bundi, check-in at a hotel. In the afternoon, we will take a tour of Bundi. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1798, 307, 'BUNDI – PUSHKAR', '\"After the breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Pushkar. On arrival at Pushkar check-in at a hotel. In the afternoon, we will visit the temples and Ghats of Pushkar. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\nPushkar is a famous as a Hindu pilgrimage. It houses various sacred temple and is located on the shores of Pushkar Lake and has five main temples along with other small temples. It has almost 52 ghats. The town borders the Thar Desert and is home to one of its kind Brahma Temple.\r\n \"'),
(1799, 307, 'PUSHKAR – DELHI', 'After the breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Delhi. On arrival at Delhi, check-in at a hotel for overnight stay.'),
(1800, 307, 'DELHI DEPARTURE', 'Post breakfast, we shall drop you at the airport to board the flight for onward destination.'),
(1801, 308, 'ARRIVE DELHI', 'On arrival, meet our representative at the airport who will help you with check-in at the hotel. Overnight at the hotel.'),
(1802, 308, 'DELHI', 'In the morning, we shall go for a sightseeing tour of Delhi. We will visit Raj Ghat (the cremation site of Mahatma Gandhi) and Shanti Vana (the cremation site of Jawaharlal Nehru), Jama Masjid and drive past the Red Fort and the Chandni Chowk. In the afternoon visit Qutub Minar (built by Qutub-ud-Din Aibek in 1199), Humayun\'s Tomb, India Gate (War Memorial Arch) and Lakshminarayan Temple (a modern Hindu Temple). Also drive past President\'s House, Parliament House, Government Secretariat Buildings and Connaught Place shopping centre. Stay overnight at the hotel.'),
(1803, 308, 'DELHI -AGRA', '\" After the breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Agra. On arrival at Agra, check-in at a hotel. Afternoon visit Taj Mahal and Agra Fort. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\nTaj Mahal is one of the Seven Wonders of the world and surely the most beautiful epitome of love. It is said that over 20,000 men laboured for about 17 years to build this memorial to Shah Jahan\'s beloved wife. It\'s a wealth of white marble and semi-precious stones that truly deserves visiting at least once in a lifetime.\r\n \"'),
(1804, 308, 'AGRA – RANTHAMBORE', 'After the breakfast, we shall drive to Ranthambore. En route , we would visit Fatehpur Sikri, which is definitely a masterpiece in sandstone with stunning elegance of its palaces and courts. Each important edifice here represents a type by itself. Notable among them is the Diwan-e-Khas; Panch Mahal, the Tomb of Salim Chishti, and the Buland Darwaza. After the visit, we will continue our drive to Ranthambore. On arrival, check-in to a hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1805, 308, 'RANTHAMBORE', 'Today, we will enter twice into the National Park on an open jeep for exploration. Overnight stay at wildlife resort.'),
(1806, 308, 'RANTHAMBORE – BUNDI', '\"Post breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Bundi. On arrival at Bundi, we shall check-in at a hotel. In the afternoon, we shall go for a city tour of Bundi. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1807, 308, 'BUNDI – UDAIPUR', '\"Today, after the breakfast, we will drive to Udaipur. On arrival at Udaipur, check-in at a hotel for a night stay.\r\nUdaipur is situated 1900ft above the sea level in the beautiful Aravalli Hills. This ‘City of Lakes’ was founded by Maharaja Udai Singh in 1559 AD and is thus named after him. One of the most romantic places in Rajasthan, Udaipur is known for its marble palaces, beautifully laid out gardens and the lakes.\"'),
(1808, 308, 'UDAIPUR', 'After the breakfast, we shall go for a city tour of Udaipur. We will visit City Palace, Jagdish Temple, Museum, Saheliyon ki Bari (Gardens of the maids of Honor) and in the evening, we shall take a boat ride at Lake Pichola. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1809, 308, 'UDAIPUR – RANAKPUR', '\"Today, post breakfast, we will drive to Ranakpur. On arrival at Ranakpur, check-in at a hotel. In the afternoon, we shall go for a tour of Ranakpur Jain Temple. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1810, 308, 'RANAKPUR – ROHETGARH', '\"Post breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Rohetgarh today. On arrival at Rohetgarh, check-in at a hotel.\r\nRohet is also known as \'Evergreen Oasis in the Desert\'. Rohetgarh Fort used to be the ancestral home of Thakur Dalpat Singh I. This fort has now been converted in to a fine Heritage hotel. Overnight stay at Rohetgarh Fort.\"'),
(1811, 308, 'ROHETGARH – JODHPUR', 'Today after the breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Jodhpur. On arrival at Jodhpur, check-in at a hotel. In the afternoon, we shall proceed for city tour of Jodhpur. We will visit Mehrangarh Fort, Jaswant Thada and Ummaid Bhawan Palace. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1812, 308, 'JODHPUR – JAIPUR', '\"After the breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Jaipur. On arrival at Jaipur, check-in at a hotel. Evening will be kept free for self-activities. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\nFounded by Maharaja Sawai Jai Singh in 1728 A.D, Jaipur is also called Pink City because most houses in this city are pink coloured. The city is surrounded by thick walls and have eight gates. Ajmeri Gate and the Sanganeri Gate in the south, Chandpole Gate in the west and the Ghat Darwaza in the east are some of the main gates of Jaipur. The city is known for its massive forts and Rajputana architecture.\"'),
(1813, 308, 'JAIPUR', 'After the breakfast, we will go for an excursion to Amer Fort. We shall take a ride on Elephant’s back. In the afternoon, we shall go for visiting City Palace, the Jantar Mantar (observatory), the Palace of Winds and the Birla temple. In the evening check-in to a hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1814, 308, 'JAIPUR – DELHI', 'Today, after the breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Delhi. On arrival, check-in at a hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1815, 308, 'DELHI DEPARTURE', 'In the morning today, we will have breakfast at the hotel and then you will be dropped at the airport to board the flight for onward destination.');
INSERT INTO `tour_daywise` (`itinerydata_id`, `tour_id`, `itinerydata_title`, `itinerydata_description`) VALUES
(1816, 309, 'ARRIVE DELHI', '\"On arrival at the airport, you will be met by our representative who will assist you to check-in at the hotel for an overnight stay.\r\n \"'),
(1817, 309, 'DELHI', 'In the morning, we will take you for sightseeing tour of Delhi. We shall visit Raj Ghat (the cremation site of Mahatma Gandhi) and Shanti Vana (the cremation site of Jawaharlal Nehru), Jama Masjid and drive past the Red Fort and the Chandni Chowk. In the afternoon, we will visit Qutub Minar (built by Qutub-ud-Din Aibek in 1199), Humayun\'s Tomb, India Gate (War Memorial Arch) and Lakshmi Narayan Temple (a modern Hindu Temple). Also, we will drive past President\'s House, Parliament House, Government Secretariat Buildings and Connaught Place shopping centre. Overnight stay in the hotel.'),
(1818, 309, 'DELHI -AGRA', '\"Post breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Agra. On arrival, check-in at a hotel. In the afternoon, we will visit Taj Mahal and Agra Fort. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\nTaj Mahal is one of the Seven Wonders of the World and is indeed the most popular monument to see in India. It is believed 20,000 men laboured for over 17 years to build this memorial to Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan\'s beloved wife, Mumtaz. The carvings on the Taj Mahal is worth appreciating. The view of River Yamuna from the platform of Taj is also quite beautiful. Overnight stay in the hotel.\"'),
(1819, 309, 'AGRA – JAIPUR', 'Today after the breakfast proceed, we will head out for Jaipur. Enroute, we will stop for the sightseeing of Fatehpur Sikri, which is reckoned be a masterpiece in sandstone. The fort is adorned with elegant palaces and courts. Each important edifice here represents a type by itself. Notable among them is the Diwan-e-Khas; Panch Mahal, the Tomb of Salim Chishti, and the Buland Darwaza. After the sightseeing, we will continue our drive to Jaipur. On arrival, check-in at the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1820, 309, 'JAIPUR', '\"Today, we will go for an excursion to Amer Fort right after the breakfast at the hotel. We shall take an elephant ride to and back to the fort. In the afternoon, we will take a city tour and shall visit City palace, Jantar Mantar (observatory), the Palace of Winds and the Birla Temple. In the evening, return to the hotel for overnight stay.\r\nThe capital city of Rajasthan, Jaipur is said to have been founded by Maharaja Sawai Jai Singh in 1728 A.D. It is also called the Pink City because most houses in the old Jaipur city were once coloured pink . The city is surrounded by thick walls 20 feet high and 9 feet wide and eight towering gates. Forts and temples dot the hills found in the city.\"'),
(1821, 309, 'JAIPUR – DEOGARH', '\"Post breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Deogarh. On arrival at Deogarh, check-in at a hotel. In the afternoon, we shall visit the surrounding villages and learn about lifestyle of the village people . Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\nAt Deogarh village, the most prominent building to look at is the Deogarh Mahal. It is where the royal family lives. The palace is magnificent and is a fitting stronghold for one of the sixteen \"\"umraos\"\" - the most senior feudal barons attending on the Maharana of Udaipur.\"'),
(1822, 309, 'DEOGARH – UDAIPUR', '\"Today after having breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Udaipur. On arrival, check-in at a hotel for an overnight stay.\r\nUdaipur is situated 1900ft above the sea level in the Aravalli Hills and is also known as the City of Lakes This beautiful city was founded by Maharaja Udai Singh in 1559 AD and thus it is named after him. Udaipur is considered as one of the most romantic cities in Rajasthan, and therefore is an ideal honeymoon and wedding destination. The marble palaces, beautifully laid out gardens and the large lakes make Udaipur one of the most visited places in the state.\"'),
(1823, 309, 'UDAIPUR', 'After the breakfast, we shall go for city tour. We will visit City Palace, Jagdish Temple, Museum and Saheliyon ki Bari (Gardens of the maids of Honor). In the evening, we shall go for a boat ride at Lake Pichola. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1824, 309, 'UDAIPUR – CHITTORGARH – UDAIPUR', 'Today, after having breakfast at the hotel, we will proceed go for Chittorgarh Fort excursion. Later return back to Udaipur for an overnight stay.'),
(1825, 309, 'UDAIPUR – MOUNT ABU', 'After breakfast at the hotel today, we shall drive to Mount Abu, which is located at a height of 1200mt and is the only hill station in Rajasthan. On arrival at Mount Abu, check-in at a hotel. Rest of the day will be free for leisure or for local market visit. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1826, 309, 'MOUNT ABU', '\"Post breakfast today, we will visit the famed Dilwara Jain Temple, Brahmin Kumari Ashram and Nakki Lake. An overnight stay at the hotel.\r\nDilwara Temple is a group of Jain temples. Among all the temples, the two temples – Vimal Vasahi and Tejpal Temple are the most famous ones. Vimal Vasahi is the oldest temple and is devoted to Adinath, the first Tirthankar. The \'Tejpal Temple\' is devoted to Neminath, the 22nd Tirthankar.\r\nNakki Lake is located in the heart of Mount Abu. According to A legend, the lake was scooped out by gods by using nails and therefore named as \"\"Nakki\"\". The strange rock formations along the lake are a major attractions here.\"'),
(1827, 309, 'MOUNT ABU – UDAIPUR – DELHI', 'Today, after the breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Udaipur. On arrival, we will take you to the airport to board the flight to Delhi. On arrival, you will be met by our representative who will help you check-in to the hotel for a nightstay.'),
(1828, 309, 'DELHI DEPARTURE', 'Post breakfast at the hotel, we will drop you at the airport to board the flight for your onward journey.'),
(1829, 310, 'ARRIVE DELHI', 'On arrival at the airport, you will be met by our representative who will assist you to check-in at the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1830, 310, 'DELHI', '\"After the breakfast, we shall go for full day city tour of Old and New Delhi. We will visit Shanti Vana (the cremation sites of Jawaharlal Nehru, Raj Ghat (the cremation sites of Mahatma Gandhi), Jama Masjid and drive past Red Fort and Chandni Chowk.\r\nIn the afternoon we will visit India Gate (War Memorial Arch), Qutub Minar (built by Qutub-ud-Din Aibek in 1199), Humayun\'s Tomb) and drive past President\'s House, Parliament House, Connaught Place shopping centre and Akshardham temple (a modern Hindu Temple). Overnight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1831, 310, 'DELHI -AGRA', '\"After the breakfast today, we will drive to Agra, en route Sikandra, where will stop for photography. On arrival at Agra, check-in at a hotel.\r\nLater we shall visit the Agra Fort which has the Pearl Mosque, Diwan-e-am (the hall of public audience) and Diwan-e-Khas (the hall of private audience). Stay overnight at the hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1832, 310, 'AGRA – SAMODE', '\"Today post breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Samode. On arrival at Samode, we shall check-in at the hotel. Evening free to explore Samode Village. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1833, 310, 'SAMODE – JAIPUR – SAMODE', 'Post breakfast, we shall go for an excursion to Amer Fort. We will ride Elephants to the fort and back. In the afternoon, we will take tour of the city to places like City palace, Jantar Mantar (observatory), Palace of Winds and the Birla Temple. In the evening, return back to Samode and check-in to the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1834, 310, 'SAMODE – NAGAUR', 'After the breakfast at the hotel, we will drive to Nagaur. On arrival at Nagaur check-in at a hotel. In the afternoon, we shall go for a city tour of Nagaur and will visit Nagaur Fort, Tarkeen Dargah and Jain Temple. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1835, 310, 'NAGAUR- JAISALMER', '\"Today, after the breakfast at the hotel, we will head out for Jaisalmer. On arrival at Jaisalmer, check-in at a hotel for a night stay.\r\nJaisalmer is reckoned to have been founded by Prince Jaisal Bhatti. The town stands on a mound of yellow sandstone and is crowned by a fort, which contains palaces and several ornate Jain temples. These fortresses of Jaisalmer also known as Havelis of Jaisalmer are the reflection of rich Rajput architecture. On either side of the narrow lanes of Jaisalmer are the sandstone havelis, adorned with stone carvings, screen windows, delicate pavilions and balconies.\"'),
(1836, 310, 'JAISALMER', 'Post breakfast today, we shall go for half day sightseeing tour of Jaisalmer. We will visit Jaisalmer Fort, which is one of the largest forts in the world. It was built in 1156 AD by Rao Jaisal. We will also visit Manak Chowk, Havelis and Gadisar Lake, which is one of the most important tourist attractions in Jaisalmer. The charm of this lake lies in the fact that it was the only source of water for the Jaisalmer city in the olden days. We shall also visit Sam Sand Dunes and in the evening will take a camel safari and enjoy the sunset here. Later drive back to Jaisalmer. Stay overnight at the hotel.'),
(1837, 310, 'JAISALMER – JODHPUR', '\"Today, after having breakfast in the hotel, we will head out to Jodhpur. On arrival at Jodhpur, check-in at the hotel. Evening will be free for leisure activities. Stay overnight at the hotel.\r\nJodhpur is believed to be once the capital of the mighty kingdom of Marwar, Rajasthan\'s largest princely state. Presently Jodhpur is the second largest city in the state of Rajasthan and is known for its thriving textile and craft business.\"'),
(1838, 310, 'JODHPUR – UDAIPUR', 'In the morning today, after having breakfast, we will go for a half day sightseeing tour of Jodhpur city. We shall visit Mehrangarh Fort, which is one of the largest forts in India and is situated 400ft high on a hillock. We will also visit Jaswant Thada, which is an architectural landmark made of white marble in memory of Maharaja Jaswant Singh II. Another attraction would be Umaid Bhawan Palace, which is one of the world\'s largest private residences a part which has been converted in to heritage hotel that is managed by Taj Hotels. Named after Maharaja Umaid Singh, grandfather of the present owners of the palace, this monument cum hotel has 347 rooms and serves as the principal residence of the erstwhile Jodhpur royal family. After Umaid Bhawan, we will drive to Udaipur. On arrival, check-in at a hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1839, 310, 'UDAIPUR', '\"In the morning, we will go for a boat ride at Lake Pichola. Next, we shall visit City Palace, which is believed to have been built by the Maharana Udai Singh as the capital of the Sisodia Rajput clan in 1559. Another places will be Jagdish Temple, which is a large Hindu temple in the centre of Udaipur city. The temple was originally called the temple of Jagannath Rai but is now called Jagdish-Ji. We will also visit Saheliyon ki Bari (Gardens of the maids of Honor) and Museum. In the evening, we will return to the hotel for an overnight stay.\r\nUdaipur is also called the \"\"City of Lakes\"\". The city is considered one of the most romantic and beautiful places in India. It is dotted with blue water lakes, lush hills of the Aravalis and many beautiful havelis. Everything right from lakes, gardens, temples, lanes and palaces vaunt the royal past of this lovely city.\r\n \"'),
(1840, 310, 'UDAIPUR – DELHI', 'Post breakfast at the hotel, you will be assisted to the airport to board a flight to Delhi. Upon arrival at Delhi, our representative will meet you and assist you to check-in at a hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1841, 310, 'DELHI DEPARTURE', 'After the breakfast at the hotel, we will drop you to the airport to boar flight for onward destination.'),
(1842, 311, 'ARRIVE DELHI', 'Upon arrival in Delhi, meet or representatives who will transfer you to the hotel. Overnight stay at the Delhi hotel.'),
(1843, 311, 'DELHI', 'Today in the morning, you will go for city sightseeing tour, which includes places like Raj Ghat (the cremation sites of Mahatma Gandhi), Shanti Vana (the cremation sites of Jawaharlal Nehru) and Jama Masjid. Drive past Red Fort and Chandni Chowk. In the afternoon, visit Qutub Minar (built by Qutub-ud-Din Aibek in 1199), Humayun\'s Tomb, India Gate (War Memorial Arch) and Lakshminarayan Temple (a modern Hindu Temple). While doing the city tour, you will pass by some famous attractions like President\'s House, Parliament House, Government Secretariat Buildings and Connaught Place.'),
(1844, 311, 'DELHI - AGRA (203 KILOMETERS; 4 HOURS)', 'Embark on a drive to Agra. During the journey, enjoy a short stopover at Sikandra Fort. Upon arrival in Agra, you will be transferred to hotel. After a short nap, get ready to visit Agra Fort. Rest of the evening will be free for leisure. Overnight stay at the Agra hotel.'),
(1845, 311, 'AGRA - JAIPUR (233 KILOMETERS, 5 HOURS)', 'Start your day with a beautiful smile as today you will be beholding the beauty of iconic Taj Mahal. After a brief visit to Taj Mahal, go back to the hotel, and get ready for the drive to Jaipur, which is approximately 240 kilometers from Agra. During your journey, you will enjoy a short stopover at Fatehpur Sikri. Later, continue your drive to Jaipur. Upon arrival in Jaipur, check in the hotel for overnight stay.'),
(1846, 311, 'JAIPUR', 'On the fifth day, you will be going for Jaipur sightseeing tour. You will visit the Amber Fort in the morning. In the afternoon, visit City Palace, Ram Niwas Garden, Birla Temple and Jantar Mantar. You will also pass through Hawa Mahal and bazaars. Overnight stay at the Jaipur hotel.'),
(1847, 311, 'JAIPUR - DELHI (260 KILOMETERS; 6 HOURS)', 'Check out from the Jaipur hotel and drive to Delhi. During the journey, you will stop for lunch. Overnight stay at the Delhi hotel.'),
(1848, 311, 'DELHI – GOA (BY FLIGHT)', '\"After breakfast, you will be transferred to the airport to board a flight for Goa. Upon arrival in Goa, you will be transferred to a hotel for overnight stay.\r\n\r\n \"'),
(1849, 311, 'GOA', 'After breakfast at the hotel, you\'re free to explore Goa on your own. Overnight stay at the Goa hotel.'),
(1850, 311, 'GOA', 'Today as well, you will explore Goa on your own. Overnight stay will be provided in the hotel.'),
(1851, 311, 'GOA', 'On the 10th day as well, you will be exploring Goa at your own pace. Overnight stay in the Goa hotel.'),
(1852, 311, 'GOA – DELHI (BY FLIGHT)', 'Post breakfast at the Goa hotel, board a flight for Delhi. Overnight stay at the Delhi hotel.'),
(1853, 311, 'TRANSFER TO AIRPORT', 'You can start your day a little late. In the evening, you will be transferred to airport or railway station for your journey onwards.'),
(1854, 312, 'ARRIVE DELHI', 'On arrival at Delhi our representative meets you at the airport and assists you till your check in process at the hotel. Stay overnight at the hotel.'),
(1855, 312, 'DELHI - UDAIPUR (BY FLIGHT)', 'Morning free for your own activity. Afternoon transfer to Airport for Udaipur. Meet on arrival at Udaipur Airport and transfer to hotel. Rest of the day free for shopping around the local market. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1856, 312, 'UDAIPUR', '\"In the morning take a boat ride at Lake Pichola. Next visit City Palace- It was built by the Maharana Udai Singh as the capital of the Sisodia Rajput clan in 1559. Jagdish Temple - Jagdish Temple is a large Hindu temple in the middle of Udaipur in Rajasthan. A big tourist attraction, the temple was originally called the temple of Jagannath Rai but is now called Jagdish-Ji, Saheliyon ki Bari (Gardens of the maids of Honor) and Museum. Evening transfer to the hotel. Stay overnight at the hotel.\r\nUdaipur the \"\"City of Lakes\"\" is one among the most romantic and most beautiful city of India. It is a lovely land around the blue water lakes, edge of the lush hills of the Aravalis. A vision in white soaked in romance and beauty, Udaipur city of Rajasthan state is a fascinating blend of sights, sounds and experiences - an inspiration for the imagination of the painters, poets and writers. Udaipur\'s lakes, gardens, temples and narrow lanes scattered with stalls, carry the flavor of heroic past, epitomizing valor and chivalry.\"'),
(1857, 312, 'UDAIPUR - JODHPUR', '\"After breakfast drive to Jodhpur. On arrival at Jodhpur check-in at hotel. Evening free for shopping around the local market. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\nJodhpur is known as the \"\"Sun City\"\" for the bright, sunny weather it enjoys round the year. It is also referred to as the \"\"Blue City\"\" due to the bright blue-painted houses around the Mehrangarh Fort. The old city circles and the fort is bounded by a wall with several gates. Whereas, the city has expanded very much outside the wall over the past several decades.\"'),
(1858, 312, 'JODHPUR - JAISALMER', '\"After breakfast go for a half day sightseeing tour of Jodhpur city. Visit the Mehrangarh Fort - Mehrangarh Fort, located in Jodhpur, Rajasthan, is one of the largest forts in India. The fort is situated 400 feet above the city and is enclosed by imposing thick walls, The Jaswant Thada - The Jaswant Thada is an architectural landmark located in Jodhpur. It is a white marble memorial built by Sardar Singh in 1899 in memory of Maharaja Jaswant Singh II and the Umaid Bhawan Palace - Umaid Bhawan Palace is one of the world\'s largest private residences. A part of the palace is managed by Taj Hotels. Named after Maharaja Umaid Singh, grandfather of the present owners of the palace, this monument has 347 rooms and serves as the principal residence of the erstwhile Jodhpur royal family.\r\nAfternoon drive to Jaisalmer, On arrival check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1859, 312, 'JAISALMER', '\"After breakfast go for full day for sightseeing tour of Jaisalmer. Visit the Jaisalmer Fort - Jaisalmer Fort is one of the largest forts in the world. It is situated in Jaisalmer city in the Indian state of Rajasthan. It was built in 1156 AD by the Bhati Rajput ruler Rao Jaisal, from where it derives its name, Manak Chowk, Havelis, Gadisar Lake - Gadisar Lake is one of the most important tourist attractions in Jaisalmer, Rajasthan, Its charm lies in the fact that it was the only source of water for the Jaisalmer city in the olden days, and the colorful markets. In the afternoon go for an excursion to Sam Sand Dunes. In the evening take a camel safari and enjoy the sunset at sand dunes. Later drive back to Jaisalmer. Stay overnight at the hotel.\r\nJaisalmer was founded by Prince Jaisal Bhatti. The town stands on a ridge of yellowish sandstone, crowned by a fort, which contains the palace and several ornate Jain temples. Centuries ago Jaisalmer\'s strategic position on the camel train routes brought its locals enormous wealth which they spent in building intricately carved palaces and temples in golden-yellow sandstone. These fortresses of Jaisalmer also known as Havelis of Jaisalmer are like a mirage in the barren Thar Desert. On either side of the narrow lanes of Jaisalmer are the sandstone havelis, made up with stone carvings, screen windows, delicate pavilions and balconies.\"'),
(1860, 312, 'JAISALMER - BIKANER', '\"After having breakfast drive to Bikaner. On arrival check-in at hotel. Evening free to explore city by your own. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\nBikaner founded in 1488, the desert city of Bikaner is located in north-western Rajasthan. The city was founded by Rao Bika with the help of Nehra Jats. Bikaner was well protected from its enemies by the harsh deserts. It was also a major trade centre as it was located on the ancient caravan route which linked Central Asia and North India with Gujarat seaports.\"'),
(1861, 312, 'BIKANER - NAWALGARH', '\"After breakfast go for half day tour of Bikaner, visiting the Bikaner Fort (Junagarh Fort)- The fort was originally called Chintamani and was renamed Junagarh or \"\"Old Fort\"\" in the early 20th century when the ruling family moved to Lalgarh Palace outside the fort limits, The Lalgarh Palace - The palace was built between 1902 and 1926 according to Rajput, Mughal and European architectural styles and the Deshnoke Temple (Karni Mata Temple) - Karni Mata, considered as an incarnation of Goddess Durga lived here in the fourteenth century and performed many miracles.\r\nAfternoon drive to Nawalgarh, on arrival check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1862, 312, 'NAWALGARH - JAIPUR', 'After breakfast take a walking sightseeing tour of Nawalgarh Havelis, Poddar Haveli, Aath Haveli, Morarka Haveli and Bala Qila. Later drive to Jaipur. On arrival check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1863, 312, 'JAIPUR', 'After breakfast visit the Amber Fort ascend the fort on an Elephant back- Amer, originally, was the capital of the state before Jaipur. It is an old fort, built in 1592 by Raja Man Singh, Maharaja\'s City Palace - City Palace, Jaipur, which includes the Chandra Mahal and Mubarak Mahal palaces and other buildings, is a palace complex in Jaipur, The Observatory (Jantar Mantar)- The Jantar Mantar is a collection of architectural astronomical instruments, built by Sawai Jai Singh who was a Mughal Commander and served Emperor Aurangzeb and later Mughals. Drive past the Hawa Mahal (Palace of Winds)- Its unique five-storey exterior is also akin to the honeycomb of the beehive with its 953 small windows called jharokhas that are decorated with intricate latticework. Evening transfer to hotel. Stay overnight at hotel.'),
(1864, 312, 'JAIPUR - DELHI DEPART', 'After breakfast drive back to Delhi. On arrival Delhi drop you at airport to connect flight for onward destination.'),
(1865, 313, 'ARRIVE DELHI', 'Upon arrival in Delhi, meet our representatives who will transfer you to a hotel. Overnight stay at the Delhi hotel.'),
(1866, 313, 'DELHI', '\"Today, you will be experiencing the madness, and magic of Delhi, the capital city of India. You will start your day visiting the most quaint places of Delhi - Raj Ghat (the cremation sites of Mahatma Gandhi), Shanti Vana (the cremation sites of Jawaharlal Nehru) and Jama Masjid. Since all these places are located in old Delhi, during the journey, you will pass by the Red Fort and Chandni Chowk. In the afternoon, you will be exploring the South and Central Delhi, In the south Delhi, you will Qutub Minar and later proceed to Humayun\'s Tomb, India Gate (War Memorial Arch) and Lakshminarayan Temple (a modern Hindu Temple). Enroute, catch glimpses of President\'s House, Parliament House, Government Secretariat Buildings and Connaught Place. Overnight stay at the Delhi hotel.\r\n \"'),
(1867, 313, 'DELHI - JAIPUR', 'Early morning, check out from the Delhi hotel and catch Ajmer Shatabdi Express ( departure time: 06:15 AM). Upon arrival at the Jaipur airport, meet TMI (Tour My India) representatives who will transfer you to the hotel. In the afternoon, you will be visiting City Palace, Jantar Mantar, Birla Mansir, and Ram Niwas Garden. The evening will be free for leisure;; you can visit Bazar for shopping and try some delicious Rajasthani cuisine. Overnight stay at the Jaipur hotel.'),
(1868, 313, 'JAIPUR', 'On the fourth day; early morning visit the Amber Fort, where you will be enjoying elephant safari as well. In the evening, you will be visiting colorful bazaars. Overnight stay at the Jaipur hotel.'),
(1869, 313, 'JAIPUR - FATEHPUR SIKHRI - AGRA (232 KILOMETERS / 5 HOURS)', 'Wake up little early in the morning; get ready; check out from the Jaipur hotel and drive to Agra. During the journey, enjoy a short stopover at the Fatehpur Sikhri. Later, continue your drive to Agra, where you will be transferred to a hotel for overnight stay.'),
(1870, 313, 'AGRA - DELHI / OUT', 'Today, you will be visiting Agra Fort, Taj Mahal, and Itmad-ud-Daulah. In the evening, you will be transferred to the railway station to board Gatiman Express (departure time: 05:50 PM). When in Delhi, board flight or train for your journey onwards.'),
(1871, 314, 'MUNNAR SIGHTSEEING', '\"Post breakfast, we shall visit Eravikulam National Park (Raja Malai), Mattupetty Dam, Tea Estates, Eco Point, Spice Plantation, Rose Garden, Photo Point, Honey Bee Tree, Tea Museum, Blossom Park, Kundale Dam and Top Station. We shall also go for boat riding in the lake. Overnight stay in the hotel in Munnar.\r\n\"'),
(1872, 314, 'MUNNAR - THEKKADY/PERIYAR (150KM/3.5HRS)', '\"Today, we shall leave for Thekkady. Upon reaching, check-in at a hotel. After some rest, we will go for sightseeing tour of Periyar National Park and Mullaperiyar Dam. We shall also visit spice plantations where you will be allowed to shop for exotic spices. Night stay in the hotel at Thekkady\r\n \"'),
(1873, 314, 'THEKKADY SIGHTSEEING', 'Today we will go for boating and to watch Kerala’s martial art as well its traditional dance, Kathakali. Also, you will have the opportunity to enjoy elephant ride, bamboo rafting, jeep safari, nature walk, jungle patrol as well as trekking. Overnight stay in the hotel in Thekkady'),
(1874, 314, 'THEKKADY - ALLEPPEY/ KUMARAKOM RESORT (150KMS/2.5HRS)', '\"We shall leave for Alleppey/Kumarakom. We will then visit Alleppey Beach and will enjoy the beautiful sunset view in the evening. We will also enjoy shopping here. Overnight stay in the resort.\r\n\"'),
(1875, 314, 'ALLEPPEY HOUSEBOAT', '\"We will today move to the houseboat in Alleppey. Here you will have the opportunity to spend the day in the houseboat enjoying comfortable stay and pristine scenery of the backwaters. Overnight stay in the houseboat.\r\n \"'),
(1876, 314, 'ALLEPPEY TO KANYAKUMARI (250KM/5.5HRS)', '\"Early in the morning, we shall drive to Kanyakumari. Upon arrival, check-in at a hotel. Later, we shall go for sightseeing tour of Kanyakumari and will visit Kanyakumari Beach, Sangam (Confluence of Indian Ocean, Bay of Bengal and Arabian Sea) and Vivekananda Rock. In the evening, we will watch the beautiful sunset. Overnight stay in the hotel in Kanyakumari.\r\n\"'),
(1877, 314, 'KANYAKUMARI - KOVALAM (90KMS/2HRS)', '\"We shall wake up early to visit the sunrise in Kanyakumari and after the breakfast, we shall leave for Kovalam. On arrival, check-in at a hotel. Later we shall visit the beautiful golden beaches of Kovalam like Lighthouse Beach, Howah Beach and Ashoka Beach. Overnight stay in the hotel in Kovalam.\r\n \"'),
(1878, 314, 'TRIVANDRUM/KOVALAM (14KMS/0.5HR)', '\"Post breakfast, we shall leave for Trivandrum and then go for sightseeing of Sree Padmanabha Swami Temple, Kuthiramalika Palace Museum, The Napier Museum, Sree Chithra Art Gallery, Zoological Park, Science & Technology Museum, Kanakakunnu Palace, Planetarium. After Trivandrum sightseeing tour, we shall return to Kovalam for spending the night.\r\n\"'),
(1879, 314, 'KOVALAM - COCHIN (240KMS/5.5HRS) OR KOVALAM - TRIVANDRUM (14KMS/0.5HR)', 'KOVALAM - COCHIN (240KMS/5.5HRS) OR KOVALAM - TRIVANDRUM (14KMS/0.5HR)'),
(1880, 314, 'KOVALAM - COCHIN (240KMS/5.5HRS) OR KOVALAM - TRIVANDRUM (14KMS/0.5HR)', 'You have two options for departure day. One, you will be driven to Cochin, where you can spend a day sightseeing places like Fort Cochin, Navy Museum, St. Francis Church, Chinese Fishing Nets, Santa Claus Basilica, Mattanchery Palace, Jewish Synagogue, Marine Drive, Marine Walkway and Tripunitura Hill Palace. You will also be able to enjoy boating in Trivandrum. Option two would be to depart for Trivandrum, where you can indulge in more sightseeing and later catch your train/flight from here.'),
(1881, 314, 'MUNNAR SIGHTSEEING', '\"Post breakfast, we shall visit Eravikulam National Park (Raja Malai), Mattupetty Dam, Tea Estates, Eco Point, Spice Plantation, Rose Garden, Photo Point, Honey Bee Tree, Tea Museum, Blossom Park, Kundale Dam and Top Station. We shall also go for boat riding in the lake. Overnight stay in the hotel in Munnar.\r\n\"'),
(1882, 314, 'MUNNAR - THEKKADY/PERIYAR (150KM/3.5HRS)', '\"Today, we shall leave for Thekkady. Upon reaching, check-in at a hotel. After some rest, we will go for sightseeing tour of Periyar National Park and Mullaperiyar Dam. We shall also visit spice plantations where you will be allowed to shop for exotic spices. Night stay in the hotel at Thekkady\r\n \"'),
(1883, 314, 'THEKKADY SIGHTSEEING', 'Today we will go for boating and to watch Kerala’s martial art as well its traditional dance, Kathakali. Also, you will have the opportunity to enjoy elephant ride, bamboo rafting, jeep safari, nature walk, jungle patrol as well as trekking. Overnight stay in the hotel in Thekkady'),
(1884, 314, 'THEKKADY - ALLEPPEY/ KUMARAKOM RESORT (150KMS/2.5HRS)', '\"We shall leave for Alleppey/Kumarakom. We will then visit Alleppey Beach and will enjoy the beautiful sunset view in the evening. We will also enjoy shopping here. Overnight stay in the resort.\r\n\"'),
(1885, 314, 'ALLEPPEY HOUSEBOAT', '\"We will today move to the houseboat in Alleppey. Here you will have the opportunity to spend the day in the houseboat enjoying comfortable stay and pristine scenery of the backwaters. Overnight stay in the houseboat.\r\n \"'),
(1886, 314, 'ALLEPPEY TO KANYAKUMARI (250KM/5.5HRS)', '\"Early in the morning, we shall drive to Kanyakumari. Upon arrival, check-in at a hotel. Later, we shall go for sightseeing tour of Kanyakumari and will visit Kanyakumari Beach, Sangam (Confluence of Indian Ocean, Bay of Bengal and Arabian Sea) and Vivekananda Rock. In the evening, we will watch the beautiful sunset. Overnight stay in the hotel in Kanyakumari.\r\n\"'),
(1887, 314, 'KANYAKUMARI - KOVALAM (90KMS/2HRS)', '\"We shall wake up early to visit the sunrise in Kanyakumari and after the breakfast, we shall leave for Kovalam. On arrival, check-in at a hotel. Later we shall visit the beautiful golden beaches of Kovalam like Lighthouse Beach, Howah Beach and Ashoka Beach. Overnight stay in the hotel in Kovalam.\r\n \"'),
(1888, 314, 'TRIVANDRUM/KOVALAM (14KMS/0.5HR)', '\"Post breakfast, we shall leave for Trivandrum and then go for sightseeing of Sree Padmanabha Swami Temple, Kuthiramalika Palace Museum, The Napier Museum, Sree Chithra Art Gallery, Zoological Park, Science & Technology Museum, Kanakakunnu Palace, Planetarium. After Trivandrum sightseeing tour, we shall return to Kovalam for spending the night.\r\n\"'),
(1889, 314, 'KOVALAM - COCHIN (240KMS/5.5HRS) OR KOVALAM - TRIVANDRUM (14KMS/0.5HR)', 'KOVALAM - COCHIN (240KMS/5.5HRS) OR KOVALAM - TRIVANDRUM (14KMS/0.5HR)'),
(1890, 314, 'KOVALAM - COCHIN (240KMS/5.5HRS) OR KOVALAM - TRIVANDRUM (14KMS/0.5HR)', 'You have two options for departure day. One, you will be driven to Cochin, where you can spend a day sightseeing places like Fort Cochin, Navy Museum, St. Francis Church, Chinese Fishing Nets, Santa Claus Basilica, Mattanchery Palace, Jewish Synagogue, Marine Drive, Marine Walkway and Tripunitura Hill Palace. You will also be able to enjoy boating in Trivandrum. Option two would be to depart for Trivandrum, where you can indulge in more sightseeing and later catch your train/flight from here.'),
(1891, 316, 'COCHIN-MUNNAR (135KM/4.5HR)', '\"We shall leave from Cochin for Munnar and will reach by afternoon. En route, we shall sight beautiful waterfalls like Cheyyara, Valara and Attakadu along with spice plantation. Also we will stop by Kodanadu Elephant Care Centre. Overnight stay in Munnar.\r\n\"'),
(1892, 316, 'MUNNAR SIGHTSEEING', 'Today, after the breakfast, we shall visit Eravikulam National Park (Raja Malai), Mattupetty Dam, Tea Estates, Eco Point, Spice Plantation, Rose Garden, Photo Point, Honey Bee Tree, Tea Museum, Blossom Park, Kundale Dam and Top Station. We shall also go for boat riding in the lake. Overnight stay in the hotel in Munnar.'),
(1893, 316, 'MUNNAR - THEKKADY/PERIYAR (150KM/3.5HRS)', 'In the morning today, we shall leave for Thekkady. Upon reaching, check-in to a hotel. After some rest, we will go for sightseeing tour of Periyar National Park and Mullaperiyar Dam. We shall also visit spice plantations where you will be allowed to shop for exotic spices. In the evening, we will go for boat cruise and to watch Kerala’s martial art as well its traditional dance form, Kathakali. Also, you will have the opportunity to enjoy elephant ride, bamboo rafting, jeep safari, nature walk, jungle patrol as well as trekking. Overnight stay in Thekkady'),
(1894, 316, 'THEKKADY - ALLEPPEY (150KMS/3.5HRS)', 'We shall leave for Alleppey in the morning after the breakfast. Upon arrival, we will check-in the houseboat. You have the opportunity to spend the day in the houseboat enjoying comfortable stay and pristine scenery of the backwaters. Overnight stay in the houseboat.'),
(1895, 316, 'ALLEPPEY TO KANYAKUMARI (250KM/5.5HRS)', 'Early in the morning, we shall drive to Kanyakumari. Upon arrival, check-in at a hotel. Later, we shall go for sightseeing tour of Kanyakumari and will visit Kanyakumari Beach, Sangam (Confluence of Indian Ocean, Bay of Bengal and Arabian Sea) and Vivekananda Rock. In the evening, we will watch the beautiful sunset. Overnight stay in the hotel in Kanyakumari'),
(1896, 316, 'KANYAKUMARI - KOVALAM (90KMS/2HRS)', 'We shall wake up early to visit the sunrise in Kanyakumari and post breakfast, we shall leave for Kovalam. On arrival, check-in at a hotel. Later we shall visit the beautiful golden beaches of Kovalam like Lighthouse Beach, Howah Beach and Ashoka Beach. Overnight stay in the hotel in Kovalam.'),
(1897, 316, 'TRIVANDRUM/KOVALAM (14KMS/0.5HR)', 'You have the option of staying in Kovalam and explore it or can visit Trivandrum, where you go for sightseeing of Sree Padmanabha Swami Temple, Kuthiramalika Palace Museum, The Napier Museum, Sree Chithra Art Gallery, Zoological Park, Science & Technology Museum, Kanakakunnu Palace, Planetarium. After Trivandrum sightseeing tour, we shall return to Kovalam for spending the night.'),
(1898, 316, 'KOVALAM - COCHIN (240KMS/5.5HRS) OR KOVALAM - TRIVANDRUM (14KMS/0.5HR)', 'You have two options for departure day. One, you will be driven to Cochin, where you can spend a day sightseeing places like Fort Cochin, Navy Museum, St. Francis Church, Chinese Fishing Nets, Santa Claus Basilica, Mattanchery Palace, Jewish Synagogue, Marine Drive, Marine Walkway and Tripunitura Hill Palace. You will also be able to enjoy boating in Trivandrum. Option two would be to depart to Trivandrum, where you can indulge in more sightseeing and later catch your train/flight from here.'),
(1899, 317, 'COCHIN - MUNNAR (130 KILOMETERS - 4 HOURS)', 'Upon arrival at the Cochin International Airport, you will board your coach and then embark on a drive to Munnar. Dinner and overnight stay at the Munnar hotel.'),
(1900, 317, 'MUNNAR', 'Post breakfast at the hotel, visit the Mattupetty Dam to enjoy a high-speed boat ride. After a visit to the dam, go to tea garden; followed by a visit to the Echo Point and the Eravikulam (Rajamalai) National Park. Overnight stay and dinner at the Munnar hotel.'),
(1901, 317, 'MUNNAR - PERIYAR (94 KILOMETERS - 4 HOURS)', 'In the morning after breakfast, drive to Periyar. Rest of the day will be free for leisure, during which you can visit the Kumily Spice Village for shopping. Overnight stay at the Periyar hotel.'),
(1902, 317, 'PERIYAR(THEKKADY)', 'Today, you will visit Periyar National Park. Take part in bamboo rafting, jungle safari, elephant ride, etc. Enjoy get-together with your travel companions. Breakfast, lunch, and dinner will be offered by the company'),
(1903, 317, 'PERIYAR - KUMARAKOM (127 KILOMETERS - 4 HOURS)', 'Today is the day for what you\'ve been waiting. In the morning, you will drive to Kumarakom. On arrival in Kumarakom, check in the hotel and later go for the backwater ride to Kumarakom Bird Sanctuary The main attractions are local birds like the waterfowl, cuckoo, owl, egret, heron and the water duck, as well as the migratory Siberian cranes. Parrots, teal, larks, flycatchers, wood beetle, and other birds are seen here during their respective migratory seasons. Overnight stay and dinner at the hotel.'),
(1904, 317, 'KUMARAKOM - COCHIN (126 KILOMETERS - 2 HOURS)', 'Post breakfast, board your coach that will take you to Cochin. When in Cochin, check in the hotel and later go for a sightseeing tour, which includes places like St. Francis Church, Jewish Synagogue, and Dutch Palace. Take a Harbour Cruise Ride to see the Chinese Fishing Nets. Dinner and overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(1905, 317, 'DEPARTURE FROM COCHIN', 'The morning will be free for leisure. In the afternoon, you will be transferred to the airport for your journey onwards.'),
(1906, 318, 'COCHIN TO MUNNAR ( 135 KILOMETERS - 5 HOURS)', '\"Arrive at Cochin International Airport, and then drive to Munnar, which is approximately 5 hours drive away from Cochin. To spice up your five-hour journey, visit attractions like Cheyyara waterfalls, Valara waterfalls, Attukal waterfall, and spice plantations. Overnight stay at the Munnar hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1907, 318, 'MUNNAR SIGHTSEEING TOUR', '\"Today, you will have the entire day at your disposal to explore Munnar. When in Munnar, you\'ll visit attractions like Mattupetty Dam, spice plantations, tea estate, Eravikulam National Park, and various other prominent attractions of the region. Today, you will take part in boating, rock climbing, and trekking. Overnight stay at the Munnar hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1908, 318, 'MUNNAR TO THEKKADY (150 KILOMETERS - 4 HOURS)', 'In the morning, embark on a 150-kilometer long drive to reach Thekkady. For the entire day, you will explore Periyar National Park. You will go for bamboo rafting, jeep safari, nature walks, elephant ride, and trekking. Dinner and overnight stay at the Thekkady.'),
(1909, 318, 'THEKKADY - ALAPPUZHA (150 KILOMETERS - 5 HOURS)', 'After breakfast, leave for Alappuzha (commonly known as Alleppey) from Thekkady, which will take approximately 5 hours. For the rest of the day, you will enjoy the houseboat ride and visit some beautiful attractions. Even your night stay will be arranged in the houseboat.'),
(1910, 318, 'ALAPPUZHA - COCHIN (80 KILOMETERS- 1.5 HOURS)', 'Today is going to be the last day of your tour. Post breakfast board your coach that will take you to Cochin. In Cochin, check in the hotel, and go for a sightseeing tour. In the morning and afternoon, you will visit attractions of Cochin like St. Francis Church, Jewish Synagogue, and Dutch Palace. Take a Harbour Cruise Ride to see the Chinese Fishing Nets. Dinner and overnight stay at the hotel. In the evening, you will be transferred to the airport or railway station from where you can take your flight/train for your journey onwards.'),
(1911, 319, 'KANYAKUMARI', '\"Arrive at Kanyakumari Railway station and report to the coach, our representative will guide you to the hotel. Rest for the day and dine in the hotel as the sundowns.\r\n\"'),
(1912, 319, 'KANYAKUMARI – TRIVANDRUM – 91.2 KM', '\"After breakfast in the hotel, visit some of the famous landmarks in Kanyakumari. The tour will take you to Tri-Samudra Milan, Kanyakumari Mandir, Gandhi Mandapam and a short ferry ride to Swami Vivekananda Rock Memorial. After the excursion in Kanyakumari, the tour will take you to Trivandrum en-routing some must see places like the Kanyakumari wax museum, Velli Garden. After you arrive at Trivandrum you can check in the hotel and rest for the day after dinner.\r\n\"'),
(1913, 319, 'TRIVANDRUM', '\"On day 3, the tour will take you on a city expedition visiting some noted landmarks like the Raja Ravi Varma Art Gallery, Padmanabh Swami Temple and Napier Museum (subject to operation). After the city tour spend a free time in the evening at Kovalam beach.\r\n\"'),
(1914, 319, 'TRIVANDRUM – ALLEPPEY - PERIYAR (THEKKADY)', '\"Trivandrum – Alleppey – 146 km\r\nAlleppey – Periyar – 130 km\r\nArrive in Kottayam and enjoy the leisurely backwater ride from Alleppey to Nedumudi. After go back to your hotel and rest for the rest of the day.\"'),
(1915, 319, 'PERIYAR - MUNNAR – 99.0 KM', '\"After breakfast visit the Periyar Wildlife Sanctuary by boat in Periyar Lake and enjoy shopping at Kumily Spice Village. After the tour around Periyar, travel to Munnar. Upon arrival, you will be guided to your hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1916, 319, 'MUNNAR', '\"After early breakfast, go to the Mattupetty Dam and enjoy speed boat rides. Visit the sprawling Tea Garden of the south, visit the incredible beautiful Echo Point and visit the Eravikulam (Rajamalai) National Park. After the excursion, return to your hotel and rest followed by dinner and overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1917, 319, 'MUNNAR – KALADI – COCHIN – 130 KM', '\"After breakfast proceed to Cochin via Kaladi to visit Adi Shankaracharya\'s birthplace. Once you arrive in Cochin, witness the live Kathakali dance performance in the evening followed by dinner.\r\n\"'),
(1918, 319, 'COCHIN', 'Early morning after breakfast go for sightseeing to places like the St. Francis Church and Dutch Palace. Take a Harbour Cruise Ride to see the famous Chinese Fishing Nets. After the city tour, enjoy a get-together with your travel companions in the evening with dinner thereafter.'),
(1919, 319, 'DEPARTURE', 'Have a healthy breakfast and checkout from the hotel. Our representatives will drop you at the Cochin Railway Station [Ernakulam Junction South] to conclude the tour.'),
(1920, 320, 'COCHIN – MUNNAR 130 KM', '\"Arrive at Cochin International Airport or Cochin Railway Station (Ernakulam Junction South) and head straight for your coach to continue on your journey to Munnar. Once you arrive at your destination our representative will guide you to your hotel. By the sun down enjoy dinner at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1921, 320, 'MUNNAR', '\"After early breakfast, go for a fun spree fair at Mattupetty Dam and enjoy speed boat ride. Get a chance to see sprawling Tea Garden, visit the incredible beauty of Echo Point and visit the Eravikulam (Rajamalai) National Park. After the outing, return to your hotel and rest, dinner and overnight stay at the hotel follows.\r\n\"'),
(1922, 320, 'MUNNAR – KUMARAKOM (157 KM)', 'On day 3, after heavy breakfast, hop on for a short journey to Kumarakom a beautiful village near the Vembanad Lake that sits surrounded by the backwaters of Kerala. On arrival check into your hotel and spend the rest of the day in full relaxing mode.'),
(1923, 320, 'KUMARAKOM TOUR', 'After breakfast, cruise at the famous backwaters of Kerala and the main attraction of Kumarakom - Kumarakom Bird Sanctuary. Take a sneak peek of some incredible living species like the Waterfowl, heron and the water duck, owl, egret, cuckoo as well as the migratory Siberian cranes. If you are in the right migratory season, you can get a chance to see the wood beetle and other birds like flycatchers. After sightseeing, go back to your hotel and enjoy warm dinner with other travel companions and share your stories.'),
(1924, 320, 'KUMARAKOM – KOVALAM (180 KM)', '\"On day 5, check out from Kumarakom and go for a rejuvenating pleasure trip to Kovalam. Upon arrival enjoy a free and sheer beauty relaxing in Kovalam Beach.\r\n\"'),
(1925, 320, 'KOVALAM – TRIVANDRUM - KOVALAM', '\"Enjoy the grand city tour of Trivandrum and visit some renowned places like Raja Ravi Varma Art Gallery, Padmanabh Swami Temple and Napier Museum. You can also visit the beautiful Velli Garden and enjoy speed boat rides. After the tour return to your hotel at Kovalam to rest and enjoy dinner with fellow travel companions.\r\n\"'),
(1926, 320, 'DEPARTURE- KOVALAM - TRIVANDRUM INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT (13 KM)', 'After healthy and heavy breakfast in the hotel at Kovalam, our representatives will drop you to the airport. The closest airport is the Trivandrum International Airport.'),
(1927, 321, 'COCHIN - ALLEPPEY HOUSEBOAT', '\"Cochin - Alleppey 53.1 km\r\nArrive at Cochin International Airport or Cochin Railway Station (Ernakulam Junction South) and proceed to Alleppey. Enjoy the smooth ride through beautiful scenic views, once you enter Alleppey head straight to Alleppey Boathouse.\r\nEnjoy your 24-hour stay at the Kerala style houseboat from noon and you will be greeted with welcome drinks, snacks followed with lunch and dinner.\r\nSpend a night at the luxurious A/C boathouse, admiring at many beautiful sights.\r\n\"'),
(1928, 321, 'ALLEPPEY HOUSEBOAT - KUMARAKOM RESORT (32.5 KM)', '\"On the 2nd day, drive to Kumarakom Resort and check into the resort. Spend the rest of the day at one\'s own sweet time and enjoy all the amenities of the resort. Spend an overnight stay at Vivanta by TAJ Kumarakom.\r\n\"'),
(1929, 321, 'KUMARAKOM RESORT - KOVALAM (180 KM)', '\"The next day, drive to Kovalam and wander through many landmarks like Lighthouse Beach, Howah Beach, Ashoka Beach, and Kovalam Beach. Surrounded by many coconut palms fringe and golden sandy beach enjoy your every existence in Gods own Country.\r\nStay overnight at Vivanta by TAJ Kovalam.\r\n\"'),
(1930, 321, 'TRIVANDRUM/ KOVALAM', '\"On day 4, you can choose any option, whether spend a rejuvenating day at Kovalam Beach or opt for Trivandrum city tour.\r\nThe city tour of Trivandrum includes Sree Padmanabhaswami Temple, Kuthiramalika Palace Museum, The Napier Museum, Sree Chithra Art Gallery, Zoological Park, Science and Technology Museum, Kanakakunnu Palace and Planetarium.\r\nAfter the sightseeing you can return to your hotel for an overnight stay at Vivanta by TAJ Kovalam.\r\n\"'),
(1931, 321, 'LAST DAY AT COCHIN', '\"Visit the Alleppey Beach and drive to Cochin for sightseeing. Once you arrive at Cochin, you can sightsee places like fort Cochin, navy museum, St. Francis church, Chinese fishing net, Santa Cruz basilica, Mattancherry palace, Jewish synagogue, Marian drive, Marine walkway, boating, Tripunitura hill palace.\r\nIf sightseeing is a second option for you and you want to shop, you can wander around the shopping streets at Cochin.\r\nAfter the heavy excursion, our representative will leave you at Cochin International Airport or Cochin Railway Station to end the tour.\r\n\"'),
(1932, 321, 'KOVALAM – TRIVANDRUM - KOVALAM', 'Enjoy the grand city tour of Trivandrum and visit some renowned places like Raja Ravi Varma Art Gallery, Padmanabh Swami Temple and Napier Museum. You can also visit the beautiful Velli Garden and enjoy speed boat rides. After the tour return to your hotel at Kovalam to rest and enjoy dinner with fellow travel companions.'),
(1933, 321, 'DEPARTURE- KOVALAM - TRIVANDRUM INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT (13 KM)', 'After healthy and heavy breakfast in the hotel at Kovalam, our representatives will drop you to the airport. The closest airport is the Trivandrum International Airport.'),
(1934, 322, 'Arrive Mumbai', 'Upon arrival at Mumbai meeting and assistance followed by transfer to hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1935, 322, 'Arrive Cochin', '\"Breakfast at the hotel and transfer to airport to connect flight for Cochin.Munnar Tour\r\nUpon Arrival at Cochin our representative meets you and transfer to the hotel. Later sightseeing tour that includes visit to Fort Cochin, Santa Cruz Basilica, Dutch Palace (Closed on Friday and Sunday, opening time 9:30 am to 4:00 pm) at Mattancherry, St. Francis Church and Chinese fishing nets. Evening free. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1936, 322, 'Kochi - Munnar', '\"After breakfast drive to Munnar A lovely hill station, filled with tea plantations and misty mountains. The drive to Munnar is very scenic crossing the narrow hairpin road where you can see beautiful valleys, Tea gardens. Check in to the hotel. Overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1937, 322, 'Munnar Munnar Tour', '\"Today Kerala Tour Itinerary is devoted to sightseeing in and around Munnar. Enjoy panoramic views of Anamudi, the highest peak of South India at 2695 m, is visible from Munnar. Visit the Christ Church and proceed for wildlife watching at Eravikulam National Park (16 km).\r\nMadupetty Dam, a famous picnic spot for boating and horse riding en route to Top Station. Visit the Tea Plantation. Return to hotel for overnight stay.\"'),
(1938, 322, 'Munnar - Thekkady (Periyar)', '\"After breakfast depart to Thekkady (Periyar Wildlife Sanctuary). Check in your hotel. In afternoon go for a boat ride at Periyar Tiger Reserve to view the wildlife in the sanctuary. The boat ride in the lake is delightful way of spotting Elephant and Avifauna, for which the park is well known. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1939, 322, 'Thekkady Periyar Lake Tour', '\"Today enjoy the Plantation tour. Visit the spice plantations like cardamom, cinnamon, pepper, coffee and tea estates. You can shop at the local market. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1940, 322, 'Thekkady - Alleppey (152 kms)', 'After breakfast transfer to the Alleppey the Venice of the East. Here transfer you to A/c deluxe Houseboat. Explore the Kerala\'s natural beauty backwaters beauty. House boat will take you to the virgin villages of Kerala to explore the real life of Kerala people. Overnight stay at House Boat.'),
(1941, 322, 'Alleppey - Cochin (80 kms)', '\"After breakfast drive to Cochin. On arrival transfer you to the airport for Mumbai.\r\nOn arrival at Mumbai own transfer to international airport to connect flight for onward destination.\"'),
(1942, 323, 'Arrive Mumbai - Gateway of India, Mumbai', '\"Arrive Mumbai International airport. On arrival, the guest will be met by our representative and transferred to hotel. Upon arrival at hotel the guests will be provided with the traditional Indian welcome. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n\"');
INSERT INTO `tour_daywise` (`itinerydata_id`, `tour_id`, `itinerydata_title`, `itinerydata_description`) VALUES
(1943, 323, 'Mumbai', '\"Morning, one hour boat ride across Mumbai Harbour brings you to the lush green Elephanta Island. Here, visit some of the huge and intricately carved Elephanta Caves that date back to the 8th century. For rows of massive columns cut into solid rock from three magnificent avenues, lead to the outstanding three-headed sculpture representing Brahma the Creator, Vishnu the Preserver and Shiva the Destroyer. Dedicated to Shiva, the beauty and power of these phenomenal sculptures depicting the various manifestations of Shiva is overpowering. Afternoon, City tour of Mumbai - the great port city with its Victorian Gothic buildings from the British Raj Era mingling with the modern. The tour includes \'Gateway of India\' overlooking the Harbour, the \'Towers of Silence\', \'Marine Drive\', the \'Colaba Causeway\' - the commercial heart of Mumbai and the Dhobi Ghat, the unique and colourful outdoor \'laundry\'. Drive upto the Malabar Hill to the lovely \'Hanging Gardens\' and the Kamla Nehru Park from where you will get a wonderful view of Mumbai and the Arabian Sea, spread out before you. Also visit Mani Bhawan, a small museum dedicated to the life and works of Mahatma Gandhi, and the bustling Crawford Market. Overnight at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1944, 323, 'Mumbai - Cochin - Periyar - Periyar Lake', 'Morning transfer to the airport to connect flight to Cochin. Upon arrival, meet & transfer to the hotel for lunch. Thereafter drive to Periyar. Upon arrival at Periyar - check into hotel at Periyar - Sprawling across 777 sq. kms. of the Cardamom Hills of the Western Ghats, Thekkady is the home to one of the largest wildlife reserves in India. Alive with exotic flora and vibrant wildlife, it is the perfect getaway tucked away among hills. Overnight stay at wildlife Resort.'),
(1945, 323, 'Periyar - Kumarakom', 'Early morning boat cruise on the Lake of the famous Periyar wildlife sanctuary to see wildlife. Periyar - an artificial lake or reservoir created by a dam on Periyar River is the heart of the Wildlife Sanctuary wild elephants, Asiatic Deer, Black Buck and even Tigers come to shores of the lake for a drink. Return to hotel for breakfast. After breakfast drive through the winding \"Ghats\" lined with prosperous tea plantations & then arrive the fascinating countryside of low-lying palms and paddy fields to Kumarakom enroute visit the tea estates. Kumarakom - is a beautiful backwater village on the shores of the enchanting Vembanad Lake, criss crossed with meandering waterways and ancient cottages. Relax at the waterfront, with the occasional native row boat gliding silently by, and the air so calm, you can reach out and touch the sky with your finger tips. Overnight at hotel.'),
(1946, 323, 'Kumarakom - Houseboat, Kumarakom', 'Morning at leisure at hotel, after breakfast, we will take you on house boat to take a cruise on the backwaters in traditional country canoes called \"vanjis\" to see the agricultural activities of the local people living on the back waters. Visit also the beautiful bird sanctuary. Lunch at the hotel Afternoon board the traditional rice boats - \"Kettuvallam\" and begin your journey through the picturesque backwaters and small lakes relaxing in the tranquillity of Kerala\'s beautiful scenery. Experience the way of life and activity of the local people, the one bedroom house with a lounge is exclusively for you, meals will be served with freshly bought produce from the local markets and cooked on board. Overnight on board.'),
(1947, 323, 'Marari', 'Breakfast on board, Sail to Alleppey & disembark at Puthenangady Jetty. On arrival proceed directly to Mararikulam. Mararikulam - is one of the picturesque fishing villages that dot the lovely coast line of Kerala. This private, shallow beach is fringed with unending lines of coconut palms. Rest of the day at leisure for own activities and enjoy the facilities of the Resort. Overnight at hotel.'),
(1948, 323, 'Marari', 'Full day at leisure for own activities and enjoy the facilities of the Resort. Overnight at hotel.'),
(1949, 323, 'Marari', 'Full day at leisure for own activities and enjoy the facilities of the Resort. Overnight at hotel.'),
(1950, 323, 'Marari - Cochin Dutch Palace, Kochi', '\"Cochin\" Popularly known as the Queen of the Arabian Sea, Cochin is the oldest European settlement in India. Frilled with backwaters and rich with old world charm, this city has lured many a great voyager to its shores. Arrive Cochin & check into hotel Tour of Cochin or \"Kochi\"- the palm green, commercial capital of Kerala is known as the \"Queen of the Arabian Sea\". From time immemorial, Arabic, Chinese, Dutch, British & Portuguese seafarers followed the sea route to Kochi & left their impression on the town. Modern Kochi is thus a splendid mosaic of these myriad influences. Visit the Dutch Palace, the Jewish Synagogue, the Church of St. Francis, the Bolghatty Palace & the famous Chinese fishing nets. Afternoon, Harbour cruise - Cochin has one of the finest natural harbours. The backwaters extending to the east & south from the harbour are dotted with tiny islands, formed naturally by alluvial deposits from the rivers. Evening witness the Kathakali dance performance + make up demonstration - Kathakali is a unique dance which has a 2000 year old history with more than 100 different \'mudras\' or gesture depicting deities, demons, heroes, heroines and kings - each based on episodes from the Mahabharata and Ramayana, the two epic Indian myths. Dinner and overnight at hotel.'),
(1951, 323, 'Cochin - Mumbai', 'Morning transfer from hotel to the airport for flight to Mumbai. Upon arrival - met & transferred to the hotel. Dinner and overnight at hotel.'),
(1952, 323, 'Abroad - Mumbai', 'Breakfast at the hotel and transfer to international airport to connect flight for onward destination.'),
(1953, 324, 'Arrive - Cochin (By Flight)', '\"Upon arrival at Cochin airport meet with our representative and transfer to the hotel. \r\nIn the afternoon city tour of Cochin to visit Dutch Palace (Built by the Portuguese), Jew Town, the 1568 Jewish Synagogue, spice market, where the air is filled with the pungent smell of spices, St. Francis Church and Chinese fishing nets. The evening holds a show of Kerala\'s most popular classical dance. Overnight stay at hotel.Munnar\r\n\"'),
(1954, 324, 'Cochin - Munnar', '\"After breakfast drive to Munnar (4½ hours), the beautiful hill station of Kerala. Transfer to hotel on arrival. Spend the remaining day at leisure and enjoy picturesque landscapes. Visit the aromatic tea plantations or indulge in thrilling sport activities like paragliding. Evening transfer to hotel. Overnight at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1955, 324, 'Munnar', '\"After breakfast full day sightseeing in and around Munnar. Enjoy panoramic views of Anamudi, the highest peak of South India at 2695 m, is visible from Munnar. Visit the Christ Church and proceed for wildlife watching at Eravikulam National Park (16 km). \r\nNote\r\n: Park would be close from 01Jan to 28 Feb every year Continue to Rajamalai Hills lying adjacent to the park and stop by at Madupetty Dam, a famous picnic spot for boating and horse riding en route to Top Station. Evening transfer to hotel. Overnight at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1956, 324, 'Munnar - Thekkady (Periyar)Periyar Lake', '\"After breakfast leave for Periyar in the morning (4 hours) and transfer to hotel on arrival. You may opt for a pleasant boat ride along the Periyar Lake in the evening. Enjoy watching varied birds and animals like tigers, elephants, wild boar, deer, etc at the Periyar / Thekkady National Park. You can also visit a few tribal villages around Periyar and witness fascinating activities of tribals collecting honey from dangerous hill bees. Evening transfer to hotel. Overnight at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1957, 324, 'Thekkady - Kumarakom', '\"After breakfast leave for Kumarakom (3½ hours) on day 5 of Kerala Tour Itinerary. Check in at backwater resort on arrival. Spend the rest of the day at leisure at the picturesque backwaters that form one of the major attractions of Kerala. Overnight at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1958, 324, 'Kumarakom - Alleppey', '\"After breakfast transfer to Kottayam and board the luxurious houseboat for an overnight journey along the tranquil Kerala backwaters to Alleppey.\r\n\"'),
(1959, 324, 'Alleppey - Kovalam', '\"Disembark from the houseboat at Alleppey and transfer to Kovalam. Check in to hotel near the beach upon arrival. Day free to spend at leisure on the beach. Enjoy playing with the golden sands or take a swim in the shallow water. A soothing sunbath is a perfect option to unwind. The more adventurous ones can enjoy thrilling beach sports. An Ayurvedic massage can also be availed (optional). Evening transfer to hotel. Overnight at hotel.Kovalam Beach\r\n\"'),
(1960, 324, 'Kovalam', 'After breakfast full day free to explore the beaches. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1961, 324, 'Kovalam - Kanyakumari - Kovalam', '\"After breakfast drive to Trivandrum, arrive Trivandrum city tour of Trivandrum. The main attraction is Padmanabhaswamy Temple, one of the 108 pilgrimage sites for the Vaishnavites. The exquisite carvings on its 400 pillars is notable. Evening transfer to hotel. Afternoon free for leisure on beaches. Overnight at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1962, 324, 'Kovalam - Departure (By Flight)', 'After breakfast transfer to airport to connect flight for Mumbai. On arrival at Mumbai airport, transfer to international airport to connect flight for onward destination.'),
(1963, 325, 'Chennai', '\"Upon arrival at Chennai meeting and assistance followed by transfer to hotel. Chennai is popular as the gateway to southern India, established in 1639 by the East India Company, is one of the oldest cities of the country. Assistance and transfer to hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1964, 325, 'Chennai - Covelong', '\"After breakfast, half day sightseeing tour, visiting Gandhi Memorial, Kala Kshetra, Mylapore temple and Marine beach. Later drive to Covelong. Check in to the hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1965, 325, 'CovelongPondicherry Tourist Attraction', 'Day free at Covelong Beach. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1966, 325, 'Covelong - Pondicherry', 'Breakfast at the hotel and drive to Pondicherry. On arrival check-in at hotel. Later half day city tour to Aurobindo Ashram, you will be transported to a world of bliss and peace. Here the day starts with meditation and visitors are allowed to take a look of Sri Aurobindo and his chief disciple Mother\'s room. You will also visit the Pondicherry Museum where among the artifacts you will see the discoveries of Arikamedu, Chola bronze items. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1967, 325, 'Pondicherry - Thanjavur (237Kms / 6Hrs) Pondicherry Tourist Attraction', 'Breakfast at the hotel and drive to Thanjavur. On arrival check-in at hotel. Afternoon we will visit Brihadeshwara Fort & Temple, which is a Chola architectural marvel. This is also listed in the world heritage. Also you will visit Thanjavur Palace & Museum, which houses a library, museum and art gallery. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1968, 325, 'Tanjore - Trichy - Madurai', '\"Breakfast at the hotel and drive to Madurai. Enroute visit Trichy. Trichy was the citadel of the Chola dynasty in the medieval period. In the 18th century it witnessed the Carnatic wars fought between the French and the English. Lord Robert Clive\'s house is still there to see and so is the Danish Church. The Rock-Fort is the landmark of Trichy. A climb of 434 steps leads to the ancient temple of Ganapati on top and a further climb to a Shiva temple. Later continue to Madurai. On arrival check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1969, 325, 'Madurai - PeriyarPeriyar Lake', 'After breakfast visit the great Meenakshi Temple dedicated to the consort of Lord Shiva with its towering gopurams (rising high above the surrounding country side) visit the Thirumalai Nayak Palace - A gracious building in the Indo saracenic style, famous for the Stucco work on its domes & arches. Later drive to Periyar. On arrival check-in at hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1970, 325, 'Thekkady (Periyar) - Kumarakom', 'After Breakfast enjoy the boat ride in Periyar Wildlife Sanctuary to view the wildlife. The boat ride in the lake is delightful way of spotting Elephant and Avifauna, for which the park is well known. Afternoon drive to Kumarakom. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1971, 325, 'Kumarkom - Alleppey (27 kms)Periyar Lake', 'After breakfast visit Kumarakum bird Sanctuary. Later drive to Alleppey. Here transfer you to A/c deluxe Houseboat. Explore the Kerala\'s natural beauty backwaters beauty. House boat will take you to the virgin villages of Kerala to explore the real life of Kerala people. Overnight stay at House Boat.'),
(1972, 325, 'Alleppey - Kochi - Chennai', '\"After breakfast drive to Cochin. On arrival at Cochin proceed for city tour of Cochin visit to Fort Cochin, Santa Cruz Basilica, Dutch Palace (Closed on Friday and Sunday, opening time 9:30 am to 4:00 pm) at Mattancherry, St. Francis Church and Chinese fishing nets. Later drop you at airport to connect flight for Chennai.\r\nUpon arrival at Chennai meeting and assistance followed by transfer to hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.\"'),
(1973, 325, 'Chennai departs', 'Breakfast at the hotel and transfer to airport to connect flight for onward destination.'),
(1974, 326, 'Cochin Munnar', 'Upon arrival at Cochin International Airport where our representative meets you and transfer to the hotel. Evening free. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1975, 326, 'Kochi - Munnar (130 kms)', 'Breakfast at the hotel. Morning sightseeing tour that includes visit to Fort Cochin, Santa Cruz Basilica, Dutch Palace (Closed on Friday and Sunday, opening time 9:30 am to 4:00 pm) at Mattancherry, St. Francis Church and Chinese fishing nets. Afternoon drive to Munnar A lovely hill station, filled with tea plantations and misty mountains. The drive to Munnar is very scenic crossing the narrow hairpin road where you can see beautiful valleys, Tea gardens. Check in to the hotel. Overnight stay.'),
(1976, 326, 'Munnar', '\"Today Kerala Tour Itinerary is devoted to sightseeing in and around Munnar. Enjoy panoramic views of Anamudi, the highest peak of South India at 2695 m, is visible from Munnar. Visit the Christ Church and proceed for wildlife watching at Eravikulam National Park (16 km) (Note: Park would be close from 01 Jan to 28 Feb every year). Madupetty Dam, a famous picnic spot for boating and horse riding en route to Top Station. Return to hotel for overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1977, 326, 'Munnar - Ooty (250 kms) Ooty', 'after breakfast drive Ooty. Ooty is better known as the queen of hill station, 7300 feet above sea level on arrival Ooty check in at hotel. Evening take a boat ride at Ooty Lake and overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1978, 326, 'Ooty', 'After breakfast at hotel drive out for a local tour of Ooty Visit Botanical garden, Ooty Lake, Doddabetta peak, Hindustan photo films factory, Pykara Falls, Wenlock Downs etc evening return back to hotel and overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1979, 326, 'Ooty - Mysore (139 kms / 4hrs)', '\"After breakfast, drive to Mysore. Visit this ancient princely city, famous for its silks, sandalwood and various palaces, among which the largest palace in India, built in Indo-Persian style in 1900. Visit an art gallery and the Chamundeshwari Temple dedicated to the goddess Kali on Chamundi Hill, from which you have a panoramic view of the city. You will also visit Somnathpur, famous for the temple of Keshava. Overnight at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1980, 326, 'Mysore - Hassan Ooty', '\"After breakfast drive to Hassan and visiting the famous tourist attractions that falls en route such as the Shravanabelagola that is renowned for the 17m high statue of Lord Gomateshwara a top the Indragiri Hill. Overnight stay at hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1981, 326, 'Hassan', 'After breakfast, enjoy the sightseeing in Hassan that involves excursions to Belur and Halebid. Evening free for shopping. Overnight stay at hotel.'),
(1982, 326, 'Hassan Bangalore (185 kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Bangalore. On arrival at Bangalore drop you at airport to connect flight for onward destination.'),
(1983, 327, 'Coimbatore - Munnar ( 157 kms / 04 Hrs drive)', '\"Drive to Munnar from Coimbatore in the morning. Upon arrival, check into a pre-booked hotel. Rest of the day free at leisure. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1984, 327, 'Munnar - Munnar-hills-tour', 'In the morning post breakfast enjoy a full day sightseeing tour of Munnar. The tour includes a visit to Mattupetty Dam, Kundala Lake, Eravikulam National Park, Tea Museum, Attukad Waterfalls and Blossom Park. Return to the hotel for an overnight stay.'),
(1985, 327, 'Munnar', '\"Day free at leisure or you can pay a visit to the beautiful tea plantation. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(1986, 327, 'Munnar - Coimbatore', 'Morning after breakfast check out and drive back to Coimbatore.'),
(1987, 328, 'Kochi (Cochin)Cochin Backwaters', '\"On arrival in Kochi, our tour representative will be there to welcome you and transfer you to your pre-booked hotel. Check in at the hotel. Freshen up and relax in the hotel and enjoy the first glimpse of the city. You will be meeting your other group members and get a detailed overview of your trip. Thereafter, we will leave for a walk along the streets of the city and look at its major highlights. On the way, we will see coconut tress reflected in the light, waters of backwaters, ancient churches, fort, Chinese fishing nets, Dutch buildings, Bolghatty Palace and Cherai Beach, Portuguese artistic and British monuments. Further, we will be visiting the Kochi Fort to see the beautiful sunset views. Here, you can also see the old cantilevered fishing nets, brought from China, in Malayalam they\'re called \'cheena vala\'. Later in the evening return back to the hotel to enjoy delicious dinner and an overnight stay.\r\nKochi or Cochin is situated in the South Western Coast of the Indian Subcontinent. The city is often referred as the Gateway to Kerala. It is a small and beautiful town that lies in the Ernakulum district of Kerala state of India. The city is bordered by the Western Ghats in the East and the Arabian Sea in the West. Kochi is famous worldwide for its beautiful gold designer jewellery and is also offer habitat to the Dutch Palace (Mattancherry), Jew Town with its temple and the Fort.\r\n\"'),
(1988, 328, 'Cochin- Alleppeyalleppey-houseboats', '\"Today in the morning, we will travel to Allepey. On arrive in Alleppey, check in at the houseboat and enjoy journey cum stay in your pre-booked houseboat.\r\nAlleppy or Alappuzha is categorized as the Venice of the East. Alappuzha means the land between the sea and a network of rivers falling into it. The place brings to mind a sense of romance and beauty. It has a golden streak of land woven with rivers, lakes, lagoons and canals. Alappuzha has a lighthouse, where one can witness the beautiful view of Alleppey coast from above the lighthouse. The white sand beach is a beautiful place to relax and enjoy the sea and the sun. It is also home to Kuttanad, the Rice Bowl of Kerala, one of the very few interesting places in the world where farming is done below the sea level.\r\nIn the afternoon, we will explore the Vembanad Lake, a striking picnic spot and fast developing backwaters, which offers boating and fishing. Further, we will continue our explorations by boat along winding backwaters witnessing the life of the people of Kerala and its entire colour. As the sun goes down, we will be entertained by the boatmen singing traditional songs.\r\nThroughout the day, you will get an opportunity to talk and interact with the local families, learn about their life in the islands and eat traditional local cuisine in their homes. An overnight stay in the houseboat.\r\n\"'),
(1989, 328, 'Periyar Tiger Reserve (Thekkady)alleppey-houseboats', '\"In the morning, we will drive to Periyar. On arrival, our representative will transfer you to your pre-booked hotel.\r\nThe Periyar Wild Life Sanctuary is one of most fascinating and natural looking wildlife sanctuaries of India where one can see wildlife from the close range. The vegetation, flora and fauna, and the birds of Thekkady are uniquely rich. It is one of the largest wildlife sanctuaries in the world. Located on the banks of the Periyar Lake, an artificial lake, at Thekkady, Periyar Wildlife Sanctuary is a part of Project Tiger, a wildlife preservation project designed to protect Royal Bengal Tigers from extinction. The park offers habitat to 62 different kinds of mammal. Out of them, one most famous ones are the park\'s famous herds of wild Asiatic elephants that often come to bathe in the Periyar lake.\r\nIn the afternoon, we will proceed to a spice plantation to learn various things such as how cardamom and pepper grow and witness the mind bowing view of calm crystal clear Periyar Lake. Bamboo rafting and trekking, these are some other unique activities in the Periyar National Park. Here, you can take a hiking and rafting trip through the deep jungles of the Tiger Reserve and also visit Periyar National Park, which is located in the hills of the Western Ghats.\r\nLater, return back to the houseboats hotels to enjoy food and an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1990, 328, 'Periyar Tiger Reserve (Thekkady)alleppey-houseboats', '\"In the morning, we will drive to Periyar. On arrival, our representative will transfer you to your pre-booked hotel.\r\nThe Periyar Wild Life Sanctuary is one of most fascinating and natural looking wildlife sanctuaries of India where one can see wildlife from the close range. The vegetation, flora and fauna, and the birds of Thekkady are uniquely rich. It is one of the largest wildlife sanctuaries in the world. Located on the banks of the Periyar Lake, an artificial lake, at Thekkady, Periyar Wildlife Sanctuary is a part of Project Tiger, a wildlife preservation project designed to protect Royal Bengal Tigers from extinction. The park offers habitat to 62 different kinds of mammal. Out of them, one most famous ones are the park\'s famous herds of wild Asiatic elephants that often come to bathe in the Periyar lake.\r\nIn the afternoon, we will proceed to a spice plantation to learn various things such as how cardamom and pepper grow and witness the mind bowing view of calm crystal clear Periyar Lake. Bamboo rafting and trekking, these are some other unique activities in the Periyar National Park. Here, you can take a hiking and rafting trip through the deep jungles of the Tiger Reserve and also visit Periyar National Park, which is located in the hills of the Western Ghats.\r\nLater, return back to the houseboats hotels to enjoy food and an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1991, 328, 'Thekkady-Varkalaalleppey-houseboats', '\"Today we will start our day a bit early in the morning and drive to Varkala. On arrival, check in at the hotel.\r\nVarkela, a temple town, is also famous for its landscape. Nestled in the southern Indian state of Kerala, it is known for its mineral water springs and sea beach getaway. A tour to Kerala remains incomplete without a stop-off at the beautiful beaches of Varkala. The silvery stretches of sands along the Arabian Sea offer a placid destination for the beach lovers. The sunset at Varakala Beach is truly overwhelming with the sun sinking into the sky just like a ball of molten gold as the sun.\r\nIn the evening, spend some time travelling in the peaceful gardens of an ashram devoted to the most eminent spiritual and social reformer of Kerala. Also, visit the mystical Janardhana Swamy Temple or just head to the beach to relax and watch the Arabian Sea.\r\nLater return back to the hotel to enjoy delicious meal and an overnight stay.\"'),
(1992, 328, 'Varkalakappil-lake', '\"Take pleasure of another purifying morning in Varkala. This picturesque town is a group of religious pilgrims approached Narada, a saint of ancient times and confessed to having sinned. Narada threw his valkalam and it landed at a place near the seashore.\r\nWe will be visiting the ancient Janardhana temple. It is at the cliff top where most of the hotels and restaurants are situated. Further, we will visit Sivagiri Mautt, which is located just 3 kms away from the Janardana Temple, Varkala Tunnel which is the 924ft tunnel and Kappil Lake that gives way to the beautiful world of the Kerala backwaters. Also, one can enjoy an elephant ride down the village roads.\r\nLater return back to the hotel for meal and an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1993, 328, 'Varkala-Kochi (Cochin) Departure', 'Today in the morning, we will leave for railway station where you will take train from Varkala to Cochin.'),
(1994, 329, 'Arrive Goakappil-lake', '\"On arrival at the beach capital of India, Goa, our representative will be there to greet you and transfer you to the hotel. After check in at the hotel, freshen up and relax. Rest of the day is free for leisure.\r\nGoa is a world famous tourist destination of India especially among the beach lovers. It is acknowledged for its abundant natural beauty, shiny beaches, feats and festival, old churches and temples, and evergreen hills and mountains. This small yet beautiful state of India is blessed with a lot of beaches such as Anjuna Beach, Baga Beach, the Candolim Beach, Chapora beach, Vagator and Dona Paula Beach. All these beaches are popular for its scenic beauty and lively ambience. In addition, old Goa has many important Cathedrals and churches such as St. Catherine\'s Church, Church of St. Francis Xavier and Arch of vice Roy of Goa.\r\nYou can visit these famous places of Goa during your leisure time. Later, in the evening you can take pleasure of the Ayurveda massage and relax near the beaches. Enjoy dinner and an overnight stay at the hotel.\"'),
(1995, 329, 'Goa-Mumbai-Mangalore (By Flight) Drive to UdupiUdupi Krihsna Temple', '\"Today morning, we will fly to Mangalore. On arrive in Mangalore, we will drive to Udupi, after refreshment, we will proceed for the local sightseeing of the land of the \"\"lord of the stars\"\".\r\nSandwiched between tranquil Arabian Sea on the west and the verdant mountains of the Western Ghats on the east, Udupi is a land of spiritual beauty. The place is famous for its religious passion and vivacity among those who wish to take a religious pilgrimage and give boost to their spirituality. The Sri Krishna Temple, is famous for Navagraha Kitiki, a window with nine holes, from where Lord Krishna is worshipped. Ambalpady is another holy place known for its complex of several temples. Further, Kaup and Malpe beaches are the major attractions of the town. Some other places that are worth exploring in Udupi are Balakrishna Temple, Pajaka village and Indrani Panchadurga temple.\r\nLater, in the evening return back to the hotel to enjoy delicious meal followed by an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(1996, 329, 'Udupi- ChikmagalurUdupi Krihsna Temple', '\"We will drive to the hill station of Chikmagalur, which is located in the southern state of Karnataka. It comprises of deep valleys, massive hills, historical temples, wildlife sanctuaries, silver-waterfalls and beautiful coffee blossoms that together make this hill station a paradise for the visitors.\r\nFurther, we will proceed to Mullayangiri in order to get some breathtaking views of the region. Mullayangiri is a part of the Baba Budan Giri Hill Ranges, which is the highest peak in Karnataka. On the way, we will visit a Sitalayanagiri where the water in the Shiva temple neither decreases not increases. Thereafter, we will visit Hebbe Falls. Water streams down from an altitude of 168 meters in this beautiful waterfall. The region is also blessed with the famous Kudremukh National Park and Bhadra Wildlife Sanctuary.\r\nIn the evening, we will be visiting the Raj Bhavan to get the glimpse of its beautiful sunset scenes. We will also explore the numerous coffee producing areas and the Rose Garden to explore varieties of roses. In evening, return back to the hotel to enjoy dinner followed by an overnight stay.\"'),
(1997, 329, 'Chickmaglur-MysoreShravanabelagola-temple', '\"In the morning after breakfasts, we will proceed for Mysore by road. En-route, we will be visiting the Shravanabelagola temple, whcih is one of the major Jain shrines. There are various statues along with the famous statue of Gommateshwar around the temple.\r\nOn arrival at Mysore, check in at the hotel and take rest. After lunch, get ready for sightseeing tour of the \'City of Palaces\' Mysore. Well defined by scenic gardens, magnificent palaces, luxurious silks, fragrant sandalwood and festivals.\r\nHere, we will be visiting the Palace of Mysore also known as the Amba Vilas Palace. It is a splendid structure designed in the Indo-Saracenic style. Further, we will be visiting Chamundi Hill, Brindavan Garden – the famous gardens at the Krishna Raja Sagar Dam.\r\nLater, return back to the hotel to enjoy the delicious food and an overnight stay in the hotel.\"'),
(1998, 329, 'Mysore Sight Seeing- Chennai (By Train)lalitha-mahal-palace', '\"After breakfast, we will proceed for a visit to the Chamundeshwari Temple which is located on the top of Chamundi Hills and the Lalitha Mahal. Further, we visit the Kukkarahalli Lake also called Kukkarhalli Kere. This beautiful lake is located in the heart of the Mysore. Also, we will be visiting the art gallery of dayaganmohan Palace and the beautiful Karanji Lake. Later, we will transfer you to the railway station to board train to Chennai.\r\nOn arrive in Chennai, we will drive straight to Mammallapuram.\r\n(Suggested Train Shatabdi Express. It departs from Mysore @ 1415 Hrs and arrive Chennai @ 2125 Hrs with Total Travel time of 0710 Hrs)\"'),
(1999, 329, 'Mammallapuram- PondicherryMamallapuram-tour', '\"After breakfast, we will proceed to visit Mamallapuram. Later on, we will drive to Pondicherry. On arrival at Pondicherry, check in at the hotel. Evening is free for leisure to explore city, enjoy delicious meal. An overnight stay at the hotel.\r\nMamallapuram is a UNESCO World Heritage site and an architectural wonder of Dravidian style. As the name suggested, this temple overlooks the Bay of Bengal. Arjuna\'s Penance filled with detailed carvings, including a family of elephants and monkeys, Varaha Cave Temple, an example of Indian rock-cut architecture.\r\n\"'),
(2000, 329, 'Pondicherry', '\"The day is fixed to explore the beautiful Pondicherry city. Mamallapuram-tour\r\nPuducherry is a well-planned and beautiful city also known as \"\"The French Riviera of the East\"\" -Puducherry. It is now recognized as Pondicherry which was used to be a French colony. The city is blessed with lots of French element all around which gives it a unique look. Some of the major tourist places to be visited here are the beach, museum, Auriobindo ashram, Auroville, botanical gardens, and the French Quarter. Paradise beach of the city is famous for its beautiful half moon shape and dolphins.\r\nIn the evening, you can just revive your day experience and relax. Later return back to the hotel for dinner and an overnight stay.\"'),
(2001, 329, 'Pondicherry-Thanjavurthanjavur-temple', '\"Today early in the morning, we will travel by road to Thanjavur, also known as Tanjore, located on the eastern coast of Tamil Nadu. On arrival in Thanjavur, check in the hotel.\r\nTanjore is well known as \'the rice bowl of Tamil Nadu\'. It is famous for its arts and architecture from the time of the Cholas. The Cholas built most of the 93 odd temples here. The most famous one is the Brahadeeswarar Temple. It is one of most prized architectural sites of India. The temple was constructed more than thousand years ago by the King Rajarajan. Thanjavur is a thriving centre for bronze sculpture and painting. The uniqueness of the Tanjore paintings is their awesome gold leaf work, attractive jewellery with stones, dazzling color design, and eye catching carve glasses. These paintings will illuminate in the dark room. Some of the major places to visit in Tanjore are The Shrine of Sri Subramanya, Thanjavur Royal Palace, the Art Gallery and Museum, Schwartz Church and the Saraswati Mahal Library.\r\nLater in the evening return back to the hotel for dinner and an overnight stay in the hotel.\"'),
(2002, 329, 'Thanjavur- Karaikudikaraikudi-palace', '\"Early in the morning, we will drive to Karaikudi. On arrival, check in at the hotel. After breakfast, we will proceed to explore one of the biggest cities in the district of Sivaganga that lies in the Tamil Nadu state of India between two famous place of Trichy and Rameshwaram. A great place of worship, the place is famous for the temples dedicated to Ganesha or Pillaiyar, the elephant god.\r\nKaraikudi is famous for the Chettinad House that accommodate a number of peoples for gathering and celebrations. It is now converted into a magnificent museum.\r\nMajor tourist attractions of Karaikudi are Kamban Mani Mandapam, Pillaiyar Patti Lord Ganesha temple, Athangudi tiles factories, famous for handmade tiles and The Meenakshi-Sundareswarar temple.\r\nNow return back to the hotel to enjoy dinner and an overnight stay.\"'),
(2003, 329, 'Karaikudi-Maduraikaraikudi-palace', '\"Today in the morning, we will arrive at Madurai and check in to the hotel. After breakfast explore the city of Madurai.\r\nThe temple city of Madurai which means \"\"sweetness\"\" is an ancient city, located on the bank of the Vaigai River. It is surrounded by numerous mountains and 3 hills as its city boundary. Because of its rich cultural heritage and architectural magnificence, the city is often referred to as the \'Athens of the East\'. It is famous for Jasmine Flowers.\r\nMadurai is full of lively bazaars, pilgrims and rickshaws that attracts thousands of pilgrims and visitors for its magnificent monuments as the Gandhi Museum, constructed in the loving memory of the Father of the Nation and the Thirumalai Nayak Palace is an example of architectural splendor, the airy corridors of the Sri Meenakshi Amman Temple dedicated to goddess Parvati, Vandiyur Mariamman Teppakulam is the pond located near to Vandiyur Mariamman Temple.\r\nIn the evening, we will visit Athisayam park which is famous for its water rides, recreating the experience waterfalls and return back to the hotel for dinner and an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(2004, 329, 'Madurai-Periyar (Thekkady)periyar lake', '\"After breakfast in the morning, we will start our journey of the day for Periyar. We will drive through paddy fields and vast spice plantation. On arrival in Periyar, check in at hotel.\r\nPeriyar is famous for its wildlife sanctuary that owns a beautiful lake at the center. It is a permanent source of water for the local wildlife take a dip or to drink. Also known as the Thekkady Wildlife Sanctuary, this place is ideal for watching the animals in their natural habitat. The wildlife sanctuary is mainly known for its tiger reserve. Every year lots of tourist come here to see the Indian elephants, Tigers, Leopards, Malabar Flying Squirrels, etc.\r\nIn addition to elephant rides, visitors can sail on the lake and take a trip to the ruined Mangaladevi temple – an attractive old stone temple nestled in the heart of the Thekkady forest.\r\nAfter exploring the sanctuary return back to the hotel to fresh n\' up and enjoy delicious meal followed by an overnight stay.\"'),
(2005, 329, 'Periyar (Thekkady)periyar lake', '\"In the morning after breakfast, we will witness the splendid view of sunrise through Boat riding on Lake Periyar. It is also a great way to see the Flora and Fauna of the Sanctuary and spice plantations like pepper, coffee, cardamom, cinnamon, tea estates, coconut plantation, etc. Further, one can also see wild animals like elephants, deer, tigers and leopards.\r\nIn the afternoon, we will try Bamboo rafting and trekking, which is another unique activity in the Periyar National Park. One can take a hiking and rafting trip through the deep jungles of the Periyar Tiger Reserve and also visit Periyar National Park, which is situated in the hills of the Western Ghats.\r\nOn the way back to the hotel, you can stop at the local market and pick up some fragrant spices and get practical experience in Pollachi cooking techniques. An overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(2006, 329, 'Periyar (Thekkady) Alleppey Kerala Backwatersperiyar lake', '\"Today in the morning, we will start our journey to the rich beauty of coastal Kerala. On arrival, check in at the houseboat which is well equipped with all modern facilities.\r\nBackwaters of Kerala are a network of lakes, canals and deltas of forty-four rivers that drain into the Arabian Sea and are unique natures. They are found nowhere else in the world and are popular for water sports, traditional boat racing and the forests with coconut trees allure tourists from around the world.\r\nPlace to visit in Kerala are Alappuzha backwater, Kuttanadu, Ambablapuzha Shreekrishana Temple and Pathiramanal, a small island which is a favourite place of hundreds of rare migratory birds. And, you can visit the Guruvayur temple which is dedicated to Balagopalan, the child form of Lord Krishna lies at Guruvayur and popularly known as the Dwarka of the South.\r\nIn the evening, return back to the houseboats hotel and watch the romantic view of the sunset. Enjoy dinner and an overnight stay in the middle of the water.\"'),
(2007, 329, 'Alleppey-Kochicochin-fort', '\"In the morning, we will proceeds to Kochi. On arrival in Kochi, check in at the hotel. We will leave for sightseeing tour of Kochi.\r\nKochi is a modern city well known as the \"\"Heart of Kerala\"\". It is the overwhelming picturesque and prosperous state of Kerala, known as \'God\'s Own Country\' and also one of the finest natural harbours of the world and was the centre of the world spice trade for many centuries.\r\nOn the sightseeing tour of Kochi, we will walk along its streets and explore all its highlights, ancient churches, Dutch buildings, Portuguese artistic and British monuments. Some of the major tourist places in Kochi are the Cochin Fort, The splendid Bolghatty Palace and The Chinese fishing nets at Fort Kochi that uses a mechanical method to catch fishes.\r\nAt the sunset return back to the hotel to enjoy dinner followed by a night stay.\"'),
(2008, 329, 'Kochi Sightseeingcochin-fort', '\"In the morning after breakfast, we will enter the heart of through Kochi backwaters and coconut trees lining the glassy lake waters. We will continue our drive and stroll down to Marine Drive which is a beautiful passageway in Kochi, The Willington Island which is an artificial man-made island, Cherai Beach which is an ideal place for swimming, Munambam Beach, Parikshith Thampuran Museum and the Museum of Kerala.\r\nIn the evening, we will walk through the shopping area of Kochi that includes handicrafts, spices and nuts. Here, one can also enjoy a Kathakali dance performance.\r\nLater return back to the hotel to have dinner and an overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(2009, 329, 'Onward departure', 'In the morning, check-out from the hotel and transfer to railway-station for onward destination.'),
(2010, 330, 'Cochin - Munnar (140 kms / 4hrs) Munnar', '\"Drive to Munnar from Cochin in the morning. En-route oodles of natural splendors will greet you like rubber plantation, pineapple gardens, waterfalls, spice plantations. Moreover, as you will reach Munnar, you will see beautiful tea gardens all over the hills. On arrival, check in at pre-booked hotel and enjoy a comfortable overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(2011, 330, 'Munnar', 'In the morning after breakfast we will take you for a sightseeing tour of Munnar, which will include a visit to Mattupetty Dam, Kundala Lake, Eravikulam National Park, Tea Museum, Attukad Waterfalls and Blossom Park. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(2012, 330, 'Munnar - Kodaikanal (190 kms / 5 hours)', 'Check out from hotel and drive to Kodaikanal in the morning. En-route you can sight waterfalls, dams, orange and spice plantations. On arrival at Kodaikanal, check in at pre-booked hotel. In the evening you are free to have leisure time, followed by an overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(2013, 330, 'Kodaikanal - Kodaikanal lake', 'Morning after breakfast you enjoy full day sightseeing tour of Kodaikanal. The tour includes a visit to Coaker\'s Walk, 500 year old tree, Pamper Falls, (liril), Upper Lake View, Green Valley View, Golf Course, Pillar rocks, Guna cave, (Devils Kitchen), Pine Tree Forest, Shanthi Valley View, Bryant Park and Lake Boating. In the evening you are free to explore the local market. Overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(2014, 330, 'Kodaikanal - Ooty (270 kms / 6 hours)', '\"Morning after breakfast drive to Ooty. En-route you will visit Palani Temple and Mettupalayam Black Thunder. Upon arrival, check into a pre-booked hotel. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(2015, 330, 'Ooty - Ooty tour', 'In morning after breakfast full day sightseeing tour of Ooty, which includes a visit to Botanical Garden, Ooty Boat House (Ooty Lake), Rose Garden, St. Stephen\'s Church, Wax World museum. Evening free at leisure. Dinner and overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(2016, 330, 'Ooty - Coimbatore (120 kms / 3 hours)', '\"Post breakfast you are free to explore Ooty, later in the afternoon check out and drive to Coimbatore. Upon arrival, check into a hotel. In the evening you are free to explore the local market. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(2017, 330, 'Coimbatore - Cochin', 'Morning after breakfast drive back to Cochin.'),
(2018, 331, 'Arrive Coimbatore - Kodaikanal (145 Kms)', '\"Our representative will meet you on arrival at Coimbatore Railway station, thereafter drive to Kodaikanal. On arrival, check into a hotel. Rest of the day you are free for leisure. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(2019, 331, 'Kodaikanal', '\"After breakfast proceed for sightseeing tour of Kodaikanal, which includes a visit to Kurinji Andavar, Bryant\'s Park, Pillar\'s Rock, Coaker\'s Park, Green Valley View Point, Telescope House, Silent Valley View, Star Shaped Kodai Lake and Chettiar Park. Later in the evening transfer to the hotel for overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(2020, 331, 'Kodaikanal - Munnar (160 Kms)', '\"After breakfast drive to Munnar. On arrival at Munnar, check into a hotel. For the rest of the day you are free for enjoying your own activities. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(2021, 331, 'Munnar', '\"After breakfast, we will proceed for a full day sightseeing tour of Munnar. The tour will include a visit to Photo Point, Elephant Arrival Spot, Shooting Spot and Echo Point. Later, after lunch we will take you to the Tea Museum, Nyayamakad Waterfalls, Anamudi view, (RAJAMALA), \"\"SOUTH INDIA HIGHEST PEAK 8841 feet, 2695 meters\"\", Eravikulam National Park, Blossom Park, Pothamedu View, Plantations of Cardamom, Coffee & Pepper and Atukkad Waterfalls. In the evening transfer to the hotel for overnight stay.\r\n\"'),
(2022, 331, 'Munnar - Ooty (245 Kms)', '\"After breakfast drive to Ooty. Ooty is in deep within the Nilgiri hills that are also known as The Blue Mountains. On arrival at Ooty, check into a hotel and for therest of the day you are free for leisure. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(2023, 331, 'Ooty', '\"After breakfast proceed for sightseeing tour of Ooty. Visit the Botanical Garden, one of the best tourist attractions that allures visitors from all over the world. This garden was laid out in 1847 by the Marquis of Tweeddale and is spread over 22 hectares ascending the slopes on the hill at an elevation of 2,400 meters above sea level. Later visit Doddabetta (highest point of the place), Ooty Lake and Rose Garden.\r\nLocated in the heart of Ooty, Rose Park is not even a km from Charing Cross at Vijayanagaram. It has been laid on 10 acres of land in terraces with rose tunnels, pergolas and bowers with rose creepers. \r\nOvernight stay at the hotel.\"'),
(2024, 331, 'Ooty - Coimbatore (130 Kms)', 'After breakfast drive to Coimbatore. On arrival at Coimbatore we will transfer you to railway station for your onward destination.'),
(2025, 332, 'Arrive Cochin Butterfly Tour', '\"On arrival at Cochin Airport, meet our representative and transfer to the hotel. At hotel, meets with ornithologist for an overview of the itinerary. Enjoy a night stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(2026, 332, 'Cochin - Thattekkad', '\"After breakfast, drive to Thattekkad - This area is a butterfly country and one should sight such species as Malabar Rose (Pachliopta pandiyana), Blue Mormon (Papilio polymnestor), Paris Peacock (Papilio paris), Malabar Raven (Papilio dravidarum), Clipper (Parthenos sylvia), Gladeye Bushbrown (Mycalesis patnia), Tamil Catseye (Zipoetis saitis), White bar Bushbrown (Mycalesis anaxias) and the Red Pierrot (Talicada nyseus). \r\nOn arrival at Thattekkad, check-in at the hotel and enjoy an Overnight stay. Munnar\"'),
(2027, 332, 'Thattekkad - Munnar', 'Morning is free for watching butterflies. In the afternoon, take a drive to Munnar (120 Kms), the tea town of India. Also, we will visit to Rajamalai to see the endangered Nilgiri Tahr. This place is also home to several endemic bird and butterfly species. Birds like the Black winged Kite, Crested Serpent Eagle, Peregrine Falcon, Kestrel, Painted Bush quail, Rufous-backed Shrike, Grey headed Myna etc. are seen as well as butterflies like Bluebottle (Graphium sarpedon), Common Jezebel (Delias eucharis), Indian Cabbage White (Artogeia candida), Nilgiri Tiger (Parantica nilgiriensis), Red Helen (Papilio helenus), Tailed Jay (Graphium agamemnon), Giant Orange Tip (Hebomoia glaucippe), Red Disk Bushbrown (Mycalesis oculus), Palni Four Ring (Ypthima ypthimoides). An overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(2028, 332, 'Munnar - Chinnar - Munnar  Munnar', 'In the morning after breakfast go for excursion to Chinnar, (60 kms), the dry deciduous forest sanctuary in the rain shadow region of the Western Ghats. This sanctuary has large bird and butterfly population. You should see the rare Grizzled Giant Squirrel or the Star Tortoise, endemic to this region. Also, you should see birds such as the Common Peafowl, Grey Partridge, White-bellied Drongo, Indian black Robin, Green-billed Malkoha, Redwinged Crested Cuckoo etc. and butterflies like Yellow Pansy, Blue Pansy, Great Eggfly. Further, you should see Travancore Evening Brown (Parantirrhoea marshalli), Five-bar Swordtail (Pathysa antiphates), Southern Duffer (Discophora lepida), Cruise (Vindula erota), Tamil Lacewing (Cethosia nietneri) Malabar Banded Swallowtail (Papilio liomedon). In the evening return to Munnar and enjoy an overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(2029, 332, 'Munnar - Periyar  Periyar', 'In the morning after breakfast go for excursion to Chinnar, (60 kms), the dry deciduous forest sanctuary in the rain shadow region of the Western Ghats. This sanctuary has large bird and butterfly population. You should see the rare Grizzled Giant Squirrel or the Star Tortoise, endemic to this region. Also, you should see birds such as the Common Peafowl, Grey Partridge, White-bellied Drongo, Indian black Robin, Green-billed Malkoha, Redwinged Crested Cuckoo etc. and butterflies like Yellow Pansy, Blue Pansy, Great Eggfly. Further, you should see Travancore Evening Brown (Parantirrhoea marshalli), Five-bar Swordtail (Pathysa antiphates), Southern Duffer (Discophora lepida), Cruise (Vindula erota), Tamil Lacewing (Cethosia nietneri) Malabar Banded Swallowtail (Papilio liomedon). In the evening return to Munnar and enjoy an overnight stay at the hotel.'),
(2030, 332, 'Periyar', 'Early morning butterfly watching trip alongside the banks of the lakes & streams, which are abound here. Short treks into the forest should yield very rewarding butterfly sightings. In the evening, get back to the hotel for an Overnight stay.'),
(2031, 332, 'Periyar - Cochin drop', 'After breakfast transfer to Cochin Airport for your onward destination.'),
(2032, 334, 'Arrive Coimbatore - Ooty (130 Kms)', '\"Meet our representative on arrival at Coimbatore railway station and drive straight to Ooty. On arrival, check into a hotel. Rest of the day you are free for leisure. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(2033, 334, 'Ooty', '\"After breakfast proceed for sightseeing tour of Ooty. Visit the Botanical Garden, one of the best tourist attractions that allures visitors from all over the world. This garden was laid out in 1847 by the Marquis of Tweedale and is spread over 22 hectares ascending the slopes on the hill at an elevation of 2,400 meters above sea level. Later visit Doddabetta (highest point of the place), Ooty Lake and Rose Garden.\r\nLocated in the heart of Ooty, Rose Park is not even a km from Charing Cross at Vijayanagaram. It has been laid on 10 acres of land in terraces with rose tunnels, pergolas and bowers with rose creepers. \r\nOvernight stay at the hotel.\"'),
(2034, 334, 'Ooty - Wayanad (115 Kms)', '\"After breakfast drive to Wayanad. On arrival, check into the hotel. In the evening you are free for your own activities. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(2035, 334, 'Wayanad', '\"After breakfast proceed to Wayanad Wildlife Sanctuary. Later, visit the Pookode Natural Lake, Soochipara Waterfalls, Muthanga Wildlife Sanctuary and Edakkal Caves (a prehistoric shelter made of natural rock formation). Throughout this journey you can enjoy different types of spice plantations like cardamom, vanilla, pepper, cinnamon, clove etc. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"'),
(2036, 334, 'Wayanad - Coorg (110 Kms)', '\"After breakfast drive to Coorg. On arrival, check into a hotel. Rest of the day you are free for leisure or your own activity. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n\"');
INSERT INTO `tour_daywise` (`itinerydata_id`, `tour_id`, `itinerydata_title`, `itinerydata_description`) VALUES
(2037, 334, 'Coorg - Coorg-Brahmagiri-Peak', 'After breakfast full day city tour of Coorg, visit Dubare Elephant Camp, a forest camp on the banks of the River Kaveri where bathing and feeding of the elephants are done. Dubare elephant camp in Coorg is the perfect destination to enjoy Elephant rides and bird watching. In afternoon visit to Talacauvery, which is situated in the picturesque location of Brahmagiri hills. It is the origin of River Kaveri and a beautiful Talacauvery Temple built around it. Later, climb Brahmagiri peak and then pay a visit to Bhagamandala. Bhagamandala is famous for the confluence of the three sacred rivers, Kaveri, Sujyothi and Kanike. You can also visit to the temple dedicated to Bhagandeshwara (Lord Shiva) and get the blessings. Return to the hotel by evening for overnight stay.'),
